<p data-start="128" data-end="179"> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> Good morning.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> Hi. This is Shelley Mayer.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">I’m renting your house on Archwood Avenue. I’m due to move in next week.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> Oh yes, hello Ms Mayer. What can I do for you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> When I viewed the house, I told you I’ll most probably need to rent some furniture – at least until I know whether my temporary work contract is going to be made permanent.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> Yes of course, I remember.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">And I said I could give you some information about furniture rental companies in the city.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> That’s right.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> Well, the biggest company is called Peak Rentals.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">I’ve recommended them to other people and have always heard positive reports about them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> Could you give me an idea of their costs?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> Sure, I actually have one of their brochures here.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">It says the monthly price per room starts at a hundred and five dollars and goes up to<span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">two hundred and thirty-nine dollars</strong> (Q1)</span> – that depends on which rooms you need furniture for, of course.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> Sure. It’s just to get a general idea of how much it’s gonna cost.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">And you said you had some positive feedback about this company.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> Yes, people have mentioned that the furniture from Peak Rentals is more<span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">modern</strong> (Q2)</span> than any of the other companies.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\">And also, once you place an order, the furniture will be delivered to you in just one or two days.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> That would be really helpful.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> Oh, and the brochure says that there’s a special offer at the moment.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\">If you rent living room furniture – I believe that’s a set of chairs and a TV table, you’ll also get a<span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"103\">lamp</strong> (Q3)</span> at no extra cost.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> OK. But, you know, that price range you gave is more than I was hoping to pay.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> Then you could try <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">Aaron</strong> (Q4) </span>and Oliver.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> Sorry, what and Oliver?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> Aaron. Double-A-R-O-N.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> OK. Are they cheaper?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> I’d say they’re a mid-price company.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\">But if you chose them, you need to be aware that they charge an extra twelve per cent every month in case of <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"109\">damage</strong> (Q5)</span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> Oh I see. I’d have to do the math carefully then.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> Right. But one helpful thing is that they also do cleaning for customers.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> For the furniture?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> For the house.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> Oh I see. I probably won’t need that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> There’s another company called Larch Furniture.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\">It’s quite new, and it has the lowest prices in town.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"39\">That’s for both furniture and also <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">electronic</strong> (Q6) </span>equipment.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"40\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"40\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> Well that would be good.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"41\">I’m not bringing much with me, and I won’t have much time to go shopping after I start my job.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"42\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"42\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> There are two things you need to know about Larch Furniture.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"43\">First of all, you have to take out <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"43\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">insurance</strong> (Q7)</span> on the furniture, and you need to organise that yourself.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"44\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"44\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> That wouldn’t be too hard.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"45\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"45\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> Also, you can’t take out a contract for less than six months, but I figure that might not be a problem for you.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"46\">You’re renting the house for twelve months after all, aren’t you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"47\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"47\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> Yes. OK, well I…</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"48\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"48\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> … sorry to interrupt. I just thought of another furniture rental company.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"49\">It’s called <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"49\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Space</strong> (Q8) </span>Rentals. And it’s located very near to the house.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"50\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"50\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> OK.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"51\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"51\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> I don’t have any information about their charges, so it’s best to use their <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"51\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">app</strong> (Q9)</span> to find out what it would cost you to use them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"52\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"52\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> OK thanks. I’ll do that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"53\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"53\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MAN:</strong> One good thing about that company is that if you don’t like the furniture once it’s delivered, you can request <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"53\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">exchanges</strong> (Q10)</span> – as long as you do that within a week of receiving it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"54\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"54\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SHELLEY:</strong> That sounds really great. OK. Well thanks very much. That’s so helpful …</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('17c28024-4989-488c-9584-e0ae1878a7c7', '17f083a4-c2c5-49fa-ad24-d014daf2ce98', 'radio', 'Questions 11–16', '', '<p><em>Choose the correct answer.</em></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>THE MIDDLETOWN URBAN FARMING SCHEME (MUFS)</strong></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "university specialists"}, {"option_text": "business people"}, {"option_text": "town planners"}], "question": "Who founded the Middletown Urban Farming Scheme?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "to encourage more efficient land use"}, {"option_text": "to help lessen CO2 emissions"}, {"option_text": "to improve people’s eating habits"}], "question": "What was the original reason for starting the MUFS?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "schools"}, {"option_text": "companies."}, {"option_text": "community centres."}], "question": "For the coming year, the MUFS will focus on recruiting members from"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "practical gardening tips"}, {"option_text": "plant science"}, {"option_text": "location of local garden sites"}], "question": "What kind of information is available from members of the MUFS committee?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "soil and compost"}, {"option_text": "containers for plants"}, {"option_text": "gardening tools"}], "question": "What are provided by the MUFS for the physically disabled?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "its usefulness as an aid for teaching science"}, {"option_text": "its contribution to reducing costs of school meals"}, {"option_text": "its help in encouraging community pride among students"}], "question": "According to school teachers, what has been an unexpected advantage of the MUFS?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Chris Butler:</strong> I’m Chris Butler, and I’m the chairperson of the Middletown Urban Farming Scheme, or MUFS for short—a highly successful program which encourages city dwellers to grow their own fruit and vegetables, to become “city farmers” if you will.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">Who started MUFS? Well, the idea of urban farming has been around for quite a while, particularly among town planners. <strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"119\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q11) But it was actually a group of Middletown business people, including myself, who decided to create what became MUFS</span>.</strong> University agriculture specialists got involved later.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Now initially, the aim was not some eco-friendly goal of reducing CO2 emissions caused by the transport of food from farm to dinner plate. <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"139\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q12) It was simply to maximize the utilization of the vacant or idle land that lies within the city</span>.</strong> Of course, later we realized that an additional benefit might be a healthier diet for local people.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Let me tell you a bit about the groups that have joined the scheme. We’ve got any number of schools involved and loads of corporate employees, so our message seems to have been well received there. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"198\">(Q13) But for next year, we’re going to concentrate on getting various community centres, like those for senior citizens, to join</strong></span>, because so far they’ve been somewhat slow to take up the scheme.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Now the core committee of the MUFS is a group of dedicated gardeners. They probably won’t be familiar with your specific plot of land—they’re mostly amateurs—but <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">(Q14) they are the people who know the ins and outs of gardening. And they will be happy to sit down with any MUFS member and make some hands-on suggestions about gardening.</strong></span> But don’t expect them to know the answers to technical questions like the Latin names of plants.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">The MUFS are keen to support members who are physically disabled. We’re looking at the possibility of providing specially adapted gardening tools on loan to members who can’t cope with regular tools—that’s not happening yet—but <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"228\">(Q15) we do have some window boxes as well as larger containers which we can distribute free of charge to these members</strong></span>, although they will have to provide their own soil and compost themselves.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">I’m especially proud of the work we’ve done with the local schools, both grade school level and high schools. The teachers say that they knew the scheme would be of some practical use in science classes like biology. Despite the original hopes of some, the fruit and vegetable plots haven’t provided cheaper lunches for their students, but what they didn’t anticipate was the change in attitude that the scheme has created amongst their students. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"447\">(Q16) They say the students have become much more conscious of their surrounding environment; they want to keep it neat and tidy.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Chris Butler:</strong> Now, a number of local organizations and businesses provide our members with free goods and services. Let me go through some of them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">The city hospital, as you might expect, has to provide thousands of meals for its patients. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">(Q17) So, the manager of its kitchen runs a course for our members on how to use vegetables in a huge variety of dishes.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">The local government found it had a large glass building which the parks department used to start off flower seeds and young plants during the winter, and <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"155\">(Q18) they agreed to allow our members to use this free of charge to get their own little seedlings off to a good start.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">Another thing:<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">(Q19) the university has agreed that if members send them a sample of their soil, they will do a series of tests on it to indicate what kind of plants will grow best</strong></span> and what types of fertilizer and nutrients would be best to use.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">And just to make sure our members know what’s good for them, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">(Q20) a supermarket is offering a series of classes on how to lose weight and stay healthy by having a sensible diet.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">Now, let’s talk about the practicalities…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a839af8b-c968-4824-9d3a-ad2410b3a645', 'cb106480-bfc8-4317-ba8e-6dc776768e44', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', '', '<p data-start="105" data-end="307">Choose <strong data-start="112" data-end="120">TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong data-start="192" data-end="201">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong data-start="258" data-end="271">NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "An inspection fee on fish oil was introduced in New York in 1818"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Samuel Judd argued that the inspection fee should exclude whale oil"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Judd had been in trouble with city officials before the inspection fee disagreement"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Many New Yorkers were interested in the court case at the time"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Traditionally, non-human creatures had been classified in one of three groups"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Generally speaking, ordinary people thought fish were the lowest form of life"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Whales were excluded from the Linnaean system in 1818"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('62763967-294c-4b78-a405-2592a047b063', '30a3bb93-86d4-4720-958e-82d89d774bf5', 'matrix', 'Questions 1-8', '', '<p>Write the correct letter, <strong>A-E</strong>, in boxes 1-8 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p>NB You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The reviewer thinks some of the cast are unsuitable for their roles.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "The dialogue in this film seems unrealistic.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "The reviewer found this film unexpectedly emotional.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "This film contains dialogue that is uninteresting for some viewers.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "This film carries a moral message.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Non-actors take part in this film.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "The reviewer thinks this film should be seen again.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "This film mentions things that audience members won''t know about.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. The reviewer thinks some of the cast are unsuitable for their roles. — {E: Uplands}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “But the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">two lead actors are at their best in thrillers</strong>, not films like this one. James Petherick… <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">fails to gain the sympathy</strong> of the audience…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Người đánh giá cho rằng hai diễn viên chính hợp đóng phim giật gân hơn là phim này, và nam chính không chiếm được cảm tình của khán giả (unsuitable).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. The dialogue in this film seems unrealistic. — {C: The Jeffersons}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…neither she nor the other actors could <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">make the script sound natural</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Sound natural” (nghe tự nhiên) tương ứng với “realistic”. Việc diễn viên không thể làm kịch bản nghe tự nhiên đồng nghĩa với việc lời thoại bị giả/không thực tế (unrealistic).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. The reviewer found this film unexpectedly emotional. — {A: Purple Rainbow}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “And the support that band members gave… <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">had me close to tears</strong>, giving me a new appreciation of the band.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Close to tears” (suýt khóc) thể hiện sự xúc động mạnh (emotional). Người viết vốn tưởng phim chỉ có nhạc và thoại yếu nhưng kết quả lại khiến họ cảm động.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. This film contains dialogue that is uninteresting for some viewers. — {B: Home Fires}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…many children would find the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">long discussions of relationship issues boring</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Uninteresting” tương ứng với “boring”. Những cuộc thảo luận dài về mối quan hệ bị coi là nhàm chán đối với đối tượng trẻ em.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. This film carries a moral message. — {D: Space Challenge 5}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “This film makes an <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">important ethical point about treating other people with respect</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Ethical point” (điểm đạo đức) tương ứng với “moral message” (thông điệp đạo đức/nhân văn).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Non-actors take part in this film. — {A: Purple Rainbow}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Their <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"18\">fans in the film were actual fans</strong> of the group…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những người đóng vai người hâm mộ trong phim chính là những fan thật ngoài đời, không phải diễn viên chuyên nghiệp (non-actors).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. The reviewer thinks this film should be seen again. — {B: Home Fires}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “It’s certainly <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">worth a second viewing</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Worth a second viewing” (đáng để xem lần thứ hai) đồng nghĩa với “should be seen again”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. This film mentions things that audience members won’t know about. — {D: Space Challenge 5}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…as it assumes <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">familiarity with the world as it was 20 years ago</strong>. …many of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">references will leave them confused</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Phim nhắc đến những sự kiện/bối cảnh từ 20 năm trước khiến khán giả trẻ ngày nay thấy bối rối/không biết tới (won’t know about).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('34829bff-80d8-4a79-b1bd-c379d6250b70', '53d6e3a3-9589-46fc-bd5c-b49210cced68', 'checkbox', 'Questions 23-24', '', '<p data-start="514" data-end="546">Choose <strong data-start="521" data-end="528">TWO</strong> letters, <strong data-start="538" data-end="545">A–E</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="548" data-end="659">Which <strong>TWO</strong> ways do the students agree that touch-sensitive sensors for food labels could be developed in future?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A for use on medical products"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B to show that food is no longer fit to eat"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C for use with drinks as well as foods"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D to provide applications for blind people"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "E to indicate weight of certain foods"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6a2f2877-4841-4ee1-88fc-aea40f2be325', '520f0653-78ff-4aa9-bc98-43e1eb823d79', 'fillup', 'Questions 1-10', '<p data-start="103" data-end="156"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">Write <strong data-start="109" data-end="137">ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</span></p>
<p data-start="158" data-end="253"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">Local councils can arrange practical support to help those caring for elderly people at home.</span></p>
<p data-start="255" data-end="336"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">This can give the carer:</span><br data-start="279" data-end="282"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">• time for other responsibilities</span><br data-start="315" data-end="318"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">• a  {break}</span></span></p>
<p data-start="338" data-end="372"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-start="338" data-end="370">Assessment of mother’s needs</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="374" data-end="497"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">This may include discussion of:</span><br data-start="405" data-end="408"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">• how much  {time}</span><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;"> the caring involves</span><br data-start="451" data-end="454"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">• what types of tasks are involved, e.g.:</span></p>
<ul data-start="500" data-end="630">
<li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;" data-start="500" data-end="522">
<p data-start="502" data-end="522"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">help with dressing</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;" data-start="525" data-end="560">
<p data-start="527" data-end="560"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">helping her have a  {shower}</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;" data-start="563" data-end="575">
<p data-start="565" data-end="575"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">shopping</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;" data-start="578" data-end="600">
<p data-start="580" data-end="600"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">helping with meals</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;" data-start="603" data-end="630">
<p data-start="605" data-end="630"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">dealing with  {money}</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="54" data-end="116"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">• any aspects of caring that are especially difficult, e.g.:</span></p>
<ul data-start="119" data-end="198">
<li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;" data-start="119" data-end="143">
<p data-start="121" data-end="143"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">loss of  {memory}</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;" data-start="146" data-end="166">
<p data-start="148" data-end="166"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;"> {lifting} her</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;" data-start="169" data-end="198">
<p data-start="171" data-end="198"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">preventing a  {fall}</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="200" data-end="252"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-start="200" data-end="250">Types of support that may be offered to carers</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="254" data-end="407"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">• transport costs, e.g. cost of a  {taxi}</span><br data-start="300" data-end="303"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">• car-related costs, e.g. fuel and  {insurance}</span><br data-start="350" data-end="353"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">• help with housework</span><br data-start="374" data-end="377"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;">• help to reduce  {stress}</span></p>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>(Questions 1–4)<br> </p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: It’s really good to see you Tom.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Since I had to give up work I feel I’m losing touch with my friends and colleagues.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: We really miss you in the office.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: We were all so sorry you had to leave.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: But you must be relieved to have more time to look after your mother.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: How is she?</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Well she’s very cheerful but she needs a lot of help.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: Have you tried to get any support from the local council?</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: No, I didn’t know I could.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: Yes, they offer different kinds of practical support.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: They realise that carers sometimes need time for all the other responsibilities they have, apart from the person they’re caring for, and also that they sometimes need a break.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Absolutely.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Okay, so tell me more.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: How do I go about getting this support?</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: Well you’d have to have an assessment of your mother’s needs. (Question 1)</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: That means someone would come round and talk to you about the situation and what you need.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: So for a start they’d want to know the amount of time you spend looking after your mother every day.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Okay.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: Then they’ll probably ask you what sorts of tasks you do for your mother during the day.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: Things like if she needs help with getting dressed for example.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Right, I do help her with that, and also I help her get into the shower in the morning. (Question 2)</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: Yes, that sort of thing.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: They’ll probably ask you if you do the shopping for her and help her at meal times, and whether she can cope using money. (Question 3)</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Yes, that’s becoming a bit of a problem.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: She used to be very good at it, but not anymore.</p>\n<p> <br> </p>\n<p>2. Những Khó khăn và Hỗ trợ (Questions 5–10)<br> </p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: And be ready to tell them about anything you find particularly difficult about caring for your mother.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: So recently I’ve noticed she’s started to have quite bad problems with her memory. (Question 4)</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: If I wasn’t there, I think she’d forget to eat, for example.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: And often she doesn’t seem quite sure what day it is.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: Yes, tell them about that.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: And are there any physical difficulties you have caring for her?</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: Lifting her, for example. (Question 5)</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Yes, she’s quite heavy, and I’m afraid of hurting my back.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: I’d be in real trouble if that happened.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: They can give you advice about that, and also about how to avoid the possibility of your mum having a fall. (Question 6)</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Great.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: So once they’ve done this assessment, if I’m eligible, what happens next?</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: Well, they might support you financially, so they might help you with transport costs, like if you have to get a taxi to take your mother for an appointment, for example.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: I usually drive her myself, actually.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: So, could I claim for the petrol? (Question 7)</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: You could.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: And you can claim for the insurance, too. (Question 8)</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Oh, right.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: And if you need help with the housework, they can arrange for someone to come along once or twice a week. (Question 9)</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: And one other thing.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: I hope you don’t mind me saying this, but it’s important you look after yourself.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: And it seems to me you’re under quite a bit of stress.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: I am, yes.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 2: Well, tell the council, because they may be able to give you some advice on how to minimise it (stress). (Question 10)</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Really?</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Though, actually, I feel so much better having talked to you.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: I’ll get in touch with the council straight away.</p>\n<p>SPEAKER 1: Now, shall we go for coffee?</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0a2a113b-b21f-4157-ace2-d4a2b9787c8e', '0d78bc92-e925-46c5-9ef8-0664e6cfbc3d', 'fillup', 'Questions 18–21', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the summary below:</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>The history of herbal medicines in New Zealand</strong></span></p>
<p>Originally, the Maori people consumed plants to help deal with {pain} and also as food. When Europeans settled in the country, a  {book} by James Neil showed that some of them also recognized the medicinal value of native plants. However, criticism of herbal medicine appeared in one newspaper in 1907. The following year, the use of herbal medicines was made more difficult because of a new {law} , and for a time in the mid-20th century, they were largely ignored. Then, in the 1980s, a number of institutions started offering a  {course}<span class="fill-history-correct"> </span> in the subject, although for many years there was still little evidence to support their use because doctors and academics were not interested.</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. {pain}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…the forest was well stocked with edible plants that were an obvious source of nutrition, but that were taken for the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">relief of pain</strong> as well.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Người Maori dùng cây cỏ làm thức ăn (nutrition/food) và để giảm đau (relief of pain).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. {book}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…in his <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">book</strong> published in 1891, herbalist James Neil described manuka and koromiko as among New Zealand’s most valuable herbs.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> James Neil đã công nhận giá trị của thảo dược bản địa thông qua cuốn sách xuất bản năm 1891 của ông.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. {law}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In 1908 the government passed a controversial <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">law</strong> that had the effect of restricting traditional herbal practice…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một đạo luật mới (law) năm 1908 đã gây khó khăn và hạn chế việc hành nghề thảo dược truyền thống.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. {course}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…it became possible to complete a <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">course</strong> in herbal medicine at several polytechnics around the country.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vào những năm 1980, các trường bách khoa (institutions) bắt đầu cung cấp các khóa học (course) về chủ đề này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bd527bf7-8b29-499d-85a0-c73e6ed62512', '3bddf77b-e479-402d-938a-f2dd4deb4c5b', 'matrix', 'Questions 5-8', '', '<p>Reading Passage 1 has seven paragraphs, <strong>A-G</strong>.</p>
<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p><strong>NB </strong>You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Examples of things that affect the distance sound can travel in water.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Details of the connection between ocean temperatures and climate.", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Details of ways in which light and sound are similar.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a reference to a long-term study of different types of weather", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Examples of things that affect the distance sound can travel in water. — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “A number of factors influence how far sound travels under water… including <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">particles, salinity, temperature and pressure</strong>.” (Đoạn C)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Details of the connection between ocean temperatures and climate. — {F}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…obtain information crucial to our understanding of <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">climate</strong>. The system has enabled researchers to begin making <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">ocean temperature measurements</strong> on a global scale…” (Đoạn F)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Details of ways in which light and sound are similar. — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Particles in seawater can reflect, scatter and absorb certain frequencies of <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">sound</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">just as</strong> certain wavelengths of <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">light</strong> may be reflected, scattered and absorbed…” (Đoạn C)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C so sánh sự tương đồng giữa âm thanh và ánh sáng khi cả hai đều bị phản xạ, tán xạ và hấp thụ bởi các hạt phân tử.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. A reference to a long-term study of different types of weather. — {G}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Since 1985</strong>, Nystuen has used hydrophones to listen to rain over the ocean… ranging from <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">drizzle to thunderstorms</strong>.” (Đoạn G)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khoảng thời gian từ 1985 đến nay là dài hạn (<em data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">long-term</em>) và các loại mưa chính là các loại hình thời tiết (<em data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">weather</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7ab805c2-aea6-4e20-98f7-3e3795dd71d8', '8ab18682-6a52-4089-97e3-8322fe967131', 'fillup', ' Questions 1–10', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<p class="txt"><em>Complete the notes below. </em><em>Write </em><strong><em>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER </em></strong><em>for each answer.</em></p>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: center;"><strong>SWIMMING LESSONS</strong></p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: center;">Classes available</p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border: 1px solid #000000;" border="1">
<colgroup>
<col width="144" />
<col width="524" />
<col width="100" /></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-row="row-7art">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-7art"><em> Example</em></p>
<p>Water</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-7art"><em>Answer</em></p>
<p><strong><em><u>Babies</u></em></strong></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p>For babies of three months upwards</p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000; width: 99.9495%; height: 122.917px;" border="1">
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 20.3994%;" width="143" />
<col style="width: 74.465%;" width="522" />
<col style="width: 14.2653%;" width="100" /></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 61.4583px;" data-row="row-mri5">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-mri5"> Focus</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-mri5">water familiarisation using {toys}</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 61.4583px;" data-row="row-ctt0">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-ctt0"> Cost</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-ctt0">£ 3.80 per lesson</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Beginners</strong></p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">For people with no experience of swimming</p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" border="1">
<colgroup>
<col width="147" />
<col width="514" />
<col width="100" /></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-row="row-8lhq">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-8lhq"> Focus</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-8lhq">– {breathing} techniques</p>
<p>– opening the eyes underwater</p>
<p>– swimming five metres</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Intermediate</strong></p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" border="1">
<colgroup>
<col width="144" />
<col width="504" />
<col width="100" /></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-row="row-72yd">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-72yd"> Focus</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-72yd">– learning main swimming strokes</p>
<p>– introduction to {diving}</p>
<p>– swimming underwater</p>
<p>– {safety} in the water</td>
</tr>
<tr data-row="row-ro99">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-ro99"> Cost</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-ro99">£61 per course</td>
</tr>
<tr data-row="row-4j9d">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-4j9d"> Other information:</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-4j9d">– maximum of 12 pupils per class</p>
<p>– class is for {adults}</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Advances</strong></p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" border="1">
<colgroup>
<col width="142" />
<col width="502" />
<col width="100" /></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-row="row-truv">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-truv"> Focus:</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-truv">– more efficient techniques</p>
<p>– improving {speed}</p>
<p>– competitions</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Other information</strong></p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Date when Intermediate course begins: Tuesday {January 13th|January 13|13th January|13 January} (need to register soon)</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Time: 7.30 p.m.</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Participants will be provided with a swimming {hat}</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Bring change for the {locker}</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;"><strong>Benefits of swimming</strong></p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Health benefits</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Improvement in {confidence}</p>
<p class="content-write" style="text-align: left;">– Could save a life</p>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a man telephoning to ask for information about swimming lessons. First you have some time to look at questions 1 to 6 on page two. You will see that there is an example that has been done for you. On this occasion only the conversation relating to this will be played first.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Hello City Swim School.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Oh, Hello. Uh, I wanted to ask about swimming lessons. That’s in a class, not individual, right?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, we do group lessons at various levels. To start off with, we have what we call the Water Babies class.</p>\n<p><strong>(Narrator)</strong> The first class is called Water Babies, so babies has been written in the space. Now we shall begin. You should answer the questions as you listen because you will not hear the recording a second time. Listen carefully and answer questions 1 to six.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Hello City Swim School.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Oh, Hello. Uh, I wanted to ask about swimming lessons. That’s in a class, not individual, right?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, we do group lessons at various levels. To start off with, we have what we call the Water Babies class. That’s for babies of three months and over.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Really, as young as that?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Yes, that’s really the best time to start.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Right. Well, we do have a baby so I’ll make a note of that. Um, what do they actually do in the lessons?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, the main aim is just to familiarise them with the water, so they feel at ease there. They get the children to enjoy themselves. They have lots of <strong>(1) toys</strong> and things they can use to play with in the water.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Right. And how much do the lessons cost?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> They’re held on Tuesday mornings and each lesson costs £3 80. It’s not really a course as such.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Okay, well, I’ll talk to my wife about that. Uh, but I was actually ringing about lessons for me.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Okay, so are you a beginner?</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Not exactly, but I’m not very good. (ha)</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, the beginner’s classes are really for people who don’t have any experience of swimming. They aim to teach you techniques for <strong>(2) breathing</strong> in the water, and they get you to do things like put your head underwater and open your eyes.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Okay, I can do that.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> And by the end of the course, they aim to have you swimming five metres.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> I think I can probably just about do that.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> OK, so you’d be better in the intermediate class then. That’s where you learn the main swimming strokes—front stroke, back stroke, and so on.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> What about <strong>(3) diving</strong>?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Yes, they’d teach you how to do that, and you’d also do some underwater swimming. Not with a tank or anything.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Oh no, not scuba, just ordinary underwater swimming.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> And in the intermediate course, you also look at water <strong>(4) safety</strong>. Both in the pool and when swimming in other places.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Okay, well, that sounds the right level for me.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> I think so. How much does that cost?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> <strong>£61</strong> for a course. That’s 10 lessons.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Can you tell me a bit more about the class? How many people would there be in it?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, the intermediate class is usually around 8 to 10. That’s what we aim at, though occasionally it might go up to twelve.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> OK, that sounds quite a reasonable size. Not too many. And the class is for <strong>(5) adults</strong>, is it?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Yes.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> OK. And just out of interest, is there an advanced class?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Yes. They focus on developing more efficient swimming techniques and on working on your <strong>(6) speed</strong>. And they also prepare you for competitive swimming.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Okay. Now I think I’d want to start with the intermediate one, really.</p>\n<p><strong>(Narrator)</strong> Before you hear the rest of the conversation, you have some time to look at questions 7 to 10 on page three. Now listen and answer questions 7 to ten.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Now, is there anything special I need to know?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, the classes are on Tuesdays, and the first lesson is on <strong>(7) January the thirteenth</strong>. So you need to register before then. January the 8th is the latest, but it’s filling up quickly, so I’d do it straight away. You can pick up a form here or get one off the internet.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> And classes are at 7:30 PM. Right. Then I just roll up with my swimming trunks. Do I have to bring my own towel?</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> That’s right. We provide all participants with a swimming <strong>(8) hat</strong> though.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Oh, huh. I don’t usually wear one.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Well, we do insist on it, actually. It helps the instructor to identify you, apart from anything else. Oh, and don’t forget you need a 20p coin for the <strong>(9) locker</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> Oh, okay. Right. Well, I’ve been meaning to do this for ages. I really need to get some more exercise. And everyone says swimming is good for your health.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Yes, and a lot of people find it improves their <strong>(10) confidence</strong> too. And of course, it could save your life or even someone else’s.</p>\n<p><strong>Man:</strong> That’s right. Okay, well, thanks very much.</p>\n<p><strong>School:</strong> Goodbye.</p>\n<p><strong>(Narrator)</strong> That is the end of Section 1. You now have half a minute to check your answers.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('af118855-f9d5-42df-a549-e0de91ec8181', 'cb106480-bfc8-4317-ba8e-6dc776768e44', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–13', '<p data-start="1081" data-end="1155">Complete the notes. Write <strong data-start="1107" data-end="1124">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="1157" data-end="1186"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The Trial of December 1818</span></strong></p>
<p data-start="1188" data-end="1209"><strong>The Personalities</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1211" data-end="1433">
<li data-start="1211" data-end="1268">
<p data-start="1213" data-end="1268">Samuel Mitchill worked as a congressman and a {lecturer}.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1269" data-end="1336">
<p data-start="1271" data-end="1336">The defence wanted Mitchill to present the biology of the case.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1337" data-end="1433">
<p data-start="1339" data-end="1433">William Sampson called {whalers} as witnesses in order to appeal to the common sense of the jury.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1435" data-end="1452"><strong>The Arguments</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1454" data-end="1667">
<li data-start="1454" data-end="1526">
<p data-start="1456" data-end="1526">Sampson’s case was based on the consequences for humans if Judd won.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1527" data-end="1599">
<p data-start="1529" data-end="1599">Mitchill admitted that scientists had disputes about classification.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1600" data-end="1667">
<p data-start="1602" data-end="1667">New Yorkers disliked Mitchill because his ideas came from {Europe}.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1669" data-end="1684"><strong>Conclusions</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1686" data-end="1914">
<li data-start="1686" data-end="1785">
<p data-start="1688" data-end="1785">In the end it was statements from local {merchants}, not Mitchill’s testimony which helped Judd win.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1786" data-end="1840">
<p data-start="1788" data-end="1840">Whale oil made a good {fuel} because it was clean.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1841" data-end="1914">
<p data-start="1843" data-end="1914">Judd’s case is relevant today, e.g. in the debate about Earth’s {climate}.</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7dfe1dd0-9221-4c10-a145-5ffdc790253d', '30a3bb93-86d4-4720-958e-82d89d774bf5', 'matrix', 'Questions 9–14', '', '<p id="p-rc_33670399215acaa1-280" data-path-to-node="4"><span class="citation-9855 citation-9856 citation-9857 citation-9858 citation-9859">Write the correct letter, </span><strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="26"><span class="citation-9855 citation-9856 citation-9857 citation-9858 citation-9859">A–D</span></strong><span class="citation-9855 citation-9856 citation-9857 citation-9858 citation-9859 citation-end-9859">, in boxes 9–14 on your answer sheet.</span></p>
<p id="p-rc_33670399215acaa1-281" data-path-to-node="5"><strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-9850 citation-9851 citation-9852 citation-9853 citation-9854">NB</span></strong><span class="citation-9850 citation-9851 citation-9852 citation-9853 citation-9854 citation-end-9854"> You may use any letter more than once.</span></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "You see spectacular scenery.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "You are provided with special clothing.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "You may be watched while you are doing the activity.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "You watch someone else before doing the activity yourself.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "You meet people who are expert at the activity.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "You can raise money for a charity.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. You see spectacular scenery. — {B: The Pioneer}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…awe-inspiring… pristine Southern Alps. …where <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">soaring mountain peaks, crystal-clear lakes</strong>, and high country await.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Spectacular scenery” (phong cảnh ngoạn mục) tương ứng với những mô tả về đỉnh núi cao và hồ nước trong vắt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. You are provided with special clothing. — {C: Race Drive Experience}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…before being fully <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">kitted out with one of our race suits and safety helmet</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khách hàng được trang bị bộ đồ đua xe và mũ bảo hiểm (special clothing).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. You may be watched while you are doing the activity. — {A: McLeans Island Run}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…where your <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">spectators will include lions, tigers, gorillas and giraffes</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Spectators” (khán giả) ở đây là các loài động vật trong sở thú Orana Park sẽ quan sát bạn khi bạn về đích.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. You watch someone else before doing the activity yourself. — {C: Race Drive Experience}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Then you are strapped into the passenger seat… and <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">taken on a demo drive</strong>… <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">Finally you take the driver’s seat</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bạn ngồi ghế phụ xem lái thử (demo drive) trước, sau đó mới tự mình lái xe (do it yourself).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. You meet people who are expert at the activity. — {C: Race Drive Experience}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…meeting the <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">skilled team of racing drivers</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Skilled team” (đội ngũ lành nghề) tương ứng với “expert” (chuyên gia).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. You can raise money for a charity. — {A: McLeans Island Run}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “You can race to <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">help other people</strong> too… win $25,000 to put towards a <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">good cause of your choice</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Good cause” (mục đích tốt đẹp) thường dùng để chỉ các quỹ từ thiện (charity).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8776bb84-a5ca-44b8-b44a-c34cba17db51', 'd3f9c1bd-0a6f-4652-8c28-0e28ee73b7a7', 'matrix', 'Questions 11-16', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>SIX </strong>answers from the box and write the correct letter, A-I</p>
<p>What is the role of the volunteers in each of the following activities?</p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "walking around the town centre", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "helping at concerts", "correctCategoryLetter": "I"}, {"itemText": "getting involved with community groups", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "helping with a magazine", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "participating at funches for retired people", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "helping with the website", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "providing entertainment", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "providing publicity about a council service", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "contacting local businesses", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "giving advice to visitors", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "collecting feedback on events", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "selling tickets", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "introducing guest speakers at an event", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "encouraging cooperation between local organisations", "categoryLetter": "H"}, {"categoryText": "helping people find their seats", "categoryLetter": "I"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>1. Các Hoạt Động Của Tình Nguyện Viên (Questions 11–16)<br /> </p>\n<p>STEVE WAINWRIGHT:</p>\n<p>Good morning everyone.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m Steve Wainwright from Elmley Town Council and I organise the Towns Volunteer Scheme.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;m delighted you&#8217;re all interested in joining the scheme.</p>\n<p>Our volunteers help to create a sense of community among the many people who live in our historic town of Elmley and make residents and visitors feel welcome at local events.</p>\n<p>First, I&#8217;ll mention just a few of the activities that volunteers carry out.</p>\n<p>One is to walk around the town centre streets wearing our volunteer T-shirt.</p>\n<p>Tourists often ask how to get to a particular shop and they might also be grateful for recommendations about what to visit. (Question 11)</p>\n<p>The town holds a large number of concerts each year and part of the volunteers&#8217; role is to get everyone in the audience to the right place as smoothly as possible.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;d be surprised how many people buy tickets then don&#8217;t check them and head for the wrong section of the hall. (Question 12)</p>\n<p>Volunteers may get involved with community groups such as sports clubs or gardeners&#8217; associations.</p>\n<p>Here, the volunteers talk about how groups can help each other.</p>\n<p>For instance, a writing group might want to travel to another town to hear a talk by a well-known author but may not know that another club has a coach they could travel in. (Question 13)</p>\n<p>The town produces a monthly magazine and anyone who lives in the town can send in articles.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s free to residents and is paid for by local businesses.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s the responsibility of the council&#8217;s advertising department.</p>\n<p>We depend on volunteers, though, to find out what people think of events they&#8217;ve attended and any suggestions they have for the future.</p>\n<p>The volunteers then send a summary to the editors. (Question 14)</p>\n<p>There are a number of clubs for retired people and every year the council arranges lunch for all the members.</p>\n<p>The volunteers welcome the guests and when everyone&#8217;s sitting down and relaxing after the meal, some volunteers put on a show. (Question 15)</p>\n<p>Usually around half an hour of songs and short plays, the club members really welcome the chance to chat to the volunteers at these events.</p>\n<p>The town council has a website, of course, and volunteers are asked to help by making sure residents know about it.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s updated every day with information about future activities and we want as many people as possible to use it. (Question 16)</p>\n<p> <br /> </p>\n<p>2. Thông tin Thực tế và Lịch trình (Questions 17–20)<br /> </p>\n<p>STEVE WAINWRIGHT:</p>\n<p>Okay, now you know some of the things our volunteers do, I&#8217;ll go on to some practical matters.</p>\n<p>As you probably know, the town arranges three major festivals every year and they all depend on a large number of volunteers.</p>\n<p>Tên Lễ hội<br />Số ngày<br />Số lượng Tình nguyện viên cần thiết<br />Book Festival<br />three days<br />fewer needed<br />Music Festival<br />a whole week<br />more needed<br />Science Festival<br />two days<br />even more help required<br />It&#8217;s a good idea to help at the festival you&#8217;re most interested in because you can attend most of the events for free.</p>\n<p>We try to use volunteers who are flexible though because some festival events are held outdoors and the weather may affect the size of the audience and even whether the event can take place, so there can be changes at short notice.</p>\n<p>What&#8217;s essential though is being able to get on well with other people and also to deal with someone who&#8217;s behaving badly, as occasionally happens. (Question 17)</p>\n<p>Our plan is to get you all working in September, after a week&#8217;s training starting on the 2nd, so we&#8217;ll be timetabling you for duties the following week from the 9th onward. (Question 18)</p>\n<p>Later, in the week beginning September 23rd, we have a chat with each of you to find out how you feel about being a volunteer and what extra support you need. (Question 19)</p>\n<p>As a thank you to the volunteers, we arrange an annual event.</p>\n<p>In recent years, we&#8217;ve had a party in the town hall and last year, a barbecue in Chamber Park.</p>\n<p>Our forthcoming event is a trip along the canal from here to Dewhurst and back. (Question 20)</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s on Saturday, September the 28th and if you&#8217;d like to attend, you can sign up once you start work.</p>\n<p>Now, this is the volunteers&#8217; T-shirt.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('559520e9-f411-410c-9332-e157690db9dd', 'd3f9c1bd-0a6f-4652-8c28-0e28ee73b7a7', 'radio', 'Questions 17-20', NULL, '<p data-start="107" data-end="148"><strong data-start="107" data-end="148">Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</strong></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. the music festival"}, {"content": "B. the science festival"}, {"content": "C. the book festival"}], "question": "Which event requires the largest number of volunteers?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. interpersonal skills"}, {"content": "B. personal interest in the event"}, {"content": "C. flexibility"}], "question": "What is the most important requirement for volunteers at the festivals?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. 2 September"}, {"content": "B. 9 September"}, {"content": "C. 23 September"}], "question": "New volunteers will start working in the week beginning"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. a boat trip"}, {"content": "B. a barbecue"}, {"content": "C. a party"}], "question": "What is the next annual event for volunteers?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('27b303ba-9bb5-418f-88d0-46cd868e3c0f', '1917d49b-66e7-4167-837b-de28547e4a60', 'matching', 'Questions 1-7 ', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 1 has seven paragraphs.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of heading below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct number, i-x, in boxes 1-7.</p>', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. Early years of Gilbert"}, {"optionText": "ii. What was new about his scientific research method"}, {"optionText": "iii. The development of chemistry"}, {"optionText": "iv. Questioning traditional astronomy"}, {"optionText": "v. Pioneers of the early science"}, {"optionText": "vi. Professional and social recognition"}, {"optionText": "vii. Becoming the president of the Royal Science Society"}, {"optionText": "viii. The great works of Gilbert"}, {"optionText": "ix. His discovery about magnetism"}, {"optionText": "x. His change of focus"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Paragraph 1: v (Pioneers of the early science)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The 16th and 17th centuries saw two great <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">pioneers</strong> of modern science: Galileo and Gilbert.”</li>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này giới thiệu Gilbert cùng với Galileo là những người tiên phong khởi đầu cho khoa học hiện đại.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Paragraph 2: i (Early years of Gilbert)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Born in an eminent local family… 1544, he went to grammar school, and then studied medicine…”</li>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này cung cấp thông tin về gia thế, ngày sinh và quá trình học tập thời trẻ của ông.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Paragraph 3: vi (Professional and social recognition)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…election to the president of the Royal Science Society. He was also appointed personal physician to the Queen… knighted by the Queen.”</li>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Liệt kê các thành tựu nghề nghiệp (bác sĩ) và sự công nhận từ xã hội/hoàng gia (được phong hiệp sĩ, làm chủ tịch hiệp hội khoa học).</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Paragraph 4: x (His change of focus)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Gilbert was first interested in chemistry but <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">later changed his focus</strong>… He gradually developed his interest in physics…”</li>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mô tả quá trình Gilbert từ bỏ hóa học (vì tính thần bí của thuật giả kim) để chuyển sang nghiên cứu vật lý và nam châm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,4,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Paragraph 5: ix (His discovery about magnetism)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Gilbert’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">discovery</strong> was so important… He investigated the nature of magnetism… coined the word ‘electric’…”</li>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tập trung vào các phát hiện cụ thể của ông về từ tính và điện lực sơ khai.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,5,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Paragraph 6: iv (Questioning traditional astronomy)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “He also <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">questioned the traditional astronomical beliefs</strong>… stars are not equidistant from the earth…”</li>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trình bày những quan điểm khác biệt của ông so với thiên văn học truyền thống thời bấy giờ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,6,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Paragraph 7: ii (What was new about his scientific research method)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “His <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">research method was revolutionary</strong> in that he used <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">experiments</strong> rather than pure logic…”</li>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhấn mạnh sự thay đổi mang tính cách mạng trong phương pháp nghiên cứu: dùng thực nghiệm thay vì chỉ dùng suy luận lý thuyết.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('79839e4a-53d8-4fcc-9106-661cbe48288b', '5107cef4-3ea8-4af9-96a8-5af78ecaee13', 'fillup', 'Questions 15–21', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="49">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 15–21 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-path-to-node="5"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="0">Dealing with redundancy</strong></span></p>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="6" data-index-in-node="0">Initial steps</strong></p>
<p>Start by considering what needs to be done and make a {list} to work through. Get the company’s policy concerning laying off staff and check personal work-related documents.</p>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="7" data-index-in-node="0">Dealing with the company</strong></p>
<p>Avoid letting the management see you are annoyed because:</p>
<ul data-path-to-node="8">
<li>you want to receive a positive {reference} from them for a future post.</li>
<li>you might get some {consultancy} projects from them in the future.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="9" data-index-in-node="0">Moving on</strong></p>
<p>Find<span class="citation-14146 citation-14147"> an organisation that specialises in {outplacement}</span><span class="citation-14146 citation-14147 citation-end-14147"> to help you look for another job.</span> <span class="citation-14144 citation-14145">Invest time in doing serious {research} </span><span class="citation-14144 citation-14145 citation-end-14145">concerning the current requirements in your sector.</span> <span class="citation-14142 citation-14143">Consider if your work and training records contain {gaps}</span><span class="citation-14142 citation-14143 citation-end-14143"> that might prevent you finding work.</span> <span class="citation-14140 citation-14141 citation-end-14141">Sign up for any relevant courses to improve your chances of being selected for a new pos</span><span class="citation-14140 citation-end-14140">t.</span></p>
<p><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="0">Conclusion</strong></p>
<p>Look on redundancy as a useful {incentive} to advance, rather than the end of your career.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Start by considering what needs to be done and make a {list} to work through.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “The best course of action is to keep calm and <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">draw up a list</strong> of all of the things you need to arrange…” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Draw up” tương ứng với “make”. Bước đầu tiên sau khi bị thôi việc là lập một danh sách các việc cần làm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. …you want to receive a positive {reference} from them for a future post.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “You will still need a <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">reasonable reference</strong> when the time comes to move on…” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc giữ quan hệ tốt với chủ cũ giúp bạn có được một thư giới thiệu hoặc xác nhận năng lực (reference) tốt cho công việc tương lai.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. …you might get some {consultancy} projects from them in the future.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…it may be that your boss can… offer you <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">consultancy</strong> work.” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Giữ quan hệ tốt còn giúp bạn có cơ hội nhận các dự án tư vấn (consultancy) từ chính công ty cũ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Find an organisation that specialises in {outplacement} to help you look for another job.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Help from a professional <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">outplacement</strong> company can make a huge difference to your job search success…” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Organisation” tương ứng với “company”. Các công ty dịch vụ hỗ trợ tìm việc làm mới (outplacement) sẽ giúp quá trình chuyển đổi nghề nghiệp hiệu quả hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Invest time in doing serious {research} concerning the current requirements in your sector.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…carry out <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">in-depth research</strong> to find out what employers are actually looking for.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Serious” tương ứng với “in-depth”, “current requirements” tương ứng với “what employers are actually looking for”. Bạn cần nghiên cứu kỹ nhu cầu thị trường.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Consider if your work and training records contain {gaps} that might prevent you finding work.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Assess whether there are any <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">gaps</strong> in experience or qualifications that could be a barrier to getting another job…” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Prevent you finding work” tương ứng với “barrier to getting another job”. Bạn cần kiểm tra xem hồ sơ của mình có lỗ hổng (gaps) nào về kinh nghiệm hay bằng cấp không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Look on redundancy as a useful {incentive} to advance, rather than the end of your career.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…many people find that redundancy is actually the <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">incentive</strong> they need to take their career in the direction they actually want to go.” (Đoạn cuối)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thay vì coi là kết thúc, hãy coi việc bị thôi việc là một động lực (incentive) để phát triển sự nghiệp theo ý muốn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('47367587-bc2d-4248-aeac-54a6aeaaae4e', '2233b1bc-2fdb-4d24-9641-80c114ebf715', 'radio', 'Questions 26–30', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "Many people know little about it"}, {"content": "People understand it because it has been in the news recently"}, {"content": "People are eager to find out more about it"}], "question": "What does Sylvia say about people''s knowledge of renewable energy?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "the best way of preventing pollution"}, {"content": "possible future developments"}, {"content": "how expensive people find it"}], "question": "What do Sylvia and Greg decide to ask about traditional energy consumption?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "It is not important for their survey"}, {"content": "People today have a positive attitude towards it"}, {"content": "Some people think it is unsafe"}], "question": "What does Greg say about nuclear power?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "Prices will drop in the future"}, {"content": "People won''t pay the high price"}, {"content": "The benefits outweigh the high cost"}], "question": "What do Sylvia and Greg agree about the cost of renewable energy?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "are the most efficient way of harnessing energy"}, {"content": "should be put in carefully selected locations"}, {"content": "make the landscape look unattractive"}], "question": "Sylvia and Greg agree that modern windmills"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('46811edd-5021-4dc3-a414-50a15069e748', 'de4cc89f-516a-4b2a-ae69-e415a5e3fdc5', 'matching', 'Questions 14–19', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has six paragraphs. Choose the correct heading for each section and move it into the gap.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i Different areas of professional expertise"}, {"optionText": "ii Reasons why it is unfair to criticise lawyers"}, {"optionText": "iii The disadvantages of the legal system"}, {"optionText": "iv The law applies throughout our lives"}, {"optionText": "v The law has affected historical events"}, {"optionText": "vi A negative regard for lawyers"}, {"optionText": "vii Public’s increasing ability to Influence the law"}, {"optionText": "viii Growth in laws"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>14. (Đoạn 1)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>iv The law applies throughout our lives</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “The law influences all of us virtually all the time. It governs almost all aspects of our behavior, and even what happens to us when we are no longer alive. It affects us from the embryo onwards.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn nhấn mạnh luật pháp điều chỉnh và ảnh hưởng đến <strong>tất cả các khía cạnh</strong> cuộc sống của chúng ta, từ khi là phôi thai trở đi, cho thấy sự áp dụng liên tục và xuyên suốt.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>15. (Đoạn 2)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vii Public’s increasing ability to influence the law</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “…it is becoming easier for people to take an interest in law, and for the <strong>general population to help actually shape the law</strong> in many countries.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn tập trung vào sự phát triển gần đây, trong đó <strong>công chúng</strong> (<em>general population</em>) ngày càng có khả năng <strong>định hình luật pháp</strong> (<em>shape the law</em>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>16. (Đoạn 3)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>i Different areas of professional expertise</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “Those people, for example, with knowledge of computers, the internet, and communications technology are relied upon by the rest of us… But <strong>legal understanding is just as vital and as universally needed</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn so sánh hiểu biết về luật pháp với các chuyên môn khác (như IT) và kết luận rằng <strong>kiến thức pháp lý cũng quan trọng và cần thiết phổ quát</strong> như các lĩnh vực chuyên môn khác.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>17. (Đoạn 4)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>viii Growth in laws</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “<strong>The number of laws has never been greater.</strong>… The legislative output of the British Parliament has <strong>more than doubled</strong> in recent times…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này cung cấp bằng chứng thống kê về việc <strong>số lượng luật đang tăng lên</strong> (<em>“Growth in laws”</em>), với số lượng đạo luật và trang lập pháp tăng gấp đôi.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>18. (Đoạn 5)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vi A negative regard for lawyers</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “However, despite their important role in developing the rules, <strong>lawyers are not universally admired</strong>. Anti-lawyer jokes have a long history going back to the ancient Greeks.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn thảo luận về sự thiếu ngưỡng mộ và các câu chuyện cười (<em>jokes</em>) chống lại luật sư, cho thấy thái độ tiêu cực đối với họ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>19. (Đoạn 6)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>ii Reasons why it is unfair to criticise lawyers</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “But, in general, it is <strong>no more just to say that lawyers are bad</strong> because they make a living from people’s problems than it is to make the same accusation in respect of nurses or IT consultants.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này cung cấp các lý do (ví dụ: công việc công ích, nhu cầu soạn thảo tài liệu) để lập luận rằng việc chỉ trích luật sư là không công bằng (“unfair to criticise”).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8481b891-b5d6-48ee-853a-f9b5322f5c4f', '5f327ba8-9402-47fb-b5b6-d0e5f5b602f8', 'fillup', 'Questions 31-40', '<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<p>Complete the notes below</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<p class="s-component-content s-font-body"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>New engineering designs: Scottish case study</strong></span></p>
<p class="s-component-content s-font-body"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Project to renovate and link two canals in Scotland</span></p>
<p class="s-component-content s-font-body"><strong>Historical background</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<ul>
<li>
<p>1790: opening of the Forth and Clyde Canal (Scotland’s {oldest} canal)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>1822: opening of the Union Canal</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The two canals allowed boats to cross the {central} part of Scotland</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Locks (steps) connected the two canals near Falkirk</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>1842: competition from a new {railway}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>1930s: the locks were demolished</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Millennium project</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Aim: to improve Scotland’s {transport}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The long-term goal – to strengthen the Scottish {economy}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Involved restoration of the two canals</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Problem: one canal is 35m lower than the other</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The Falkirk Wheel (a mechanical lift)</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Completed in 2002</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Two large tanks are attached to the ends of an arm</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The tanks are designed to remain in a {horizontal} position.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>A boat sails into each tank</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The weight of the tanks with their contents is always {equal}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Little energy is needed to rotate the arm</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Visual quality – resembles a {sculpture}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Manufacturing</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>All the parts were constructed off-site</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>1,200 tonnes of {steel} were used</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Joints were bolted and welded to reduce the effects of {stress}</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 4: NEW ENGINEERING DESIGNS – SCOTTISH CASE STUDY</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Good morning everyone. In the last lecture, we discussed innovation in engineering design, and today I want to look at a case study. I’ll be talking about an engineering project which was recently carried out in Scotland to restore two old waterways—canals in fact—and then link them together.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">I’ll talk about the design features, but first, I’ll tell you a little bit about the historical background of the project. One of these canals, called the Forth and Clyde, opened in 1790, and it’s the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"201\">(31) oldest</strong></span> of Scotland’s canals. The other, the Union Canal, opened in 1822.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Although the two canals were built at different levels, together they enabled vessels to travel from west to east across <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">(32) central</strong></span> Scotland. This is because the canals were connected near a town called Falkirk by a complicated system of locks, which have steps and gates allowing boats to move from one level to another.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">However, from 1842, the two canals faced serious competition when the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">(33) railway</strong></span> opened, which served the same cross-country route. After that, their use declined steadily, and in the 1930s, the locks at Falkirk were demolished.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"7\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">THE MILLENNIUM PROJECT</strong></h3>\n<p id=\"p-rc_75e4fd8b36b34943-50\" data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Times change, however. Moving on now to the turn of the millennium, Scotland embarked on an ambitious new project. The aim was to upgrade the country’s infrastructure, especially in the area of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"204\">(34) transport</strong></span>. It was a very big investment indeed, and in fact, the whole project was just one part of a long-term plan which had been developed to stimulate the national <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"377\">(35) economy</strong></span>. <span class=\"citation-163 citation-end-163\">And amongst other things, it involved restoring the two old canals and bringing them back into use.</span><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" aria-label=\"View source details for citation from IELTS Song Ngữ 🎉. Opens side panel.\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwi27a3CyICTAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQmQI\"></button></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">However, there was one major challenge. As I mentioned just now, the Forth and Clyde Canal lies below the level of the Union Canal. There’s a 35m difference, and the locks had been destroyed. So the problem was how to get boats from one level to the other.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"11\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">THE FALKIRK WHEEL (MECHANICAL LIFT)</strong></h3>\n<p id=\"p-rc_75e4fd8b36b34943-51\" data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Whatever kind of solution was chosen, it was felt that it should be really innovative and imaginative—a fitting way to mark the beginning of a new millennium. <span class=\"citation-162 citation-end-162\">The resulting structure was a mechanical lift for boats, and because it rotates, it was called the Falkirk Wheel.</span><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" aria-label=\"View source details for citation from Institution of Civil Engineers (ICE). Opens side panel.\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwi27a3CyICTAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQmgI\"></button></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_75e4fd8b36b34943-52\" data-path-to-node=\"14\"><span class=\"citation-161 citation-end-161\">The Falkirk Wheel was completed in 2002, and it was the first structure of its kind—an engineering innovation.</span> The structure consists of two very large tanks, each large enough to contain a boat. In fact, these are fixed onto opposite sides of a vertical arm.<button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" aria-label=\"View source details for citation from Institution of Civil Engineers (ICE). Opens side panel.\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwi27a3CyICTAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQmwI\"></button></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">Basically, what happens is that the arm lowers one boat from the higher canal to the canal below, and at the same time, it raises another boat from the lower canal to the level of the upper canal. How does this work? Well, the tanks are mounted in such a way that they stay in a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"279\">(36) horizontal</strong></span> plane.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">As one boat, together with the water that it floats in, sails into the upper tank, another floating boat simultaneously enters the lower tank. The system works on scientific principles which ensure that the weight of each boat plus the water that it floats in will be <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"268\">(37) equal</strong></span> to the other.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">So once the boats have entered the tank, the arm rotates, and because the tanks are in balance, only a very small amount of energy is required for this rotation. Engineers generally agree that the Falkirk Wheel is highly functional. It’s also visually stunning; it’s an unusual shape, it looks very attractive with a lot of curves. In fact, it almost looks like a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"364\">(38) sculpture</strong>.</span></p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"18\" />\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">MANUFACTURING</strong></h3>\n<p id=\"p-rc_75e4fd8b36b34943-53\" data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> So where was the Falkirk Wheel manufactured? Well, it was produced entirely off-site at a place in England, about 370km away. It was constructed from <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">(39) steel</strong></span>—1,200 tonnes of it. It was also very strong. For example, the joints were bolted together as well as being welded. This was because a lot of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"312\">(40) stress</strong></span> would be placed on them by the weight of the boats and the water. <span class=\"citation-160 citation-end-160\">Over 15,000 bolts were used, and each one was tightened by hand.</span><button class=\"button ng-star-inserted\" aria-label=\"View source details for citation from Institution of Civil Engineers (ICE). Opens side panel.\" data-hveid=\"0\" data-ved=\"0CAAQvoAQahgKEwi27a3CyICTAxUAAAAAHQAAAAAQnAI\"></button></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\">Of course, since it’s been in use, the design has been tested on an ongoing basis…</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('770b421e-4ab5-457d-adae-6cf0c034dee9', '94204bcc-3719-4410-8ef3-cd4386038d70', 'radio', 'Questions 11-14', '', '<p>Choose the correct answer</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Starting work at Hollies supermarket</strong></span></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "be aware of the importance of teamwork"}, {"option_text": "be flexible in terms of their availability."}, {"option_text": "be capable of lifting heavy loads."}], "question": "The supervisor starts her talk by explaining that employees have to"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "decide for themselves what needs doing"}, {"option_text": "postpone their scheduled break"}, {"option_text": "report minor accidents quickly."}], "question": "The supervisor says that when the supermarket is very busy, employees must"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "helps everyone in the supermarket to relax"}, {"option_text": "encourages customers to spend more"}, {"option_text": "improves work effectiveness"}], "question": "The supervisor explains that when employees have a positive attitude, it"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "reports an employee to the manager."}, {"option_text": "delays other shoppers."}, {"option_text": "refuses to wait their turn."}], "question": "The supervisor says it is essential to stay calm when a customer"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong>Questions 11–14</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a supervisor at Holly’s Supermarket talking to a group of new employees. First you have some time to look at questions eleven to fourteen. Now listen carefully and answer questions eleven to fourteen.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong>Supervisor:</strong> Welcome to Holly’s Supermarket! I’m sure you’ll all enjoy working in our dedicated team here. So what will you be doing? Well, we’re open Monday through Sunday, so you’ll need to be able to work weekends as well as irregular weekday shifts. These sometimes start at 5 a.m. or finish at 11 p.m. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(11) (be flexible in terms of their availability)</strong>.</span> Your duties will include checking and unpacking lorry deliveries, as well as working on the shop floor, stocking shelves and so on. But you’ll only be required to do manual lifting if the goods are light.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong>Supervisor:</strong> When the store is very busy, you’ll also have to assess changing priorities <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(12) (decide for themselves what needs doing)</strong>. </span>For example, if there’s a queue at the tills, you’ll jump on a spare one to help. If you notice something’s been spilt and the surface is a little bit wet, you’ll get a mop to clean it up; no need to check with the manager first. Similarly, if bakery items are selling quickly, you’ll help cook some more, and if a customer can’t find say the apples, you’ll instantly leave what you’re doing and show them. But you’ll still get time off to relax too, of course.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong>Supervisor:</strong> We pride ourselves on a positive attitude here. A little small talk shows you’re interested in the customers and are providing excellent service, just as long as you don’t overdo it and keep another customer waiting. And always smile. It forces you to stay positive, and being generally upbeat <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(13) makes your whole team happy too. This increases efficiency</strong></span> and gives a good impression to customers. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(13) (improves work effectiveness)</strong>. </span>If it’s quiet, help someone pack their bags. Customers really appreciate it, especially when they’ve bought more than they expected to.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong>Supervisor:</strong> Staying calm’s also a necessity. If a customer’s unhappy for any reason, keep cool and call for a supervisor to help defuse a situation if things are getting out of hand. Occasionally when working tills, you’ll find yourself waiting for someone to extract their wallet from the bottom of a cluttered bag while a long queue of annoyed customers builds up. You have to make sure, however hard it might be, that you <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(14) remain composed</strong>.</span></p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4887cb75-b9be-4723-be59-4cd318915137', '94204bcc-3719-4410-8ef3-cd4386038d70', 'matrix', 'Questions 15–20', '', '<p>Questions 15–20</p>
<p>Label the plan below.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="471" height="484" loading="lazy"></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Staff entrance", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Manager''s office", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": " Storage and unpacking", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Kitchen", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Cleaning equipment", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Staff relaxation area", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}, {"categoryText": "I", "categoryLetter": "I"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>(Questions 15–20)</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the talk, you have some time to look at questions fifteen to twenty. Now listen and answer questions fifteen to twenty.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong>Supervisor:</strong> So, now let’s look at the plan of the supermarket. Have you all got your plans? Okay, good. We’ll start with the<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(15) Staff entrance (A)</strong></span>. Today you came in through the customer entrance, clearly marked on the bottom of your plan, but in future, you’ll enter through the door in the <strong>top left hand corner</strong> of the diagram. Please don’t confuse this with the emergency exits in the top right hand corner and bottom left; it’s very important that these are kept clear at all times.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong>Supervisor:</strong> Regarding the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(16) Manager’s office (D)</strong></span>, some of you may have attended interviews here when it was next to the newspaper and magazine sales area. However, it’s recently been moved and is now the <strong>circular space</strong> marked on the <strong>right</strong> of your plans. When the manager’s not on the shop floor, that’s where you’ll find her.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong>Supervisor:</strong> The <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(17) Storage and unpacking area (B)</strong></span>—you may be asked to help out here both before and after opening hours. This is represented by the <strong>largest of the four rectangles in the top section</strong> of the plan. It tends to get very busy there at times, so please be careful on entering and leaving this area.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong>Supervisor:</strong> There’s a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(18) Kitchen (E)</strong></span> on site where food and drinks are prepared for customers.It has specialist staff, but some of you may have to fill in occasionally. On the plan, it’s shown by the <strong>triangular shape to the left of the tinned goods aisle</strong>. It’s very busy as many customers like to take a break in the café and read a newspaper before or after doing their shopping.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong>Supervisor:</strong> Cleaning equipment is stored in a cupboard. It’s the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(19) smaller of the two squares (G)</strong> </span>marked near the vegetable and fruit section and can come in very handy. You’d be surprised how often we have to mop up squashed tomatoes or grapes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong>Supervisor:</strong> Finally, you’ll be pleased to know there’s a separate <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(20) staff relaxation area (C)</strong></span>. This is at the <strong>top</strong> of your plan, between the frozen goods section and the exit. As well as comfortable chairs, there’s also a microwave for heating up snacks and a drinks dispenser.So let’s go there now.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of Part Two. You now have thirty seconds to check your answers to Part Two.</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('25b36325-8d4e-4143-b8ac-320771d75896', 'ca1c622c-a77f-4ba5-a395-9bfe5e8e298b', 'matrix', 'Questions 20-23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following findings (Questions 20-23) and the list of academics below.</p>
<p>Choose each finding with the correct academic, <strong>A-D</strong>.</p>
<p><strong><em>NB</em> </strong><em>you may use any letter more than</em><strong><em> </em></strong><em>once</em><strong><em>.</em></strong></p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of academics", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Certain members can influence the rest of the group to alter a previous decision.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Individual verification of a proposed choice is important for successful decision outcome.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "The more individuals taking part in a decision, the better the decision will be.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "The decision-making process of certain insects produces excellent results even when fine distinctions are required.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Nicolas de Condorcet", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Christian List and colleagues", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "José Halloy", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Nigel Franks and colleagues", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>20. Certain members can influence the rest of the group to alter a previous decision.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C (José Halloy)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) Halloy đã sử dụng gián robot (<em>robotic cockroaches</em>) để <strong>thay đổi hành vi</strong> (<em>subvert the behaviour</em>) và <strong>thuyết phục</strong> (<em>persuade</em>) những con gián sống chọn nơi trú ẩn không phù hợp (tức là thay đổi quyết định trước đó).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> José Halloy đã chứng minh khả năng thiểu số (robot) kiểm soát quyết định của đa số (gián sống).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>21. Individual verification of a proposed choice is important for successful decision outcome.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B (Christian List and colleagues)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) Các nhà nghiên cứu kết luận rằng khả năng chọn địa điểm tốt nhất của ong phụ thuộc vào sự <strong>độc lập trong việc xác nhận thông tin</strong> (<em>“independence in confirming this information for themselves”</em>) sau khi nghe “waggle dance”.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Phát hiện của List nhấn mạnh tầm quan trọng của việc xác minh cá nhân (individual verification).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>22. The more individuals taking part in a decision, the better the decision will be.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A (Nicolas de Condorcet)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) Condorcet’s theory nói rằng <strong>“the probability of a correct decision increases with the size of the jury”</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Lý thuyết bồi thẩm đoàn của Condorcet là về việc quy mô nhóm càng lớn thì quyết định càng chính xác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>23. The decision-making process of certain insects produces excellent results even when fine distinctions are required.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B (Christian List and colleagues)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) Nghiên cứu của List về ong cho thấy: “The decision is <strong>remarkably reliable, with the bees choosing the best site even when there is only small difference between alternative sites</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ong chọn được địa điểm tốt nhất ngay cả khi sự khác biệt giữa các lựa chọn là rất nhỏ (<em>fine distinctions</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a14ce903-05be-44b1-9cab-24ad77b82f5a', '5107cef4-3ea8-4af9-96a8-5af78ecaee13', 'fillup', 'Questions 22–27', '<p id="p-rc_4ad79a48dc61b792-325" data-path-to-node="13">Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="13">Choose <strong data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="53">NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from<span class="citation-14136 citation-14137 citation-14138 citation-14139 citation-end-14139"> the text for each answer.</span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="13"><span class="citation-14132 citation-14133 citation-14134 citation-14135 citation-end-14135">Write your answers in boxes 22–27 on your answer sheet.</span></p>
<p> </p>
<ul>
<li><span class="citation-14128 citation-14129 citation-14130 citation-14131 citation-end-14131">New staff must record their own body {measurements} before arriving at work.</span></li>
<li><span class="citation-14124 citation-14125 citation-14126 citation-14127 citation-end-14127">You should use your {laundry allowance} to ensure that your uniform is never dirty.</span></li>
<li><span class="citation-14120 citation-14121 citation-14122 citation-14123 citation-end-14123">Clothes worn to travel to work must be</span><span class="citation-14120 citation-14121 citation-14122 citation-end-14122"> {respectable} .</span></li>
<li><span class="citation-14117 citation-14118 citation-14119 citation-end-14119">Casual wear, such as {hoodies}, should not be worn in the kitchen area.</span></li>
<li><span class="citation-14114 citation-14115 citation-14116 citation-end-14116">Staff</span><span class="citation-14114 citation-14115 citation-end-14115"> using {crutches} may still come to work.</span></li>
<li><span class="citation-14112 citation-14113 citation-end-14113">Please contact the manager before arriving at the kitchens if you have any {hand cuts}</span><span class="citation-14112 citation-end-14112"> or other similar injuries.</span></li>
</ul>', NULL, 'short_answer', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. New staff must record their own body {measurements} before arriving at work.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…advised to come to work with a note of your <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">chest, waist and hip measurements</strong> to assist in this process.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Body measurements” là từ bao quát cho các số đo cơ thể (ngực, eo, mông) mà nhân viên cần chuẩn bị trước để bộ phận cấp phát đồng phục chọn được size vừa vặn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. You should use your {laundry allowance} to ensure that your uniform is never dirty.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…you will receive a <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">laundry allowance</strong> to help you do this [keep uniform clean].” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Never dirty” tương ứng với “kept clean”. Nhà hàng không tự giặt đồ cho bạn mà cấp một khoản tiền phụ cấp giặt ủi (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">laundry allowance</em>) để bạn tự có trách nhiệm giữ đồng phục luôn sạch sẽ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Clothes worn to travel to work must be {respectable}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “You should wear your normal clothes to and from work but make sure they’re <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">respectable</strong>.” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mặc dù nhân viên thay đồng phục tại nơi làm việc, nhưng trang phục cá nhân mặc lúc đi đường (to and from work) vẫn phải đảm bảo tính lịch sự, chỉnh tề (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">respectable</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. Casual wear, such as {hoodies}, should not be worn in the kitchen area.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “For example, <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">hoodies</strong> and other similar tops are <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">not acceptable in the kitchens</strong>…” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Casual wear” (đồ mặc thường ngày) như áo nỉ có mũ (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">hoodies</em>) bị cấm sử dụng trong khu vực bếp vì không phù hợp với tiêu chuẩn an toàn và chuyên nghiệp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. Staff using {crutches} may still come to work.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “If you incur any injuries that require <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">crutches</strong>… we will make every effort to place you in an appropriate area… so you will <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">not need to take time off</strong>.” (Đoạn cuối)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Not need to take time off” nghĩa là vẫn có thể đi làm. Nếu phải dùng nạng (<em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">crutches</em>), nhà hàng sẽ linh động sắp xếp công việc ngồi làm để nhân viên không phải nghỉ phép.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Please contact the manager before arriving at the kitchens if you have any {hand cuts} or other similar injuries.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Employees who have smaller injuries, such as <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">hand cuts</strong>, need to <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">check with their manager</strong> whether they can come to work…” (Đoạn cuối)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Contact” tương ứng với “check with”. Vì làm việc trong môi trường thực phẩm, các vết đứt tay (<em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">hand cuts</em>) cần được quản lý kiểm tra để đảm bảo vệ sinh và tránh nhiễm trùng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2ce05962-4900-4ceb-b6a8-3f2b99b10083', '3bddf77b-e479-402d-938a-f2dd4deb4c5b', 'radio', 'Questions 9-13', '', '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "Leonardo da Vinci"}, {"option_text": "Colladon and Sturm"}, {"option_text": "Ewing and Worzel"}, {"option_text": "Jeff Nystuen"}], "question": "According to the passage, who conducted research into the rate at which sound travels in water?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "Leonardo da Vinci"}, {"option_text": "Colladon and Sturm"}, {"option_text": "Ewing and Worzel"}, {"option_text": "Christopher Clark"}], "question": "According to the passage, who conducted research into the distances certain types of sound waves travel in water?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "follow a number of whales at the same time."}, {"option_text": "protect whales as they migrate."}, {"option_text": "imitate whale calls of different species."}, {"option_text": "change the whales* direction of travel."}], "question": "SOSUS allows whale researchers to"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "when scientists track them."}, {"option_text": "at different times of year."}, {"option_text": "when whales communicate with other species."}, {"option_text": "when whales come to the surface."}], "question": "Finback whale calls change"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "make accurate maps of the ocean floor."}, {"option_text": "measure water level changes."}, {"option_text": "investigate ocean currents."}, {"option_text": "measure variations in temperature."}], "question": "SOSUS allows scientists to"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. Who conducted research into the rate at which sound travels in water? — {B: Colladon and Sturm}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “It was not until 1826 that two scientists, <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">Colladon and Sturm, accurately measured the speed of sound</strong> in water.” (Đoạn B)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Rate” ở đây đồng nghĩa với “speed” (tốc độ).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. Who conducted research into the distances certain types of sound waves travel in water? — {C: Ewing and Worzel}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “In 1943, <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Maurice Ewing and J L Worzel</strong> conducted an experiment to test the theory that low-frequency waves… should be able to <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">travel great distances</strong>…” (Đoạn C)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. SOSUS allows whale researchers to — {A} follow a number of whales at the same time.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…they can track not just one whale at a time, but <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">many creatures simultaneously</strong>.” (Đoạn E)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Many creatures simultaneously” tương ứng với “a number of whales at the same time”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Finback whale calls change — {B} at different times of year.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…researchers have detected changes in the calls of finback whales <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">as the seasons change</strong>…” (Đoạn E)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Seasons change” tương ứng với “different times of year”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. SOSUS allows scientists to — {D} measure variations in temperature.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…scientists can <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">track changes in temperature</strong> over months or years.” (Đoạn F)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Variations” đồng nghĩa với “changes”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7ecc6f2d-235b-4551-a773-b220b9475f14', '9b6d9897-cf82-4f9c-a390-603e391efdb0', 'radio', 'Questions 27-30', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Most people understand how innovation happens."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The word \"innovation\" is overused in business in New Zealand."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There are many interpretations of what innovation means in business, according to one global study."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Research and development projects have a higher priority today than in the past."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27 Most people understand how innovation happens.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 1, câu 3: &#8220;&#8230;however, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">majority of us have little comprehension</strong> of the processes that actually lead to innovation occurring.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định đa số chúng ta (the majority of us) có rất ít sự hiểu biết (little comprehension) về quá trình dẫn đến đổi mới. Điều này trái ngược hoàn toàn với ý &#8220;đa số mọi người hiểu&#8221; (most people understand) trong câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28 The word &#8220;innovation&#8221; is overused in business in New Zealand.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 1, câu 5: &#8220;However, in company boardrooms across <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">New Zealand</strong>, the term is <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">heard far too frequently</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ &#8220;heard far too frequently&#8221; (nghe thấy quá thường xuyên) đồng nghĩa với &#8220;overused&#8221; (bị lạm dụng/dùng quá nhiều). Văn bản xác nhận tình trạng này đang xảy ra tại các phòng họp công ty ở New Zealand.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29 There are many interpretations of what innovation means in business, according to one global study.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 1, câu 6: &#8220;Certainly, a recent <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">international survey</strong> showed that&#8230; different sectors of the business world&#8230; often <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">defining innovation in their own way</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> &#8220;International survey&#8221; tương ứng với &#8220;global study&#8221;. Việc các bộ phận khác nhau &#8220;định nghĩa theo cách riêng của họ&#8221; (defining&#8230; in their own way) chính là có &#8220;nhiều cách hiểu/giải thích khác nhau&#8221; (many interpretations).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30 Research and development projects have a higher priority today than in the past.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 2, câu 1: &#8220;While there is an obvious attraction to the new, innovation is <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">not always about large-scale research and development projects</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến các dự án nghiên cứu và phát triển (R&amp;D) để nói rằng đổi mới không phải lúc nào cũng nằm ở những dự án quy mô lớn này. Tuy nhiên, bài đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">không hề so sánh</strong> mức độ ưu tiên của các dự án R&amp;D giữa &#8220;nay&#8221; và &#8220;xưa&#8221;.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b330e6ec-d897-4595-bc72-61bb62685f93', 'ca1c622c-a77f-4ba5-a395-9bfe5e8e298b', 'fillup', 'Questions 24-26', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<p class="txt" style="text-align: left;">Complete the summary below.<br />
Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p class="txt" style="text-align: center;"><strong>A study of insect decision-making</strong></p>
<p class="txt">A Bristol University study looked at how insects make decisions when their home has been {threatened}. The ants in the experiment relied on the use of individuals called {scouts} new nest and efficiently direct the others to go there. The study concluded that the effective implementation of the ants’ decision meant that the insects could change homes quickly. The study emphasized the necessity, for people well as insects, of having active {leaders} in order to execute decisions successfully.</p>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>24. A Bristol University study looked at how insects make decisions when their home has been <strong>threatened</strong>.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>threatened</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…the problems associated with making a necessarily swift choice. If the ants’ existing nest become <strong>suddenly threatened</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>25. The ants in the experiment relied on the use of individuals called <strong>scouts</strong> to find a new nest and efficiently direct the others to go there.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>scouts</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…the insects choose certain ants to act as <strong>scouts</strong> to find a new nest.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>26. The study emphasized the necessity, for people as well as insects, of having active <strong>leaders</strong> in order to execute decisions successfully.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>leaders</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “But it does suggest, even for humans, the importance of recruiting <strong>dynamic leaders</strong> to a cause, because the most important thing about collective decision-making, as shown by these insect experiments, is to get others to follow.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> “Dynamic leaders” (nhà lãnh đạo năng động) được coi là cần thiết để thực thi các quyết định.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('80cb6416-1812-41eb-b6bf-ca6eed465a62', 'cbefaab9-b1e1-4cbb-b7e4-769b3b0e7bdd', 'matrix', 'Questions 14–20', '', '<p>Reading Passage 2 has eight paragraphs, <strong>A-H.</strong></p>
<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "A description of how a test showed some evidence to be fake", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Reasons why scientists may be unwilling to admit that they play", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "The result of a trick going wrong", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "The similarity between a skill used in play and one used in science", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "How a group of scientists stopped a colleague misusing their results", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Some examples of the playful nature of scientific language", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "An example of an everyday object put to a scientific use", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('36bffe03-5791-4a75-88b9-fca4b3495c11', 'cbefaab9-b1e1-4cbb-b7e4-769b3b0e7bdd', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21–22', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> of the following reasons are given as possible explanations of scientists play behaviour?</p>', 'list_selection', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A Play may provide relief from their work."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B Scientists sometimes spend time as teachers."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C The age of scientists predisposes them to play."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D Scientists get ideas from children''s questions"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E Scientists are secretive about their work."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('76e7352f-8980-4b54-9c50-66aec2b9f0c6', '94489cd2-0611-4edd-badd-8e3a86e20530', 'radio', 'Questions 28–32', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="27">A, B, C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="38">D</strong>.</p>
<p>Write the correct letter in boxes 28–32 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A It confirmed what they had assumed when they started it."}, {"option_text": "B It was hard to persuade other historians about their findings."}, {"option_text": "C It could reveal the importance of various women in history."}, {"option_text": "D It could help identify the number of books written in the Middle Ages."}], "question": "In Paragraph A, what does the writer say about the archaeology team’s work?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A Archaeologists could make more use of it than they do at present."}, {"option_text": "B Some particles are more easily trapped in it than others."}, {"option_text": "C The environment can cause it to break down."}, {"option_text": "D Changes in people’s diet have influenced its composition."}], "question": "What point does the writer make about dental tartar in Paragraph C?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A She had not been very old when she died."}, {"option_text": "B Her life had not been very physically demanding."}, {"option_text": "C Her teeth had more tartar than most skeletons of that age."}, {"option_text": "D She had been given a grander burial than other women of her time."}], "question": "What did the skeleton of B78 suggest about her?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A supporting the team’s view that the blue pigment was imported"}, {"option_text": "B explaining why artists in Europe liked to use the blue pigment"}, {"option_text": "C comparing artistic designs using the blue pigment in different parts of the world"}, {"option_text": "D criticising arguments put forward by other scientists about the blue pigment"}], "question": "What is the writer doing in Paragraph F?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A the poor facilities available to females in the profession"}, {"option_text": "B the small number of projects available to them"}, {"option_text": "C the difficulties locating their skeletal remains for study"}, {"option_text": "D the lack of evidence for their contribution to books"}], "question": "What problem does the writer highlight about medieval artists in Paragraph G?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. In Paragraph A, what does the writer say about the archaeology team’s work? — {C} It could reveal the importance of various women in history.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…strongly suggest it will be possible to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">increase the profile of ancient female artists</strong> in the historical and archaeological record…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Increase the profile” (nâng cao vị thế/hồ sơ) tương ứng với việc tiết lộ tầm quan trọng (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">importance</em>) của phụ nữ trong lịch sử.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. What point does the writer make about dental tartar in Paragraph C? — {A} Archaeologists could make more use of it than they do at present.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Despite such promising evidence, the value of tartar as environmental evidence <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">has not, so far, been much exploited</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Has not been much exploited” (chưa được khai thác nhiều) tương ứng với việc các nhà khảo cổ có thể sử dụng nó nhiều hơn hiện tại (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">make more use of it</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. What did the skeleton of B78 suggest about her? — {B} Her life had not been very physically demanding.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…a general indication that she probably <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">did not do any hard labour</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Did not do any hard labour” (không làm công việc nặng nhọc) tương ứng với “not very physically demanding”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. What is the writer doing in Paragraph F? — {A} supporting the team’s view that the blue pigment was imported.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “This all suggests that it’s more likely that this ultramarine pigment was <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">brought into the region as a finished product</strong> for use by artists.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Brought into the region” nghĩa là được nhập khẩu (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">imported</em>). Đoạn F đưa ra các lập luận để củng cố quan điểm này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. What problem does the writer highlight about medieval artists in Paragraph G? — {D} the lack of evidence for their contribution to books.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Additionally, artists are <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">largely invisible</strong>… as they rarely signed their work… and, until now, there have been <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">no known skeletal markers</strong> directly associated with producing art.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Invisible” và việc không ký tên/không có dấu vết xương cốt cho thấy sự thiếu hụt bằng chứng (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">lack of evidence</em>) về đóng góp của họ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('464f33ee-4e7c-4fb4-943a-f2651085a5bd', '94489cd2-0611-4edd-badd-8e3a86e20530', 'matrix', 'Questions 33–36', '', '<p><span class="citation-16158 citation-16159 citation-16160 citation-16161 citation-end-16161">Which paragraph mentions the following?</span></p>
<p><span class="citation-16154 citation-16155 citation-16156 citation-16157">Write the correct letter, </span><strong data-path-to-node="16" data-index-in-node="121"><span class="citation-16154 citation-16155 citation-16156 citation-16157">A–G</span></strong><span class="citation-16154 citation-16155 citation-16156 citation-16157 citation-end-16157">, in boxes 33–36 on your answer sheet.</span></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "reference to the possible length of time that tartar can preserve particles from the air", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "two reasons why the particles that the team found in teeth were unique", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "various examples of the types of particle that can be discovered in old teeth", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a suggestion that the blue pigment might have been used in medieval times to cure illness", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. Reference to the possible length of time that tartar can preserve particles — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…can entomb these particles and molecules for <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">hundreds or thousands of years – potentially even millions</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn B nói về khả năng lưu giữ (preserve/entomb) các hạt siêu nhỏ của cao răng (tartar) trong một khoảng thời gian cực kỳ dài, có thể lên đến hàng triệu năm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Two reasons why the particles that the team found in teeth were unique — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “The blue particles were <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">unlike any other discovery</strong> – <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">firstly because of their colour</strong>, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">secondly because of their sheer number</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả nêu rõ hai lý do khiến phát hiện này trở nên độc nhất (unique/unlike any other): một là vì màu sắc (xanh dương rực rỡ) và hai là vì số lượng cực lớn (hơn 100 hạt).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Various examples of the types of particle that can be discovered in old teeth — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Tree and grass pollen, spores, cotton fibres, medicinal plants and micro-charcoal</strong> have all been reported…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C liệt kê một loạt các ví dụ (examples) về những loại hạt khác nhau có thể được tìm thấy thông qua phân tích cao răng ngoài thức ăn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. A suggestion that the blue pigment might have been used… to cure illness — {F}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…or even the <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">consumption of the powder as a medicine</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn F đưa ra giả thuyết về lý do hạt màu xanh xuất hiện trên răng, trong đó có đề cập đến việc người xưa có thể đã nuốt bột này như một loại thuốc chữa bệnh (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"171\">medicine</em> tương ứng với <em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"194\">cure illness</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d7c25305-de97-415b-be70-66c3eaceb5fc', 'cbefaab9-b1e1-4cbb-b7e4-769b3b0e7bdd', 'fillup', 'Questions 23–26', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Scientists play tricks</strong></span></p>
<p>The passage gives two examples of tricks arising from the playfulness of scientists. Researchers at Caltech found that a colleague had been stealing their {data} and used a hoax involving a fake NMR spectrum to trap the offender. Another story concerns a plate which a famous {English navigator} is said to have left behind on a visit to California.</p>
<p>The {copper and zinc} that the plate was made of later revealed that it was a fake, a hoax carried out by friends of the director of the {bancroft library}</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cde8d3c6-0b24-46f0-91b7-430f960bc346', 'df332c92-4c48-41fb-ace5-f8a71801e0cc', 'matching', 'Questions 27-33', '', '<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct number, <strong>i-ix</strong>, in boxes 1-7.</p>', 'matching_headings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. methods used to investigate termite mound formation"}, {"optionText": "ii. challenging our assumptions about the nature of life"}, {"optionText": "iii. reconsidering the termite’s reputation"}, {"optionText": "iv. principal functions of the termite mound"}, {"optionText": "v. distribution of termite mounds in sub-Saharan Africa"}, {"optionText": "vi. some potential benefits of understanding termite architecture"}, {"optionText": "vii. the astonishing physical dimensions of the termite mound"}, {"optionText": "viii. termite mounds under threat from global climate change"}, {"optionText": "ix. a mutually beneficial relationship"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a1b74cdd-9f71-421c-9e31-f5dc9c1c1c94', '94489cd2-0611-4edd-badd-8e3a86e20530', 'fillup', 'Questions 37–40', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="20" data-index-in-node="35">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 37–40 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-path-to-node="21"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="21" data-index-in-node="0">Lapis lazuli</strong></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-16138 citation-16139 citation-16140 citation-16141">A blue pigment used to create artworks in Europe in the Middle Ages was derived from a stone called lapis lazuli. In medieval times, even {gold}</span><span class="citation-16138 citation-16139 citation-16140 citation-16141"> was not as valuable. Lapis lazuli could only be found in Afghanistan and a lot of {skill}</span><span class="citation-16138 citation-16139 citation-16140 citation-16141 citation-end-16141"> was needed to make the</span><span class="citation-16138 citation-16139 citation-16140 citation-end-16140"> pigment from the stone.</span></p>
<p><span class="citation-16135 citation-16136 citation-16137 citation-end-16137">The procedure used to do this appeared much later in the manuals used by European artists and this suggests that the product came to their countr</span><span class="citation-16135 citation-16136">ies as an imported powder. Artists often had to make a {point}</span><span class="citation-16135 citation-16136 citation-end-16136"> on their brushes using their mouths, which then enabled them to produce</span><span class="citation-16135"> the fine features needed for {manuscripts}</span><span class="citation-16135 citation-end-16135"> and boo</span>ks.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. In medieval times, even {gold} was not as valuable.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…a substance <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">more precious than gold</strong> in Medieval Europe.” (Đoạn E)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Not as valuable” (không giá trị bằng) tương ứng với “more precious than” (quý giá hơn). Tác giả so sánh sắc tố xanh này với vàng để nhấn mạnh sự đắt đỏ của nó vào thời điểm đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. …and a lot of {skill} was needed to make the pigment from the stone.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…the preparation of the pigment <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">took great skill</strong>.” (Đoạn E)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “A lot of” tương ứng với “great”. Việc chế biến đá Lapis Lazuli thành bột màu không hề đơn giản mà đòi hỏi kỹ thuật và kỹ năng (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">skill</em>) rất cao.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Artists often had to make a {point} on their brushes using their mouths,</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…used her lips to <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">make a fine point</strong> on the end of her brush…” (Đoạn G)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để vẽ được những chi tiết cực nhỏ, các nghệ sĩ thường dùng môi/miệng để liếm hoặc vuốt nhọn đầu cọ (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">make a point</em>), giúp đầu cọ sắc nét hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. …which then enabled them to produce the fine features needed for {manuscripts} and books.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…in order to paint intricate detail on <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">manuscripts</strong>.” (Đoạn G)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Fine features” (các đặc điểm tinh xảo) tương ứng với “intricate detail” (chi tiết phức tạp). Việc làm nhọn đầu cọ giúp họ vẽ được những chi tiết này trên các bản thảo viết tay (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"190\">manuscripts</em>) thời Trung cổ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5b3dbd3b-3f60-417d-91c1-5c21e3380f62', '3a087756-f21b-4c93-a62b-7b2d2ef760ae', 'matrix', 'Questions 21-25', NULL, '<p>What is Rosie and Colin’s opinion about each of the following aspects of human geography?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FIVE </strong>answers from the box and write the correct letter, A–G</p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Population ", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Health", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Economies ", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Culture ", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Poverty ", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "The information given about this was too vague.", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "This may not be relevant to their course.", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "This will involve only a small number of statistics.", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "It will be easy to find facts about this.", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "The facts about this may not be reliable.", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "No useful research has been done on this.", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "The information provided about this was interesting.", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>1. Chọn Chủ đề cho Bài Tập (Questions 21–25)<br /> </p>\n<p>ROSIE: Colin, I&#8217;m really struggling to think of a topic for our Human Geography assignment.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Me too, Rosie.</p>\n<p>COLIN: I&#8217;ll tell you what, let&#8217;s think about the different aspects of Human Geography and see if we can narrow the topic down a bit to help us decide.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: OK.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: So one aspect is population.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: That would be all about population density and migration and so on.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: Lots of facts and statistics.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: Maybe a bit boring? (Question 21: Maybe a bit boring?)</p>\n<p>COLIN: Yeah, but quite straightforward to find on the internet. (Question 21: straightforward)</p>\n<p>ROSIE: Suppose so.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: How about health?</p>\n<p>ROSIE: I&#8217;d never thought about the links between that and geography until Professor Lee gave us that lecture on cholera.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: How in the 19th century, a physician used street plans and plans of water supplies to find the source of a cholera epidemic.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Yes, fascinating, wasn&#8217;t it? (Question 22: fascinating)</p>\n<p>COLIN: Or we could do something more general, like economies.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: So how financial and commercial factors are linked to the physical environment?</p>\n<p>COLIN: Yeah.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: I thought that had been taken off the syllabus for this year. (Question 23: off the syllabus)</p>\n<p>COLIN: Has it?</p>\n<p>ROSIE: I&#8217;m not sure, but it might be best to avoid it.</p>\n<p>COLIN: OK.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Maybe we could do something on culture.</p>\n<p>COLIN: We had that lecture about culture and geography last week.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: I didn&#8217;t get much out of that. (Question 24: didn&#8217;t get much out of it)</p>\n<p>ROSIE: It was all so general and the lecturer didn&#8217;t give any useful examples.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Yeah, I hardly took any notes.</p>\n<p>COLIN: It didn&#8217;t seem worth it.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: Me neither.</p>\n<p>COLIN: We could focus on poverty.</p>\n<p>COLIN: That&#8217;s something that&#8217;s a global problem.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: The trouble is, Dr Lee was saying, that you have to be careful with some of the figures relating to poverty.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: They&#8217;re sometimes deliberately manipulated. (Question 25: manipulated)</p>\n<p>COLIN: You mean the information gets changed for political reasons?</p>\n<p>ROSIE: That sort of thing, yes.</p>\n<p> <br /> </p>\n<p>2. Thảo luận về Chủ đề Đô thị hóa (Questions 26–30)<br /> </p>\n<p>ROSIE: So what are we going to do our assignment on?</p>\n<p>ROSIE: I&#8217;ll tell you what.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: One of the possibilities we haven&#8217;t discussed is urbanisation.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: And now over half the world&#8217;s population lives in cities.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>ROSIE: That&#8217;s really important.</p>\n<p>COLIN: OK.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Good idea, Rosie.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Let&#8217;s do that. (Chủ đề được chọn là Urbanisation)</p>\n<p>ROSIE: I love living in a big city, but of course there are problems.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Things like theft and robbery?</p>\n<p>ROSIE: Yes, but where I come from, that&#8217;s linked to another more serious issue, which is that a lot of people don&#8217;t have jobs. (Question 26)</p>\n<p>ROSIE: That&#8217;s getting worse and worse.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: And we also still have quite a lot of people who are homeless, though that&#8217;s not quite so bad as it was.</p>\n<p>COLIN: It&#8217;d be nice to talk about some positive developments, like some of the new developments on the outskirts of cities.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: Yeah.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: They&#8217;ve opened some massive new shopping centres outside my city.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Yeah, the same with mine, but it&#8217;s meant a lot of the shops in the city centre are closing down.</p>\n<p>COLIN: But the outskirts are ideal for buildings that need a lot of space, like for conferences. (Question 27)</p>\n<p>COLIN: They&#8217;ve opened a couple of big ones.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: Yes, we&#8217;ve got some too.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: It&#8217;d be nicer to have more facilities for things like football too, but that&#8217;s not happening where I live.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Same in my area.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: We could include something about developing disused industrial sites.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: It seems like a good idea because you&#8217;re not doing any harm to the natural environment.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Yeah, but aren&#8217;t the buildings architecturally significant?</p>\n<p>ROSIE: Not really.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: And what people forget is that they often used quite dangerous materials, chemicals and things, which haven&#8217;t been properly cleared away. (Question 28)</p>\n<p>ROSIE: So the whole site has to be made safe.</p>\n<p>COLIN: That can&#8217;t be cheap.</p>\n<p>COLIN: And I bet it&#8217;s often not budgeted for.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: You&#8217;re right.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Have you read about Masdar City?</p>\n<p>ROSIE: In Abu Dhabi?</p>\n<p>ROSIE: Yes, it was designed to be a green city, wasn&#8217;t it?</p>\n<p>ROSIE: That might be a good example of a city which set out to depend entirely on renewable energy. (Question 29)</p>\n<p>COLIN: Yes, we should say something about that.</p>\n<p>COLIN: It was designed to be totally pedestrianised too, wasn&#8217;t it?</p>\n<p>COLIN: With the transport underground.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: Yes, and they had big plans for recycling to reduce waste to the lowest possible level.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: But let&#8217;s stick to talking about power sources.</p>\n<p>COLIN: Then there&#8217;s that ecotown in England, Greenhill Abbotts.</p>\n<p>COLIN: It set out to conform to the usual principles, sustainability and so on.</p>\n<p>COLIN: A lot of people were against it at first.</p>\n<p>COLIN: They said the plans were unrealistic. (Question 30)</p>\n<p>COLIN: I&#8217;m not sure how far they&#8217;ve got with it.</p>\n<p>COLIN: I&#8217;ll check.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: Right.</p>\n<p>ROSIE: So it looks as if we have a sort of plan.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1eaf961e-f3b5-4cc5-b575-a4888872ed59', '3a087756-f21b-4c93-a62b-7b2d2ef760ae', 'radio', 'Questions 26 - 30', NULL, '<p><strong>Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</strong></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. crime."}, {"content": "B. housing."}, {"content": "C. unemployment."}], "question": "Rosie says that in her own city the main problem is"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. conference centres"}, {"content": "B. sports centres"}, {"content": "C. retail centres"}], "question": "What recent additions to the outskirts of their cities are both students happy about?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. have unexpected costs."}, {"content": "B. damage the urban environment."}, {"content": "C. destroy valuable historical buildings."}], "question": "The students agree that developing disused industrial sites may"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. daily collections for waste recycling."}, {"content": "B. sustainable energy use."}, {"content": "C. free transport for everyone."}], "question": "The students will mention Masdar City as an example of an attempt to achieve"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. what its objectives were."}, {"content": "B. why there was opposition to it."}, {"content": "C. how much of it has actually been built."}], "question": "When discussing the ecotown of Greenhill Abbots, Colin is uncertain about"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d5d91062-5e1d-4d07-a798-3fa1f506799b', '1b5b7670-da52-402a-84b6-4dd5440096c5', 'fillup', 'Questions 31-40', '<p data-start="103" data-end="132"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong data-start="103" data-end="132">Complete the notes below.</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="134" data-end="174"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong data-start="134" data-end="174">Write ONE WORD ONLY for each answer.</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="134" data-end="174"> </p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="181" data-end="207"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong data-start="181" data-end="207">Developing food trends</strong></span></p>
<ul data-start="209" data-end="642">
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="209" data-end="317">
<p data-start="211" data-end="317"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">The growth in interest in food fashions started with {photos | photographs | pictures}  of food being shared on social media.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="319" data-end="403">
<p data-start="321" data-end="403"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">The UK food industry is constantly developing products which are new or different.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="405" data-end="468">
<p data-start="407" data-end="468"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Influencers on social media become ‘ambassadors’ for a brand.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="470" data-end="537">
<p data-start="472" data-end="537"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Sales of {vegan}  food brands have grown rapidly this way.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="539" data-end="599">
<p data-start="541" data-end="599"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Supermarkets track demand for ingredients on social media.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="601" data-end="642">
<p data-start="603" data-end="642"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Famous {chefs | cooks}  are influential.</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="649" data-end="672"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong data-start="649" data-end="672">Marketing campaigns</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="674" data-end="690"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong data-start="674" data-end="690">The avocado:</strong></span></p>
<ul data-start="692" data-end="812">
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="692" data-end="756">
<p data-start="694" data-end="756"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">{journalists | reporters}  were invited to visit growers in South Africa.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="758" data-end="812">
<p data-start="760" data-end="812"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Advertising focused on its {health}  benefits.</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="819" data-end="832"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong data-start="819" data-end="832">Oat milk:</strong></span></p>
<ul data-start="834" data-end="1074">
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="834" data-end="913">
<p data-start="836" data-end="913"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">A Swedish brand’s media campaign received publicity by upsetting competitors.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="915" data-end="1001">
<p data-start="917" data-end="1001"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Promotion in the USA through {coffee}  shops reduced the need for advertising.</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="1003" data-end="1074">
<p data-start="1005" data-end="1074"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">It appealed to consumers who are concerned about the {environment} .</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1081" data-end="1101"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong data-start="1081" data-end="1101">Norwegian skrei:</strong></span></p>
<ul data-start="1103" data-end="1168">
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="1103" data-end="1168">
<p data-start="1105" data-end="1168"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Has helped strengthen the {reputation}  of Norwegian seafood.</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1175" data-end="1195"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong data-start="1175" data-end="1195">Ethical concerns</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="1197" data-end="1208"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong data-start="1197" data-end="1208">Quinoa:</strong></span></p>
<ul data-start="1210" data-end="1332">
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="1210" data-end="1266">
<p data-start="1212" data-end="1266"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Its success led to an increase in its {price | cost} .</span></p>
</li>
<li style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;" data-start="1268" data-end="1332">
<p data-start="1270" data-end="1332"><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Overuse of resources resulted in poor quality {soil} .</span></p>
</li>
</ul>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>Xu Hướng Trong Thực Phẩm (Fashions in Food)<br /> </p>\n<p>SPEAKER: There are trends in food much as there are trends in clothing. Interest in food fashions has risen rapidly since the birth of the smartphone, when people first began taking photos of their food and instantly sharing them with their friends.</p>\n<p>The food industry in the UK in particular is obsessed with finding and exploiting the next big food trend. Marketeers aim to create a huge demand for a food item which was previously unknown or not needed.</p>\n<p>One of the most effective ways of promoting a new food product is by using social media influencers as brand ambassadors. In return for free samples, many influencers will post content about a product, although there are influencers with hundreds of thousands of followers who can command large fees for their services. Companies which sell vegan produce were pioneers in being able to increase sales really quickly in this way.</p>\n<p>For a food item to become really popular, it has to be readily available. So supermarkets have a role to play in creating a new food trend. They have dedicated teams closely following which new products or ingredients are trending on social media and are particularly interested in what well-known chefs are putting on their menus.</p>\n<p>I&#8217;d like to look at a few examples of marketing campaigns which were really successful in launching a new fashion trend.</p>\n<p>Starting in the 1990s with the avocado. A British PR company was hired to raise its profile and stimulate demand. They paid for a group of journalists to travel out to South Africa to meet avocado farmers. Articles written following this visit helped to educate the British public about the avocado, which at this time was certainly not the daily staple it&#8217;s since become. Advertisements were designed to promote the avocado as a superfood, rich in nutrients and therefore beneficial for health. Avocados became hugely fashionable and within a few years, UK avocado sales had grown from £13 million annually to around £150 million, making it one of the most successful fresh produce campaigns in UK history.</p>\n<p>Oat milk is a recent example of a new product which became fashionable very quickly. Now there are many brands available, but one company which had early success was the Swedish brand Oatly. They attracted a lot of attention with a media campaign which used provocation as a way of getting their message across effectively. The fact that this campaign aggravated competitors producing milk from dairy cows was seen as a plus as it helped to make oat milk seem cool. In the USA, the brand decided against a big retail launch in favour of getting the product into coffee chains, which removed the need for a big advertising budget. This proved far more effective than offering samples in supermarkets. Oat milk had an advantage over other alternative milk products, such as almond milk. Many consumers prefer it because it has less of an impact on the environment. It requires significantly less water to produce than other alternative milk products and it also has a relatively low carbon footprint.</p>\n<p>Norwegian Skrej, a rarely available seasonal fish delicacy otherwise known as Arctic Cod, is now found on the menus of Michelin-starred restaurants throughout Europe. The demand for Skrej has been used by a food marketing agency to build the reputation of Norway&#8217;s fisheries in general. Marketing surveys have shown that a significant number of shoppers now associate Norway with excellent seafood.</p>\n<p>Food trends can be considered a good thing in some ways, as they can benefit farmers and food producers enormously. The public can also be encouraged to buy things which are more sustainably produced.</p>\n<p>But ethical concerns have been raised about the effects a surge in demand can cause. Quinoa is a classic example. This plant is native to Peru and when demand peaked some years ago, the price soared, making it unaffordable for local people. While the popularity of quinoa has benefited farmers financially, there have been other negative consequences. As demand grew, farmers began working the land all year round in order to produce more quinoa. One issue has been that the fertility of the soil decreased dramatically, which could potentially lead to desertification in some areas.</p>\n<p>Another example would be the case of&#8230;</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9886eb71-6be2-4d6a-8519-e7d6af1b14c6', '6273422c-7e57-41bb-a137-ab97ea4579d5', 'matching', 'Questions 11–14', '', '<p>What feature of each of the following walks does the speaker recommend?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FOUR </strong>correct answers, <strong>A-G</strong>, next to questions <strong>11-14</strong>.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Walks</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Boundary Walk {seashore}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Loop Track {views}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Puriri Walk {picnic area}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>North Head {wildlife}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "picnic area"}, {"optionText": "historic building"}, {"optionText": "flat paths"}, {"optionText": "seashore"}, {"optionText": "art works"}, {"optionText": "wildlife"}, {"optionText": "views"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 2</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Guide:</strong> Well morning everyone. Welcome to Palm Island. First I’ll run through the plan for the day so, um, the idea is that in the morning you’ll go for a walk. There are actually a number of different walks on the island, so I’ll describe each one and then you can choose.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">So there’s the <strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">Boundary Walk</strong>. <span class=\"citation-89 citation-end-89\">This is one of the longer walks and it will appeal especially to people who love the coastline. And in fact, the tide is out today so it’ll be perfect for exploring the very old rock formations behind th<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>e <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"235\">(11) beach (D: seashore)</strong></span>.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">A good option is the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Loop Track</strong>. Now this is quite short, but don’t be misled by that because it’s very hilly and you need to be quite fit. The reward though is that you’ll be able to see right down the length of the island and even across to the mainland. It’ll be <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"266\">(12) pretty as a picture (G: views)</strong> </span>on a fine day like today.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">There’s the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Puriri Walk</strong>, which follows one of the earliest trails that was built on the island. Unfortunately, the track’s been damaged slightly by a storm but it’s still passable. The nice thing is, about halfway there’s a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"224\">(13) table and chairs (A: picnic area)</strong></span>. They’ve recently been restored and painted in fact, and it’s a great place to eat your packed lunch and have a rest.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">You could also walk up to <strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">North Head</strong>. This is an inland walk—you’ll hardly get a glimpse of the sea the whole way—but the attraction is you’ll pass through a large area of very old native bush. The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"198\">(14) number of birds is amazing (F: wildlife)</strong></span>, including several rare species. You’ll find some are quite tame, but please don’t give them any food.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Guide:</strong> Okay well after your walk, the bus will take you to the Regional Park where you can relax for a couple of hours before going home. Now if you look at your maps of the Regional Park, I’ll just describe a few things you can do.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">So the bus will drop you at the park entrance, right at the bottom of the map. One interesting place is the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">(15) bird colony</strong></span>. To get there from the park entrance, you go up the path to the lake. About halfway round the east side of the lake, you need to turn off and take the path all the way out to the coast. You’ll find the colony there, overlooking a little island <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"369\">(D)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Now if you’d like a swim, remember that not all the beaches are really suitable in this wind. For the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">(16) safest place (Safe swimming beach)</strong></span>, follow the path north from the park entrance, but before you get to the lake, turn right and go down there to the beach <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"263\">(F)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">Something that people find interesting is the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">(17) old ship</strong></span>. It’s more than 100 years old. To get there, just north of the park entrance, you take the path which heads towards Okiwi Bay, then walk along the coast a little way before turning right and following that path over to Rocky Bay. You’ll see the wharf—go past that and the ship is just along there <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"357\">(J)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">A long walk but one that’s well worth it is up to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">(18) Stony Batter</strong></span>. You follow the path right around the lake to the far side and keep heading north. But if you reach the water tower, you’ve gone too far. Before that, you want to turn off to your left and take the path to the coast <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"284\">(E)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">Now where else is there… oh yes, the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">(19) Settlers’ Monument</strong></span>, that’s popular. So from the park entrance, take the first path on the left and follow it around behind Okiwi Bay. The Monument is out at the end there on the headland <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"231\">(C)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">Finally, if all this exercise has made you thirsty, there’s a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">(20) kiosk</strong></span> where you can get hot and cold drinks. It’s easy to find beside the lake, right on the water’s edge <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"173\">(I)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">Well now, if anyone has any questions feel free…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('66f0944e-2375-4e96-bd5e-29c81beed6a5', '7e1877f2-1970-4021-a964-a176ae473713', 'radio', 'Questions 6–14', '', '<p data-path-to-node="13,0,0">Choose<strong data-path-to-node="13,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"> TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information,<strong data-path-to-node="13,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information,<strong data-path-to-node="13,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">NOT GIVEN</strong> if the<span class="citation-23532 citation-23533 citation-23534 citation-23535 citation-end-23535">re is no information on this </span></p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Builders have already started work on the new primary school."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The new school will take in children from outside Frog Valley."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There will be an increase in the number of shops."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The community centre will replace an existing social club building."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The swimming pool will be free for residents of Frog Valley."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The office space will accommodate businesses of different sizes."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The business car parking area will be underground."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The health centre will offer a wide range of new services."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "At present, there are too few doctors at the health centre."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Builders have already started work on the new primary school. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…if building <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">does go ahead</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu “if building does go ahead” (nếu việc xây dựng được tiến hành) cho thấy đây vẫn là dự án trên giấy, chưa hề bắt đầu khởi công.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. The new school will take in children from outside Frog Valley. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…admission will <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">not be limited to families who live in the area</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Not be limited to” (không giới hạn cho người trong vùng) đồng nghĩa với việc sẽ nhận cả trẻ em từ bên ngoài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. There will be an increase in the number of shops. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…move all the existing local shops… into one shopping zone, and this will see the <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">addition of an organic farm shop and a vegan store</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói sẽ gom các shop cũ lại và <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">thêm mới</strong> (addition) hai cửa hàng khác. Có thêm cửa hàng mới nghĩa là tổng số lượng tăng lên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. The community centre will replace an existing social club building. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “It will provide a much needed meeting place for clubs and societies that, <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">until now, have had to meet wherever they can find a venue</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói các câu lạc bộ trước nay phải “họp bất cứ đâu” vì chưa có chỗ, chứ không phải trung tâm này thay thế một tòa nhà có sẵn của họ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. The swimming pool will be free for residents of Frog Valley. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “The pride of the centre will be a multi-gym with swimming pool…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến bể bơi nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">không có thông tin</strong> nào nói về việc nó miễn phí hay mất phí.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. The office space will accommodate businesses of different sizes. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…house <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">anything from small startups to large existing local businesses</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Different sizes” tương ứng với quy mô từ startup nhỏ đến doanh nghiệp lớn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. The business car parking area will be underground. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…with dedicated car parking for office workers…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói có bãi đậu xe riêng, <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">không đề cập</strong> nó nằm dưới hầm (underground) hay trên mặt đất.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. The health centre will offer a wide range of new services. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…asked if it would be possible to include services such as dentistry… <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">there are no plans to do this at present</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cư dân yêu cầu thêm các dịch vụ mới (nha khoa, xét nghiệm) nhưng kế hoạch hiện tại là <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">không thực hiện</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. At present, there are too few doctors at the health centre. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…it will be possible to see a doctor at weekends and in the evenings…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói về việc mở rộng thời gian khám bệnh, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">không hề đánh giá</strong> số lượng bác sĩ hiện tại là đủ hay thiếu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('95135e0e-31a6-497a-8e10-34ead8a07af7', 'a1b88824-6230-4a7e-b50b-647a59842b7a', 'radio', 'Questions 21–24', '', '<p data-start="90" data-end="116">Choose the correct answer.</p>
<p data-start="118" data-end="158"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The Just-in-Time Supply System (JIT)</span></strong></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "given credit to the originators of the JIT idea"}, {"option_text": "discussed why the Japanese adopted the JIT idea"}, {"option_text": "explained how supermarkets used the JIT idea"}], "question": "Ron suggests that in his presentation he should have"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "a description of classic business theory"}, {"option_text": "an introductory definition of JIT"}, {"option_text": "a statement of the aims of JIT"}], "question": "The tutor says that in his presentation Ron omitted"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "a website"}, {"option_text": "journal articles"}, {"option_text": "a textbook"}], "question": "Ron says that he found his information on standardising parts from"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "difficult to apply because of the absence of countable things"}, {"option_text": "regarded by most members of staff as unfashionable"}, {"option_text": "unlikely to be accepted by important clients"}], "question": "The tutor suggests that in the service sector, JIT is"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 3: FEEDBACK ON BUSINESS PRESENTATION</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Thanks, Ron, for coming to my office to discuss the presentation you gave yesterday to the Business Management Seminar. We’ll go over what you did with the aim of helping you improve your next presentation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Sounds good.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Now, the topic was the Just-in-Time, or J-I-T supply system used by a lot of manufacturers, first in Japan and then in the West, I think?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Yes, but actually one thing <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">(21) I should have made clearer and talked about was the fact that the Americans actually pioneered the idea of Just-in-Time [Answer: A – credit to the originators]</strong></span>, though it wasn’t called that. Henry Ford and his cars, in fact, at the turn of the 20th century. And later, a big US supermarket chain used it, and this was where Toyota in Japan got the idea for its car making.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Yes, that would have been a good addition. And now before we go any further, I think I would suggest that <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">(22) you should have stopped and clearly defined Just-in-Time for your seminar colleagues [Answer: B – introductory definition]</strong></span>. You said its aim was to reduce waste, and you mentioned that classic business theory assumes that stock or inventory of parts are counted as assets, but Just-in-Time sees them as unnecessary waste. But you never told us that J-I-T simply means waiting until the last moment to order new supplies as you need them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Yes, you’re right. I should have done that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Now, you talked a bit about standardizing parts as a way of streamlining JIT. Where did you get your data from?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Well, I tried an internet website on the subject, which is called the Lean Clearing House, but it was too technical for me. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">(23) So in the end, I got my data from a textbook called “Learning from Toyota” [Answer: C – textbook]</strong></span>. I found some journal articles too, but they didn’t seem very useful.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Yes, well, there is a US government report on it I’ve seen. I’ll get a copy for you.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Great, I look forward to reading through it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> And while you’re at it, you might want to find out about cases where JIT might not be suitable, and that’s in service industries like tourism or healthcare, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">(24) where customers are paying for something that they can’t actually see or count [Answer: A – absence of countable things]</strong></span>. Although J-I-T is fashionable today, some people would say it hasn’t proved so successful in the service sector as it has with the manufacturing of goods that can be quantified.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> That would be interesting. I’ll see what I can find out.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CRITIQUE OF TECHNICAL ASPECTS (Questions 25–30)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Now, unless you have any more questions, let’s turn to a critique of the technical aspects of the presentation. I’m afraid I’ll emphasize the things I think you might want to work on. It was a good talk, but with a little work, your next presentation should be excellent.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Fine, that would be helpful. Actually, I wasn’t happy with my <strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">delivery</strong>. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">(25) I sometimes seemed to talk fast and sometimes slow [Answer: B – too irregular]</strong></span>. I was on edge, I guess.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Yes, you were. And as well as that, your <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">purpose</strong> wasn’t very specific. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">(26) In future, you need to lay out exactly what you’re going to cover and why [Answer: H – too vague]</strong></span>. Make it clear and concise and not so general.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> And what about my <strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">transitions</strong> from one section to the next?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Well, you didn’t link the sections, did you? You went too quickly from one to the next.<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">(27) It was all just too abrupt [Answer: D – too sudden]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> OK, I’ll try to improve that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Now, your <strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"17\">PowerPoint visuals</strong> were lovely, but sometimes I got the feeling that, nice as they were as pictures, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">(28) they didn’t have much to do with what you were talking about [Answer: G – too loosely related]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Right, you’re right.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> And you know, another thing I could see from the other students’ reactions: <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">(29) they just didn’t understand some of the vocabulary I was using [Answer: E – too technical]</strong></span>. Hmm…good point and remember your audience were laymen, mostly without knowledge of JIT, so you need to simplify and try to put things in everyday English.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> I never seem to do that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> And lastly, I’ll just mention your <strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">body language</strong>. You didn’t use gestures, and you just stood straight without any animation. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">(30) It didn’t make you seem very interested in the subject [Answer: F – too unenthusiastic]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> I know, even though I really do like the subject. Sorry.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Tutor:</strong> Well, despite all this, I enjoyed your presentation and I could see you put lots of work into it. I look forward to an even better presentation from you next time.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Ron:</strong> Well, thanks for your help.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('03667345-6339-4896-b584-76c93b803d0b', '1917d49b-66e7-4167-837b-de28547e4a60', 'radio', 'Questions 8-10 ', NULL, '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
</div>
</div>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": " He is less famous than he should be."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "He was famous as a doctor before he was employed by the Queen."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "He lost faith in the medical theories of his time."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. He is less famous than he should be: TRUE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 1, câu cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;However, he is <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">less well known than he deserves</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ &#8220;less well known&#8221; tương ứng với &#8220;less famous&#8221;, và &#8220;than he deserves&#8221; (hơn mức ông xứng đáng) tương ứng với &#8220;than he should be&#8221;. Tác giả khẳng định tầm quan trọng của ông chưa được công nhận rộng rãi như lẽ ra phải thế.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. He was famous as a doctor before he was employed by the Queen: TRUE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3 và đoạn 6.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;He was a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">very successful and eminent doctor</strong>. All this <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">culminated</strong> in his election to the president of the Royal Science Society. He was <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">also</strong> appointed personal physician to the Queen&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> * Bài đọc mô tả ông là một bác sĩ &#8220;rất thành công và lỗi lạc&#8221; (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">very successful and eminent</em>).</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,1,0,0\">Từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"3\">&#8220;culminated&#8221;</strong> (đỉnh điểm/kết quả của một quá trình) cho thấy những thành tựu và sự nổi danh trong ngành y của ông đã diễn ra trước.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,1,1,0\">Việc được bầu làm Chủ tịch Hội Khoa học Hoàng gia và việc được bổ nhiệm làm bác sĩ cho Nữ hoàng là những sự kiện nối tiếp sự nghiệp lừng lẫy đó. Trong logic IELTS, &#8220;eminent&#8221; (lỗi lạc/nổi tiếng trong lĩnh vực chuyên môn) đi kèm với một chuỗi thành tựu trước khi phục vụ hoàng gia chính là bằng chứng xác nhận ông đã danh tiếng từ trước.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. He lost faith in the medical theories of his time: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 4.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Gilbert was first interested in chemistry but later changed his focus due to the large portion of mysticism of alchemy involved&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói ông từ bỏ <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">hóa học/thuật giả kim</strong> (chemistry/alchemy) vì nó mang tính thần bí. Về mảng <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">y học</strong> (medical), bài đọc vẫn nói ông là một bác sĩ rất thành công và phục vụ hoàng gia cho đến khi qua đời. Không có thông tin nào cho thấy ông mất niềm tin vào các lý thuyết y học đương thời.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4177cfad-d16a-4dc9-a31f-8cfed628ed76', 'a2682f5a-008c-4b35-b48e-a0e5d7ae138d', 'radio', 'Questions 8–13', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Their first sight of silk created fear among Roman soldiers."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The quality of Chinese silk imported by the early Romans varied widely."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Byzantine emperor first acquired silkworm eggs from the Chinese emperor."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The price of high-grade Chinese silk fell due to competition from Middle-Eastern producers."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Silk was produced in the Middle East several centuries before it was produced in Europe."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Global silk production has declined in recent years."}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>8. Their first sight of silk created fear among Roman soldiers.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “…at an important battle near the Euphrates River in 53 BC, the Roman soldiers were <strong>so startled by the bright silken banners of the enemy that they fled in panic</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Lính La Mã kinh ngạc (<em>startled</em>) và hoảng loạn (<em>fled in panic</em>) khi nhìn thấy cờ lụa sáng màu của kẻ thù, điều này cho thấy sự sợ hãi.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>9. The quality of Chinese silk imported by the early Romans varied widely.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) Văn bản chỉ nói lụa Trung Quốc được giới nhà giàu và quý tộc La Mã mặc (<em>“widely worn by the rich and noble families of Rome”</em>), <strong>không có thông tin</strong> về sự đa dạng về chất lượng (quality) của lụa nhập khẩu.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>10. The Byzantine emperor first acquired silkworm eggs from the Chinese emperor.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “Records indicate that <strong>two monks</strong> from Constantinople… appeared at their emperor’s court with silkworm eggs <strong>which they had obtained secretly</strong>, and hidden in their hollow bamboo walking sticks.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Trứng tằm được mang về một cách bí mật (<em>obtained secretly</em>) bởi hai nhà sư (<em>two monks</em>), chứ không phải do hoàng đế Trung Quốc tặng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>11. The price of high-grade Chinese silk fell due to competition from Middle-Eastern producers.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “This allowed a silk industry to be established, <strong>undercutting the market for ordinary-grade Chinese silk</strong>. However, <strong>high quality silk textiles</strong>… <strong>continued to achieve high prices</strong> in the West…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cạnh tranh chỉ làm giảm giá lụa loại thường (<em>ordinary-grade</em>), còn lụa loại cao cấp (<em>high quality</em>) vẫn giữ giá cao (<em>continued to achieve high prices</em>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>12. Silk was produced in the Middle East several centuries before it was produced in Europe.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) Lụa bắt đầu được sản xuất ở Trung Đông (<em>Middle East</em>) khoảng <strong>550 AD</strong>; nhưng mãi đến <strong>thế kỷ 13</strong> (<em>13th century</em>), Ý (Europe) mới bắt đầu sản xuất.</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> 550 AD là nhiều thế kỷ trước thế kỷ 13.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>13. Global silk production has declined in recent years.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) “<strong>World silk production has approximately doubled during the last 30 years</strong> in spite of manmade fibres replacing certain uses of silk.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sản lượng lụa toàn cầu đã <strong>tăng gấp đôi</strong> (<em>doubled</em>) trong 30 năm qua.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('133c7bc0-c28c-4388-a2c7-32d3bf50c2fe', '949f02d5-892c-45d4-a229-f14d6bf74318', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–6', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>THE EARLY HISTORY OF GRAPHITE IN BRITAIN</strong></p>
<p>– Graphite was first found below a {tree} blown down in a storm.</p>
<p>– The first use of graphite was to make marks on {sheep}.</p>
<p>– The characteristics of raw graphite:</p>
<p>+ dirty to use because it is so {soft}</p>
<p>+ originally wrapped in {rope} or animal skin to make it useable as a pencil.</p>
<p>– Graphite came to the notice of the government for military and commercial purposes.</p>
<p>+ The government completely took over the {mines} at Borrowdale.</p>
<p>+ They employed guards to protect the graphite on its journey south.</p>
<p>– Local people began to {steal} graphite for the money involved.</p>
<p>+ The government passed a law to protect the graphite industry.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">1. Graphite was first found below a {tree} blown down in a storm.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>tree</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 1, dòng 3.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…locals in the village of Borrowdale discovered a large uprooted <strong>tree</strong>. Underneath the <strong>tree</strong> lay an unknown black substance…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc mô tả sau một trận bão lớn (<em>ferocious weather</em>), một cái cây bị bật gốc (<em>uprooted</em>) và người ta tìm thấy graphite ở bên dưới nó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">2. The first use of graphite was to make marks on {sheep}.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>sheep</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 2, dòng 1.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Initially, the local farmers used the newly discovered material as a handy way to identify their <strong>sheep</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Công dụng đầu tiên của graphite không phải để viết mà là để những người nông dân đánh dấu/nhận diện đàn <strong>cừu</strong> của họ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">3. The characteristics of raw graphite: dirty to use because it is so {soft}</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>soft</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 2, dòng 3.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “When it was untreated the material was very <strong>soft</strong>, which meant that it was messy to handle.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> “Dirty to use” trong câu hỏi đồng nghĩa với “messy to handle” (bẩn/lộn xộn khi cầm nắm). Nguyên nhân là do ở trạng thái thô, graphite rất <strong>mềm</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">4. …originally wrapped in {rope} or animal skin to make it useable as a pencil.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>rope</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 2, dòng 4.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…people enclosed a thin core of the substance in stiff sheep hides or <strong>rope</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Để dùng làm bút viết mà không bị bẩn tay, người ta bọc graphite trong da cừu (<em>sheep hides</em> – tương ứng với <em>animal skin</em>) hoặc dây thừng (<strong>rope</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">5. The government completely took over the {mines} at Borrowdale.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>mines</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 7.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the government quickly realised the commercial potential… and assumed control of all the <strong>mines</strong> there during the sixteenth century.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> “Took over” đồng nghĩa với “assumed control of” (chiếm quyền kiểm soát/tiếp quản). Chính phủ đã tiếp quản toàn bộ các <strong>mỏ</strong> graphite.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">6. Local people began to {steal} graphite for the money involved.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>steal</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 10.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The graphite was so valuable that the locals… started to <strong>steal</strong> it.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Vì giá trị kinh tế cao, người dân địa phương bắt đầu lấy trộm (<strong>steal</strong>) graphite, dẫn đến việc chính phủ phải ban hành luật để trừng phạt hành vi này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c81b87b7-16a8-48b7-a737-fcbc720b4a95', '6273422c-7e57-41bb-a137-ab97ea4579d5', 'matrix', 'Questions 15–20', NULL, '<p>Label the map below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A-J</strong>, next to questions <strong>15-20</strong>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="data:image/png;base64," width="508" height="422" loading="lazy"></p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Bird colony", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Safe swimming beach", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "Old ship", "correctCategoryLetter": "J"}, {"itemText": "Stony Batter", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "Settlers’ Monument", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Kiosk", "correctCategoryLetter": "I"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}, {"categoryText": "I", "categoryLetter": "I"}, {"categoryText": "J", "categoryLetter": "J"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('40100a7a-d8ac-4c32-bde3-164bb9326014', '8c3f6ab2-4ae5-482a-b137-2f2b191e482b', 'fillup', 'Questions 22-26', '<p>Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>There is little information on the origin of the tomato despite the existence of  {archaeological} data on the growing of other New World crops.</p>
<p>Although it is uncertain, the tomato is thought to have first grown in the {Andes}  .</p>
<p>In regard to genetic similarities, the {currant}  tomato is the nearest to the earliest type of tomato.</p>
<p>A genetic {mutation}  which is evident in pomodoro produced larger tomatoes.</p>
<p>{infections}  are а problem for heirloom tomatoes because they frequently lead to damage and deterioration.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>22. There is little information on the origin of the tomato despite the existence of <strong>archaeological</strong> data on the growing of other New World crops.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>archaeological</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) &#8220;But whereas scientists have uncovered a wealth of <strong>archaeological</strong> evidence on early farming practices in the New World, the record is blank when it comes to the tomato.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Dữ liệu khảo cổ học (<strong>archaeological</strong>) phong phú về các cây trồng khác ở Tân Thế giới, nhưng lại thiếu thông tin về cà chua.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>23. Although it is uncertain, the tomato is thought to have first grown in the <strong>Andes</strong>.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Andes</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) &#8220;The modern tomato seems to have its origins in the <strong>Andes</strong> in South America, and may have been domesticated in Vera Cruz, Mexico.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cà chua được cho là có nguồn gốc từ vùng Andes.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>24. In regard to genetic similarities, the <strong>currant</strong> tomato is the nearest to the earliest type of tomato.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>currant</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) &#8220;The closest relative is the <strong>currant</strong> tomato which, based on genetic comparisons, split from today’s tomato some 1.4 million years ago.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cà chua currant là họ hàng gần nhất (nearest) với loại cà chua sớm nhất.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>25. A genetic <strong>mutation</strong> which is evident in pomodoro produced larger tomatoes.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>mutation</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) &#8220;&#8230;Tanksley concludes&#8230; our ancestors ultimately exploited just 30 <strong>mutations</strong> out of the tomato’s 35,000 genes&#8230; The first written record of tomatoes&#8230; confirms that this <strong>mutation</strong>, which enlarges tomatoes&#8230; existed back in the same yellow tomatoes that gave Italians the word <em>pomodoro</em>&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sự thay đổi di truyền làm cà chua lớn hơn được gọi là <strong>mutation</strong> (đột biến).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>26. <strong>Infections</strong> are a problem for heirloom tomatoes because they frequently lead to damage and deterioration.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Infections</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) &#8220;They often suffer from <strong>infections</strong> that cause the fruit to crack, split and otherwise rot quickly.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cà chua heirloom dễ bị <strong>infections</strong> (nhiễm trùng) dẫn đến hư hỏng và thối rữa</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('74d36509-a391-4338-8b41-0446d216adcd', 'd15a5b6d-9908-49e9-9b7a-630bac1ae26f', 'matrix', 'Questions 14–18', NULL, '<p>Look at the following statements (Questions 14-18) and the list of people below.</p>
<p>Match each statement with the correct person, <strong>A-D</strong>.</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A-D</strong>, in boxes 14-18.</p>
<p><strong>NB </strong>You may use any letter more than once.</p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of people", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "High-level workers tend to react positively to stress.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Stress levels are increased by trying to please customers.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Support from other workers may relieve stress.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Lack of independence at work is often responsible for stress.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Workers commonly expect their workloads to lessen over time.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Neil Plumridge", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Gal Zauberman and John Lynch", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Jan Elsner", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Tony LaMontagne", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"5\">14. High-level workers tend to react positively to stress.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “Jan Elsner, a psychologist who specialises in executive coaching, says that <strong>doing well on a demanding workload is typical of senior executives</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Jan Elsner nói rằng việc <strong>làm tốt công việc với khối lượng đòi hỏi cao là điển hình của các giám đốc điều hành cấp cao</strong> (<em>senior executives</em>), cho thấy họ có xu hướng phản ứng tích cực (<em>react positively</em>) với áp lực công việc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"8\">15. Stress levels are increased by trying to please customers.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “‘I’ll <strong>promise a client that I’ll do something tomorrow</strong>, and then I’ll promise another client that I’ll do the same thing, when I know it’s not going to happen.’”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Neil Plumridge mô tả việc hứa hẹn với khách hàng (<em>promise a client</em>) những điều không thực tế đã gây ra căng thẳng cho chính anh ấy, điều này phù hợp với việc cố gắng làm hài lòng khách hàng (<em>trying to please customers</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"11\">16. Support from other workers may relieve stress.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “He also <strong>relies on the advice of colleagues</strong>, saying that his peers coach each other on business problems: ‘Just a fresh pair of eyes over an issue can help,’ he states.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Neil Plumridge <strong>dựa vào lời khuyên của đồng nghiệp</strong> (<em>relies on the advice of colleagues</em>), cho thấy sự hỗ trợ từ đồng nghiệp có thể giúp giảm căng thẳng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"14\">17. Lack of independence at work is often responsible for stress.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) “His recent research shows that the <strong>major predictor of stress is the level of job control a person has</strong>… The worst jobs combine challenging work and <strong>low control</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tony LaMontagne nói rằng yếu tố dự báo chính gây căng thẳng là mức độ kiểm soát công việc (<em>job control</em>). Công việc có <strong>ít kiểm soát</strong> (<em>low control</em>) hay thiếu tự chủ (<em>lack of independence</em>) là nguyên nhân chính gây ra căng thẳng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"17\">18. Workers commonly expect their workloads to lessen over time.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “A study in the JOURNAL OF EXPERIMENTAL PSYCHOLOGY shows that <strong>people always believe that they will be less busy in the future</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu của Gal Zauberman và John Lynch chỉ ra rằng mọi người luôn tin rằng họ sẽ <strong>ít bận rộn hơn trong tương lai</strong> (<em>less busy in the future</em>), tức là họ kỳ vọng khối lượng công việc sẽ giảm bớt theo thời gian.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('21d2f1dd-95ba-42ad-b9c4-a86a3a5788ae', 'd15a5b6d-9908-49e9-9b7a-630bac1ae26f', 'radio', 'Questions 19–21', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "an inability to keep to his schedule"}, {"content": "inattention to family celebrations"}, {"content": "a lack of concentration on a task"}, {"content": "a period of insufficient sleep"}], "question": "Which of the following is NOT mentioned by Neil Plumridge as an indication that his workload is too heavy?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "rethinking ideas of what can be achieved"}, {"content": "extending the deadline for completing the task"}, {"content": "using more workers on a project"}, {"content": "taking more time off for sport or other recreation"}], "question": "Which method of lessening work stress is NOT suggested by Neil Plumridge?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "taking a worker''s mind off his troubles."}, {"content": "changing physical response to stress."}, {"content": "resting more effectively."}, {"content": "encouraging executives to take breaks."}], "question": "According to Jan Elsner, meditation offers a method of"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">19. Which of the following is NOT mentioned by Neil Plumridge as an indication that his workload is too heavy?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C. A lack of concentration on a task</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) Plumridge đề cập đến ba dấu hiệu: <strong>ngủ</strong> (<em>sleep</em> – less than six hours’ sleep), <strong>sắp xếp lịch trình</strong> (<em>scheduling</em> – having to reschedule appointments), và <strong>gia đình</strong> (<em>family</em> – misses a family birthday or anniversary).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cả A (reschedule), B (misses family), và D (insufficient sleep) đều được nhắc đến. <strong>Thiếu tập trung</strong> (<em>lack of concentration</em>) <strong>không</strong> nằm trong ba dấu hiệu cảnh báo của anh ấy.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">20. Which method of lessening work stress is NOT suggested by Neil Plumridge?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D. taking more time off for sport or other recreation</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) Plumridge nói về việc <strong>tái đánh giá khối lượng công việc</strong> (<em>reassess workloads</em>): “allocating extra staff to a job,” “allowing more time,” or “changing expectations.” Anh ấy cũng nói về việc nhờ đồng nghiệp hỗ trợ.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Anh ấy đề xuất A (changing expectations), B (allowing more time), và C (allocating extra staff). Anh ấy <strong>không</strong> đề xuất các hoạt động thư giãn vật lý như chơi thể thao (<em>sport or other recreation</em>). Thực tế, Đoạn E mở đầu bằng việc các chuyên gia nói rằng <strong>chìa khóa không phải là tập trung vào thư giãn</strong> (<em>relief</em> – a game of golf or a massage).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">21. According to Jan Elsner, meditation offers a method of:</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B. changing physical response to stress</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “She points to research showing that meditation can <strong>alter the biochemistry of the brain and the way that brains and bodies react to stress</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Thiền định có thể thay đổi hóa sinh của não và cách cơ thể phản ứng với căng thẳng, điều này đồng nghĩa với việc <strong>thay đổi phản ứng vật lý</strong> (<em>changing physical response</em>) đối với căng thẳng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('43d86e60-9928-444e-ac46-863fa45fb2fa', '633f7590-e44b-4545-8c87-b2be27277961', 'radio', 'Questions 15–24', '', '<p data-path-to-node="5,0,0">Choose<strong data-path-to-node="5,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"> TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information,<strong data-path-to-node="5,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information,<strong data-path-to-node="5,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">NOT GIVEN</strong> if the<span class="citation-27900 citation-27901 citation-27902 citation-27903 citation-end-27903">re is no information on this</span></p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "All of the staff have overseas teaching experience."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "All modules are of equal length."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Students are encouraged to take holidays in the two-week breaks between modules."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Courses may have very different timetables."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "You can still obtain an attendance certificate if you have been absent through illness."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Permission is required for students to bring guests into the restaurant."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The coffee lounge is closed in the evenings."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Groups of 20 or more can make reservations to dine at the restaurant on public holidays."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Guests may use the swimming pool."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Students are unable to enter the institute after 8.30 pm."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. All of the staff have overseas teaching experience. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…highly trained and experienced teaching staff, <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">many of whom</strong> have taught overseas.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết chỉ nói “nhiều người” (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">many</em>), không phải “tất cả” (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">all</em>). Sự khác biệt về định lượng này khiến câu khẳng định trở nên sai.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. All modules are of equal length. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Percil Training Institute provides courses in <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">ten-week modules</strong>.” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Viện quy định các học phần đều kéo dài 10 tuần. Do đó, tất cả các học phần đều có độ dài bằng nhau.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Students are encouraged to take holidays in the two-week breaks between modules. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…it is <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">not possible to take vacations</strong> during this time.” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngược lại với việc được khuyến khích, bài đọc nêu rõ sinh viên không thể đi nghỉ vì phải làm bài tập/dự án trong thời gian này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Courses may have very different timetables. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Since each course has <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">varying needs</strong>, there are <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">not necessarily any set hours</strong> for classes across all programmes.” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Varying needs” (nhu cầu khác nhau) và “not set hours” (không có giờ cố định chung) xác nhận rằng lịch học giữa các khóa có sự khác biệt lớn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. You can still obtain an attendance certificate if you have been absent through illness. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “In this case [illness], an <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">achievement certificate only</strong> will be issued.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Achievement certificate only” (chỉ cấp chứng chỉ thành tích) đồng nghĩa với việc bạn sẽ không nhận được chứng chỉ chuyên cần (<em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">attendance certificate</em>) dù nghỉ có lý do chính đáng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Permission is required for students to bring guests into the restaurant. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “The coffee lounge and restaurant are not normally open on public holidays. However, a group booking may be made…” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói về việc đặt bàn cho nhóm, <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">không nhắc gì</strong> đến quy định xin phép khi dẫn khách đi cùng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. The coffee lounge is closed in the evenings. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “The opening times… are printed below your course timetable.” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ dẫn người học xem giờ mở cửa trong tờ lịch trình riêng, <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">không cung cấp thông tin cụ thể</strong> về việc tối ngày thường có đóng cửa hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Groups of 20 or more can make reservations to dine at the restaurant on public holidays. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…a group booking may be made for the restaurant… on such days [public holidays], provided that there is a <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">minimum of 20 people</strong> in the group.” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Minimum of 20” (tối thiểu 20) khớp với “Groups of 20 or more”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Guests may use the swimming pool. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Guests</strong> of Percil students <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">are welcome to use the swimming pool</strong>…” (Đoạn 7)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Students are unable to enter the institute after 8.30 pm. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “If you need to <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">gain access to the Institute after this time [8.30 pm]</strong>, please contact the caretaker by pressing the doorbell…” (Đoạn 8)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sinh viên vẫn có thể vào (gain access) bằng cách gọi người quản gia qua chuông cửa, nên việc nói “không thể vào” là sai.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8ee0b8f5-e16c-4c7b-a704-868e612ff4b9', 'a1b88824-6230-4a7e-b50b-647a59842b7a', 'matching', 'Questions 25–30', '', '<p>What criticism is made of each of the following technical aspect of Ron’s presentation?<br data-start="1026" data-end="1029">Choose <strong>SIX </strong>correct answers, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>H</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Technical aspects of presentation</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>speed of delivery {too irregular}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>purpose {too vague}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>transitions {too sudden}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>visuals {too loosely related}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>vocabulary {too technical}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>body language {too unenthusiastic}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "too informal"}, {"optionText": "too irregular"}, {"optionText": "too predictable"}, {"optionText": "too sudden"}, {"optionText": "too technical"}, {"optionText": "too unenthusiastic"}, {"optionText": "too loosely related"}, {"optionText": "too vague"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f22192cf-63ac-4296-933b-ec8de0de1553', 'd15a5b6d-9908-49e9-9b7a-630bac1ae26f', 'fillup', 'Question 22-26', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p class="quests-inner-desc">Complete the summary below.</p>
<p class="quests-inner-desc">Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p class="quests-inner-desc" style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Stress: its effects and how to reduce it</strong></span></p>
<p class="quests-inner-desc">Statistics on workers’ compensation show that people take more time off work due to stress than for any other {injury} at work. On average, workers who take time off because of stress stay away for {16.6 weeks} . This absence comes at a high price – while the number of insurance claims due to stress amount to only {7% | seven percent | 7 percent} of the total, they account for a much higher proportion of the cost of claims payments.Experts believe that seeking to relieve stress through physical therapies such as sport or {a massage} may be less effective than simply reviewing your {workloads} .</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">22. Statistics on workers’ compensation show that people take more time off work due to stress than for <strong>any workplace injury</strong>.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>injury</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “Figures for National Workers’ Compensation… show that stress causes the <strong>most lost time of any workplace injury</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Căng thẳng gây ra số ngày nghỉ việc nhiều nhất so với <strong>bất kỳ chấn thương nơi làm việc nào khác</strong> (<em>any workplace injury</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">23. On average, workers who take time off because of stress stay away for <strong>16.6 weeks</strong>.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>16.6 weeks</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “…employees suffering stress are absent from work for an average of <strong>16.6 weeks</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Trung bình, nhân viên nghỉ làm vì căng thẳng trong <strong>16.6 tuần</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\">24. …the number of insurance claims due to stress amount to only <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> <strong>7%</strong> of the total, they account for a much higher proportion of the cost of claims payments.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>7%</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “…claims for stress-related psychological injury accounted for <strong>7% of insurance claims</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các khiếu nại liên quan đến căng thẳng chiếm <strong>7%</strong> tổng số yêu cầu bảo hiểm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\">25. Experts believe that seeking to relieve stress through physical therapies such as sport or <strong>a massage</strong> may be less effective…</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>a massage</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “Experts say the key to dealing with stress is not to focus on relief – a game of golf or <strong>a massage</strong> – but to reassess workloads.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các chuyên gia cho rằng việc tìm kiếm sự giảm căng thẳng thông qua các liệu pháp vật lý như thể thao hoặc <strong>mát-xa</strong> (<em>a massage</em>) có thể kém hiệu quả.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\">26. …than simply reviewing your <strong>workloads</strong>.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>workloads</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “…but to reassess <strong>workloads</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Điều quan trọng là <strong>đánh giá lại khối lượng công việc</strong> (<em>reassessing your workloads</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('41063fa5-9905-48f9-9737-8b682dcab084', 'db4b26a2-32b5-41f7-9abc-2994f428d7d0', 'checkbox', ' Questions 21–22', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>points did students most frequently make about their musical background before starting a music degree?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "They had already composed music.", "correct": false}, {"option": "They had several music qualifications.", "correct": false}, {"option": "They could play more than one instrument.", "correct": true}, {"option": "They had performed in public.", "correct": true}, {"option": "They had had piano lessons.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 3</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> So Gareth, we need to organize the findings from our survey on music students for the final presentation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> Yes Lona, I think we&#8217;ve got some very interesting results. Obviously we need to start by saying that we interviewed all the third-year students doing a music degree and state the objective of our research project, that is to find out about their attitudes to performing.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> And then we should talk about the students&#8217; musical backgrounds before coming to university. The most important points to make are that although most people have actually composed music during the course, that wasn&#8217;t the case when they arrived. And the other thing they had in common was the piano—well they&#8217;d had access to a piano at some point, but not all had studied it formally. I thought the most interesting finding was that before coming here, almost everyone was involved in a chamber orchestra or band or singing in a choir and <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"546\">(21/22) playing in front of live audiences (D: performed in public)</strong></span>, but varying enormously in size. Some had only played in tiny venues. I think it&#8217;s worth saying that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> OK. And as you might expect from people wanting to study music, they all had a degree of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">(21/22) proficiency in at least two instruments (C: play more than one instrument)</strong></span>, but in most cases one of the instruments was dominant.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> Right. We need to talk about attitudes to music practice. The most striking thing here is that even students who you&#8217;d expect to practice for hours every day until they get it perfect say it&#8217;s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"201\">(23/24) being terrified of failing that really makes them practice (C: motivated by fear)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> I know, I&#8217;m the same.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> Me too! It&#8217;s interesting what was said about practicing alone. Some people preferred that because they could focus more on their weak points, but that wasn&#8217;t a majority view. What most of them agree on is that there&#8217;s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"226\">(23/24) nothing more rewarding than mastering something that&#8217;s really hard to learn (E: enjoy the challenge of a difficult piece)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> That&#8217;s right. Okay, after that we should talk a bit about the pieces that students select for assessed performances. There wasn&#8217;t quite so much consensus on this, was there? A few people prefer to do pieces which are relatively unknown, while others choose the ones they think will show off their technical ability, but they were in the minority.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> Hmm. I think the first thing to say is that a high percentage said they would<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">(25/26) always try to learn their pieces by heart (C: play from memory)</strong></span></span> because it&#8217;s too easy to get lost if you&#8217;re trying to read and play when you&#8217;re nervous.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> Hmm okay. And quite a lot of them said <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">(25/26) it helps to listen to other people playing your chosen piece (A: hear others performing)</strong></span>, preferably recordings but even just other students.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> So finally, we need to look at the findings for students&#8217; attitudes to performing. We should point out that this includes informal and formal public performances as well as assessed ones.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> Yes, that&#8217;s important. I expected to find that performing solo would make students very nervous but in fact that isn&#8217;t the case. They do find it <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"151\">(27) hugely challenging to start with, but they appreciate the challenge and find it stimulating (B: difficult but enjoyable)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> Right. I was surprised by what students said about deciding which pieces to perform. I thought they&#8217;d all say this was easy. For me it&#8217;s always been quite straightforward: which pieces do I like best and which pieces can I play well? And my repertoire is quite limited anyway. But the most commonly cited answer was that <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"329\">(28) it took them ages to make their minds up (E: time-consuming)</strong></span>. I suppose it&#8217;s because there are so many factors involved—you need to consider your audience, the venue, the time available to learn the piece, especially if it&#8217;s complicated. You need to think about all these things and you can&#8217;t do that in a hurry.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> That&#8217;s true. Then there&#8217;s performing with musicians from a different genre, like a classical musician playing with a jazz group. That can really be fun, but <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"163\">(29) most of the music students had never even considered it (G: happens infrequently)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gareth:</strong> Right. For performing with musicians who play the same instrument, almost everyone put the same thing. Yes, they all said <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">(30) it was incredibly helpful (A: very beneficial)</strong></span> and not at all intimidating, which says a lot for the department&#8217;s ethos.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lona:</strong> Yes, that&#8217;s a good point. Okay, what I think we should sort out now is&#8230;</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('18a669b8-5789-4ab7-ac66-528a692afc8c', 'a2682f5a-008c-4b35-b48e-a0e5d7ae138d', 'fillup', ' Questions 1–7', '<p style="text-align: left;">Complete the notes below. Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answers.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>CHINESE SILK</strong></p>
<p><strong>Early Uses</strong></p>
<p><em>Clothing</em></p>
<p>– at first, silk only available to Chinese of high rank</p>
<p>– emperor wore {white} silk indoors</p>
<p><em>In industry</em></p>
<p>– silk items included parts of musical instruments, fishing strings and {paper}</p>
<p><em>Currency</em></p>
<p>– silk was used as payment of {taxes} as well as for wages and rewards</p>
<p>– silk replaced {gold} as a unit of value</p>
<p>– silk soon used as payment in {foreign} trade</p>
<p><strong>Evidence of silk trade</strong></p>
<p><em>1070 BC, Egypt:</em></p>
<p>– hair of a {mummy} contained silk</p>
<p><em>2nd century BC, Persia and Mesopotamia:</em></p>
<p>– gifts of silk were presented by Chinese ambassadors</p>
<p><em>1015 AD, north-west China:</em></p>
<p>– silk objects were hidden inside {caves}</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>1. Early Uses: Clothing – emperor wore white silk indoors.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>white</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “Within the palace, the emperor is believed to have worn a robe of <strong>white</strong> silk…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Hoàng đế mặc áo choàng lụa trắng khi ở bên trong cung điện.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>2. In industry – Silk items included parts of musical instruments, fishing strings and paper.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>paper</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “It was used in the production of musical instruments, as string for fishing, and even as the world’s first luxury <strong>paper</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Lụa được dùng làm giấy (paper), ngoài ra còn làm dây đàn và dây câu cá.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>3. Currency – silk was used as payment of taxes as well as for wages and rewards.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>taxes</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “Farmers paid their <strong>taxes</strong> in grain and silk, and silk was used to pay civil servants and to reward subjects for outstanding services.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nông dân dùng lụa để đóng thuế (taxes).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>4. Currency – silk replaced gold as a unit of value.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>gold</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “Values were calculated in lengths of silk as they had previously been calculated in weight of <strong>gold</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Giá trị được tính bằng lụa, thay thế cho đơn vị tính bằng vàng trước đó.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>5. Currency – silk soon used as payment in foreign trade.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>foreign</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “Before long, silk became a currency used in trade with <strong>foreign</strong> countries…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Lụa sớm trở thành đơn vị tiền tệ trong thương mại với các nước ngoài.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>6. Evidence of silk trade: 1070 BC, Egypt: hair of a mummy contained silk.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>mummy</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “An Egyptian <strong>mummy</strong> with a silk thread in her hair, dating from 1070 BC, has been discovered…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sợi tơ lụa được tìm thấy trong tóc của một xác ướp (mummy) Ai Cập.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>7. Evidence of silk trade: 1015 AD, north-west China: silk objects were hidden inside caves.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>caves</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…Buddhist monks… had sealed more than ten thousand manuscripts and silk paintings, silk banners and textiles in <strong>caves</strong> near Dunhuang…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các đồ vật bằng lụa và bản thảo đã được phong kín trong các hang động (caves).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0557dc94-c091-4d64-99b8-0ed3a95cf967', '633f7590-e44b-4545-8c87-b2be27277961', 'fillup', 'Questions 25–27', '<p data-path-to-node="9">Answer the questions below.</p>
<p id="p-rc_415c23e4826df562-519" data-path-to-node="10"><span class="citation-27866 citation-27867">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="7"><span class="citation-27866 citation-27867">NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</span></strong><span class="citation-27866 citation-27867 citation-end-27867"> from the text for each answer.</span></p>
<p id="p-rc_415c23e4826df562-520" data-path-to-node="11"><span class="citation-27864 citation-27865 citation-end-27865">Write your answers in boxes 25–27 on your answer sheet.</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span class="citation-27862 citation-27863">To</span><span class="citation-27861 citation-27862 citation-27863 citation-end-27863"> obtain a scholarship, what is the minimum course length? {20 | twenty weeks}</span></li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_415c23e4826df562-522" data-path-to-node="12,1,0"><span class="citation-27858 citation-27859 citation-27860 citation-end-27860">What do scholarship winners r</span><span class="citation-27858 citation-27859 citation-end-27859">eceive towards their airfar</span><span class="citation-27858 citation-end-27858">es if they live over 2,500 km from Sydney? {vouchers}</span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_415c23e4826df562-523" data-path-to-node="12,2,0"><span class="citation-27857 citation-end-27857">Who pays for dependent children to travel? {scholarship holder}</span></p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'short_answer', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. To obtain a scholarship, what is the minimum course length? — {20 weeks / twenty weeks}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…are <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"19\">not offered for courses of less than 20 weeks’</strong> duration.” (Đoạn 10)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Không cấp cho khóa dưới 20 tuần, nghĩa là tối thiểu phải đạt 20 tuần.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. What do scholarship winners receive towards their airfares if they live over 2,500 km from Sydney? — {airline vouchers / vouchers}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “If the distance exceeds this amount [2,500 km], you will be provided with <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">airline vouchers</strong>.” (Đoạn 12)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Who pays for dependent children to travel? — {scholarship holder / the scholarship holder}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Travel costs or support for <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">dependent children are at the scholarship holder’s expense</strong>.” (Đoạn 13)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “At someone’s expense” có nghĩa là người đó tự bỏ tiền túi ra trả.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c8965165-a7ab-4452-b352-8f3c30072a00', 'db4b26a2-32b5-41f7-9abc-2994f428d7d0', 'checkbox', 'Questions 23–24', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>points did students most frequently make about music practice?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "They prefer to practise alone.", "correct": false}, {"option": "They try to practise every day.", "correct": false}, {"option": "They are motivated to practise by fear.", "correct": true}, {"option": "They feel they don’t do enough practice.", "correct": false}, {"option": "They enjoy the challenge of a difficult piece.", "correct": true}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0c7535a7-9ab3-4769-a7eb-0be46f04b275', 'e7f7a56e-885d-4e62-9ccd-a7d546efc04b', 'fillup', 'Questions 28–30', '<p>Complete the summary <span class="citation-34915 citation-34916">below.</span></p>
<p><span class="citation-34913 citation-34914">Choose </span><strong><span class="citation-34913 citation-34914">ONE WORD ONLY</span></strong><span class="citation-34913 citation-34914 citation-end-34914"> from the text for each answer.</span></p>
<p><span class="citation-34911 citation-34912 citation-end-34912">Write your answers in boxes 28–30 on your answer sheet.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-path-to-node="4,0"><strong data-path-to-node="4,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Knepp Castle estate</span></strong></p>
<p><span class="citation-34904 citation-34905 citation-34906 citation-34907 citation-34908 citation-end-34908">About ten years ago, the decision was taken to rewild the farmland at Knepp Castle. Now t</span><span class="citation-34904 citation-34905 citation-34906 citation-34907">he {maize}</span><span class="citation-34904 citation-34905 citation-34906 citation-34907 citation-end-34907"> t</span><span class="citation-34904 citation-34905 citation-34906">hat used to be grown there has disappeared and the countryside is more like parts of {Africa}</span><span class="citation-34904 citation-34905 citation-34906 citation-end-34906"> . The hedges surrounding the fields have been allowed to expand and deer can be seen running among t</span><span class="citation-34904 citation-34905">he wild flowers. The estate hosts the largest number of {butterflies}</span><span class="citation-34904 citation-34905"> of a particular </span><span class="citation-34903 citation-34904 citation-34905 citation-end-34905">species in the whole country and bird numbers are incr</span><span class="citation-34903 citation-34904 citation-end-34904">easing. All these changes have happened remarkably quick</span><span class="citation-34903 citation-end-34903">ly.</span></p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. Now the {maize} that used to be grown there has disappeared…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Neat fields of <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">maize</strong> have been replaced with a landscape that resembles…” (Đoạn 1)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những cánh đồng ngô (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">maize</em>) từng được trồng ngăn nắp nay đã được thay thế bằng cảnh quan tự nhiên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. …and the countryside is more like parts of {Africa}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…resembles the typical grasslands of <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">Africa</strong>.” (Đoạn 1)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cảnh quan vùng nông thôn hiện tại được so sánh là giống với những vùng đồng cỏ đặc trưng của châu Phi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. The estate hosts the largest number of {butterflies} of a particular species…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “The estate boasts more of the unusual purple emperor <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">butterflies</strong> than anywhere else in Britain.” (Đoạn 1)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Largest number… in the whole country” tương ứng với cụm “more… than anywhere else in Britain”. Loài vật được nhắc đến ở đây là bướm (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"150\">butterflies</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2c4ab697-d029-49ff-8fc1-cb4bb4b6fa71', 'bbf91301-5bb1-4a15-8465-c0a0f209930a', 'matching', 'Questions 31–36', '', '<p><span class="citation-17243">Complete the summary using the list of phrases, </span><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="48"><span class="citation-17243">A–J</span></strong><span class="citation-17243 citation-end-17243">, below.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="124"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-17242">Write the correct letter, </span><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="86"><span class="citation-17242">A–J</span></strong><span class="citation-17242 citation-end-17242">, in boxes 31–36 on your answer sheet.</span></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-17241 citation-end-17241\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">What happens when people encounter misinformation?</span><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"126\"><!----></sup></span></strong></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p><span class=\"citation-17234 citation-17235 citation-17236 citation-17237 citation-17238 citation-17239 citation-17240 citation-end-17240\">Although people<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"127\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-17234 citation-17235 citation-17236 citation-17237 citation-17238 citation-17239\"> have {G frequent exposure}</span><span class=\"citation-17234 citation-17235 citation-17236 citation-17237 citation-17238 citation-17239\"> to misinformation, there is debate about precisely how and when we label something as true or untrue. The philosophers Descartes and Spinoza had {J different ideas}</span><span class=\"citation-17234 citation-17235 citation-17236 citation-17237 citation-17238 citation-17239 citation-end-17239\"> about how people engage with information. While Descartes believed that people accept or rej<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"128\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-17234 citation-17235 citation-17236 citation-17237 citation-17238\">ect information after considering whether it is true or not, Spinoza argued that people accepted </span><em data-path-to-node=\"11,1\" data-index-in-node=\"427\"><span class=\"citation-17234 citation-17235 citation-17236 citation-17237 citation-17238\">all</span></em><span class=\"citation-17234 citation-17235 citation-17236 citation-17237 citation-17238 citation-end-17238\"> information they encountered (and by default misinformation) and did not verify or reject <sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"129\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-17234 citation-17235 citation-17236 citation-17237\">it until afterwards. Moreover, Spinoza believed that a distinct {H mental operation}</span><span class=\"citation-17234 citation-17235 citation-17236 citation-17237\"> is involved in these stages. Recent research has provided {B additional evidence}</span><span class=\"citation-17234 citation-17235 citation-17236\"> for Spinoza’s theory and it would appear that people accept all encountered information as if it were true, even if this is for an extremely {E short period}</span><span class=\"citation-17234 citation-17235\">, and do not label the information as true or false until later. This is consistent </span><span class=\"citation-17232 citation-17233 citation-17234 citation-17235 citation-end-17235\">with the fact that the resources for scepticism and the resources for perceiving and encoding a<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"132\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-17232 citation-17233 citation-17234\">re in {C different locations}</span><span class=\"citation-17232 citation-17233 citation-17234 citation-end-17234\"> in th<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"133\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-17232 citation-17233 citation-end-17233\">e brain.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"134\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-17232 citation-end-17232\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"135\"><!----></sup></span></p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A constant conflict"}, {"optionText": "B additional evidence"}, {"optionText": "C different locations"}, {"optionText": "D experimental subjects"}, {"optionText": "E short period"}, {"optionText": "F extreme distrust"}, {"optionText": "G frequent exposure"}, {"optionText": "H mental operation"}, {"optionText": "I dubious reason"}, {"optionText": "J different ideas"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. G (frequent exposure) — {Although people have frequent exposure to misinformation}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Although it is <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">fairly routine</strong> for individuals to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">come across information that is false</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Fairly routine\" (khá thường xuyên/như cơm bữa) và \"come across\" (bắt gặp) đồng nghĩa với việc có sự tiếp xúc thường xuyên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">frequent exposure</strong>) với thông tin sai lệch.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. J (different ideas) — {Descartes and Spinoza had different ideas about how people engage with information}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"...a contrast between how... Descartes and... Spinoza described human information engagement, with <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">conflicting predictions</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Conflicting predictions\" (những dự đoán xung đột/trái ngược nhau) chính là việc họ có những ý tưởng/quan điểm khác nhau (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">different ideas</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. H (mental operation) — {a distinct mental operation is involved in these stages}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"...accept all encountered information... and then subsequently verify or reject it through a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">separate cognitive process</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Separate cognitive process\" (một quá trình nhận thức riêng biệt) tương ứng với cụm từ \"distinct mental operation\" (một hoạt động trí óc khác biệt).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. B (additional evidence) — {Recent research has provided additional evidence for Spinoza’s theory}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"In recent decades, <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">empirical evidence</strong> from the research teams of Erik Asp... has <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">supported Spinoza’s account</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc có các bằng chứng thực nghiệm (empirical evidence) ủng hộ (supported) học thuyết của Spinoza chính là việc cung cấp thêm bằng chứng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"150\">additional evidence</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. E (short period) — {even if this is for an extremely short period}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"...people appear to encode all new information as if it were true, <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">even if only momentarily</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Momentarily\" (chỉ trong khoảnh khắc) đồng nghĩa với một khoảng thời gian cực ngắn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">short period</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. C (different locations) — {are in different locations in the brain}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"...resources for skepticism physically <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">reside in a different part of the brain</strong> than the resources used in perceiving and encoding.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Reside in a different part of the brain\" (nằm ở một phần khác nhau của não bộ) khớp hoàn toàn với cụm \"different locations in the brain\".</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('493900f8-2e40-481b-bd89-86dd5f687bb2', 'db4b26a2-32b5-41f7-9abc-2994f428d7d0', 'checkbox', 'Questions 25–26', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>points were most frequently made by students about the pieces they select for assessed performances?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "They like to hear others performing the same pieces.", "correct": true}, {"option": "They like to choose little-known pieces.", "correct": false}, {"option": "They like to play pieces from memory.", "correct": true}, {"option": "They like their tutor to choose their pieces.", "correct": false}, {"option": "They like to choose technically demanding pieces.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2fbfc59a-08f7-42be-9238-87d6d27bf779', 'db4b26a2-32b5-41f7-9abc-2994f428d7d0', 'matching', 'Questions 27–30', NULL, '<p>Which comment did most students make about each of the following aspects of performance?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FOUR </strong>correct answers, <strong>A-G</strong>, next to questions <strong>27-30</strong>.</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Aspects of performance</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Performing solo {B This is difficult but enjoyable.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Deciding which pieces to perform {E This is time-consuming.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Performing with musicians from a different genre {G This happens infrequently.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Performing with musicians who play the same instrument {A This is very beneficial.}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A This is very beneficial."}, {"optionText": "B This is difficult but enjoyable."}, {"optionText": "C This can affect relationships."}, {"optionText": "D This makes them very nervous."}, {"optionText": "E This is time-consuming."}, {"optionText": "F This is easy."}, {"optionText": "G This happens infrequently."}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ed92f30e-c01f-4b26-b5c3-b220cf49dab7', 'e91fa672-f757-4df6-b10f-58605adc1d09', 'radio', 'Questions 11–16', '', '<p data-start="126" data-end="167"><strong data-start="126" data-end="167">Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</strong></p>
<p data-start="169" data-end="214"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Bidcaster Community Archaeology Project</span></strong></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A the castle owners"}, {"option_text": "B a national charity"}, {"option_text": "C the local council"}], "question": "Who was responsible for starting the community project?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A Heavy rain had removed some of the soil"}, {"option_text": "B The ground was dug up by wild rabbits"}, {"option_text": "C A person with a metal detector searched the area"}], "question": "How was the gold coin found?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A the lucky discovery of old records"}, {"option_text": "B the bases of several structures visible in the grass"}, {"option_text": "C the unusual stones found near the castle"}], "question": "What led the archaeologists to believe there was an ancient village on this site?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A everyday pottery"}, {"option_text": "B animal bones"}, {"option_text": "C pieces of jewellery"}], "question": "What are the team still hoping to find?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A the remains of a large palace"}, {"option_text": "B the outline of fields"}, {"option_text": "C a number of small huts"}], "question": "What was found on the other side of the river to the castle?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A prepare a display for a museum"}, {"option_text": "B take part in a television programme"}, {"option_text": "C start to organise school visits"}], "question": "What do the team plan to do after work ends this summer?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-section-id=\"suogjn\" data-start=\"57\" data-end=\"67\">PART 2</h3>\n<p data-start=\"69\" data-end=\"547\">Hello, I’m Hayden. I’m one of the archaeologists investigating the site here at Bidcaster. This is the third summer for this community project, and most of the people digging here are volunteers. I’m a full-time archaeologist for the town council, but I was asked to join the project by NHA, <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">a charity which sets up projects like this up and down the country. <strong data-start=\"540\" data-end=\"547\">Q11</strong></span> As you can see, we’re next to Bidcaster Castle, which is great because the owners let us use their facilities. </p>\n<p data-start=\"549\" data-end=\"983\">So, how did we get to where we are today? Many archaeology projects happen when an ancient object is found, and in our case, that object was a gold coin. Coins are often found by people using metal detectors to look for things buried in the ground – or coins are uncovered when wild animals like rabbits have been digging tunnels. Here, a walker found it on the ground <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">after a rainstorm washed away some of the earth and sand. <strong data-start=\"976\" data-end=\"983\">Q12</strong></span></p>\n<hr data-start=\"985\" data-end=\"988\">\n<p data-start=\"990\" data-end=\"1441\">When the story of the gold coin hit the news, Peter Swift, an amateur historian, contacted me to say he believed there had been a village on this site, centuries before the castle was built.<span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"> Just by chance, the team found some old maps and documents in our library <strong data-start=\"1434\" data-end=\"1441\">Q13</strong> </span>which showed five-hundred-year-old drawings of ruined buildings on the grassy area between the outer stone walls of the castle and the river. We knew then we were onto something. </p>\n<p data-start=\"1443\" data-end=\"1819\">Over the three summers the team has been here, we’ve found the remains of several buildings, and more broken pots than you can count! Normally you’d expect to <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">find brooches and other jewellery, but we’re still waiting to uncover any such items <strong data-start=\"1812\" data-end=\"1819\">Q14</strong>.</span> The people who once lived here were skilled at making tools from animal bones, as you’ll see when you visit the exhibition. </p>\n<p data-start=\"1821\" data-end=\"2141\">Besides the discovery of the village, we’ve also found evidence of human activity on the other side of the river – no other houses or huts so far, but <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">we can see the borders of an ancient field system <strong data-start=\"2134\" data-end=\"2141\">Q15</strong></span>. At one point we found a long wall and thought it was an ancient palace, but it turned out to be a modern wall. </p>\n<p data-start=\"2143\" data-end=\"2473\">This summer’s work will end soon, but we’ll be back next summer. In the meantime, we’re <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">putting on a series of guided tours for school groups <strong data-start=\"2466\" data-end=\"2473\">Q16</strong> </span>this autumn. Oh and, maybe you saw the TV documentary about our project. That suggested the objects we’ve found are going to the town’s museum, but we don’t know that for sure yet. </p>\n<hr data-start=\"2475\" data-end=\"2478\">\n<p data-start=\"2480\" data-end=\"2724\">When you enter the site, please make sure you keep to the paths at all times. There are a few other things – the highlights of the site, if you like – that I want to mention. Take a look at the map; our present location is marked at the bottom.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2726\" data-end=\"3129\">This year we’ve identified the foundations of an ancient bridge. And it’s really exciting today because a team of divers are in the river searching for lost objects. <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">To reach the bridge, take the main path ahead of you, go straight on and keep going till the path bends to the left. You’ll see a smaller track leading off to the right. Follow that to take you to the river, where the divers are. <strong data-start=\"3122\" data-end=\"3129\">Q17</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"3131\" data-end=\"3433\">You might be interested to <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">see the rubbish pit. This is very near the castle walls in the north-west corner of the site.<strong data-start=\"3426\" data-end=\"3433\">Q18</strong> </span>It actually dates to the time of the castle and not the ancient village. We found oyster shells and fish bones, and we assume they were thrown from the castle kitchen above. </p>\n<p data-start=\"3435\" data-end=\"3732\">One area we excavated in the first summer uncovered the site of a meeting hall. We knew it was an important building because it had two rows of post holes, deep enough to support a large roof. <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">It’s the largest structure in the central area of the site, next to the current excavation area. <strong data-start=\"3725\" data-end=\"3732\">Q19</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"3734\" data-end=\"4151\">Last year we discovered a fish pond in the ancient village. Normally these were beside a river. <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">The pond here is further away, but it’s possible the river has moved slightly. Anyway, to get there from here, you turn right at the first information board you come to, and follow the path into the trees. Before you come out of the trees, you’ll see it on your right.<strong data-start=\"4144\" data-end=\"4151\">Q20</strong></span> If you reach the river, you’ve gone too far. </p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('03e2dd69-f0ab-4b9e-a5f8-ecb7fa548b63', 'ee2dab1d-1d3f-4bfa-82f3-c036e621b93d', 'radio', 'Questions 11-13', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Most pre-adolescent children are capable of abstract thought."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": " Adolescents ‘limited skills’ with words may give a false impression of their ability."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Whether or not an adolescent is accepted by their age-group is an important clue to other aspects of their social adjustment"}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">11. FALSE</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 3</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…children’s thinking is dominated by a <strong>concrete example</strong>… their thinking is <strong>constrained to what is real and physical</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn 3 khẳng định tư duy của trẻ em bị giới hạn (<em>constrained</em>) vào những gì thực tế và hữu hình. Điều này mâu thuẫn trực tiếp với ý kiến cho rằng chúng có thể tư duy trừu tượng. Do đó đáp án là <strong>FALSE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">12. TRUE</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 6</strong></li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “As their <strong>conceptual development may outstrip their verbal development</strong>, adolescents may appear <strong>less competent than they really are</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn 6 giải thích rằng sự phát triển tư duy (<em>conceptual</em>) nhanh hơn khả năng ngôn ngữ (<em>verbal</em>), dẫn đến việc trẻ trông có vẻ kém cỏi hơn (<em>less competent</em>) năng lực thực sự. Điều này khớp với câu hỏi nên đáp án là <strong>TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">13. TRUE</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Vị trí:</strong> <strong>Đoạn 10</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “This degree to which an adolescent is able to make friends… is a <strong>major indicator of how well the adolescent will adjust in other areas</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn 10 khẳng định việc kết bạn là một <strong>chỉ số chính</strong> (<em>major indicator</em>) cho sự thích nghi tốt ở các mảng khác. Điều này khớp với nội dung câu hỏi nên đáp án là <strong>TRUE</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e5ef3ff4-fa53-42b3-9e2d-831b32f0ea7c', '155cd71b-f2ec-44fc-98b9-82d8cbd4374b', 'matching', 'Questions 14-19', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has six paragraphs, A-F.<br />
Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i New terminology reflecting changing attitudes to waste disposal"}, {"optionText": "ii Fundamental changes in behaviour in the past and future"}, {"optionText": "iii Ways of rewarding the public for recycling"}, {"optionText": "iv A surprising approach to waste disposal by several countries"}, {"optionText": "v Difficult choices for individuals and businesses"}, {"optionText": "vi Arguments against incineration from a country that uses it"}, {"optionText": "vii A number of justifications for the use of incineration"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Paragraph A: iv (A surprising approach to waste disposal by several countries)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Norway, however, appears to be burning its way through a sizable chunk of Europe’s municipal waste… Germany, Sweden, Belgium and the Netherlands all burn significant quantities…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thông thường, đốt rác bị coi là lựa chọn “lười biếng” và độc hại. Tuy nhiên, các quốc gia này lại sử dụng nó để sưởi ấm và tạo năng lượng, một cách tiếp cận gây bất ngờ so với quan điểm truyền thống.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Paragraph B: vii (A number of justifications for the use of incineration)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Filters and scrubbing mechanisms now capture harmful substances… incineration is the only way of preventing the long-term impacts of landfill… practical way to deal swiftly…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này đưa ra các lý do bào chữa/ủng hộ việc đốt rác: công nghệ lọc khí mới giúp giảm khí độc và đây là cách nhanh nhất để xử lý lượng rác khổng lồ thay vì chôn lấp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Paragraph C: vi (Arguments against incineration from a country that uses it)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Lars Haltbrekken, chairman of Friends of the Earth in Norway… ‘The problem in Norway… is that we have built too many waste-burning factories. So we’ve ended up importing waste…’”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Na Uy là nước sử dụng lò đốt rác, nhưng Lars Haltbrekken (người Na Uy) lại phản đối vì nó làm giảm động lực giảm thiểu và tái chế rác thải.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Paragraph D: i (New terminology reflecting changing attitudes to waste disposal)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “We used to call this the ‘cradle to grave’ life cycle; now, the talk is of ‘cradle to cradle’ and an even more comprehensive concept known as ‘zero waste’.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này giới thiệu các thuật ngữ mới như “cradle to cradle” và “zero waste” để phản ánh sự thay đổi trong cách con người nhìn nhận vòng đời sản phẩm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Paragraph E: v (Difficult choices for individuals and businesses)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “You can argue about composting that, or not buying it in the first place… that’s money the retailers don’t get… [Supermarkets] have to pay to dispose of a lot of food… but that cost is less to them than brand damage…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đề cập đến sự mâu thuẫn giữa việc cắt giảm lãng phí thực phẩm và lợi nhuận của nhà bán lẻ (siêu thị thà bỏ đồ thừa còn hơn để kệ trống gây ảnh hưởng thương hiệu).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Paragraph F: ii (Fundamental changes in behaviour in the past and future)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Nobody would have said there would be so much electronic waste. But recycling has grown, too… we need to look at whether it’s business that drives consumers or the other way around.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này nhìn lại sự thay đổi về tiêu dùng và tái chế từ những năm 1980 đến nay và định hướng thay đổi hành vi trong tương lai.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a24b33b3-dfcf-4311-889c-8a363e436c97', 'a5ed1950-3bcb-432a-a870-76f539f52ed6', 'fillup', 'Questions 27-30 ', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>It is known that the pronunciation of language changes over time. The changes include large-scale regularities known as {sound laws}. There are several possible causes for change. Firstly, there is the effect of one language on another. Secondly, there is the role of { fashion}. The speech of certain groups has prestige, and is imitated by others. It has also been suggested that some changes are introduced by  {children}, who are unable to imitate speech in an exact way. Finally, there is a factor referred to as the { principle of ease}, by which the effort necessary to produce words is reduced.</p>', '', 'short_answer', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. {sound laws}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Such regular changes are often called <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">sound laws</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài tóm tắt đề cập đến “large-scale regularities” (những quy luật diện rộng). Trong bài đọc, tác giả định nghĩa những thay đổi có hệ thống này (ví dụ: tất cả các âm [b] chuyển thành [p]) là các <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"206\">quy luật âm thanh</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. {fashion}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It is also possible that <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">fashion</strong> plays a part in the process of change. …one person imitates another, and people with the most prestige are most likely to be imitated…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngôn ngữ thay đổi do xu hướng xã hội. Con người có xu hướng bắt chước cách phát âm của những nhóm có địa vị cao (prestige). Tác giả gọi yếu tố dẫn dắt sự bắt chước này là <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"183\">thời trang/xu hướng</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. {children}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…the argument is that the imitation of <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">children</strong> is imperfect: they copy their parents’ speech, but never reproduce it exactly.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một nguyên nhân khác được đưa ra là do <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">trẻ em</strong>. Vì trẻ em không thể bắt chước chính xác (imperfect imitation/unable to imitate in an exact way) giọng nói của người lớn, những sai lệch này tích tụ dần dẫn đến sự thay đổi ngôn ngữ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. {principle of ease}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“One such force which is often invoked is the <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">principle of ease</strong>, or minimization of effort.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đây là cơ chế sinh học. Con người luôn muốn giảm thiểu nỗ lực (minimization of effort) khi nói. <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">Nguyên tắc dễ dàng</strong> giúp giải thích tại sao các âm khó phát âm thường bị biến đổi hoặc lược bỏ để việc giao tiếp trở nên trơn tru hơn.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5e7dd031-3119-4987-81b6-cb91e59f85fa', 'e7f7a56e-885d-4e62-9ccd-a7d546efc04b', 'matrix', 'Questions 31–36', '', '<p id="p-rc_43e24471eb447ed7-526" data-path-to-node="7"><span class="citation-34888 citation-34889 citation-34890 citation-34891 citation-34892 citation-34893 citation-34894 citation-end-34894">Match each stateme</span><span class="citation-34888 citation-34889 citation-34890 citation-34891 citation-34892 citation-34893">nt with the correct person, </span><strong><span class="citation-34888 citation-34889 citation-34890 citation-34891 citation-34892 citation-34893">A–G</span></strong><span class="citation-34888 citation-34889 citation-34890 citation-34891 citation-34892 citation-34893 citation-end-34893">.</span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="7"><span class="citation-34882 citation-34883 citation-34884 citation-34885 citation-34886 citation-34887">Write the correct letter, </span><strong><span class="citation-34882 citation-34883 citation-34884 citation-34885 citation-34886 citation-34887">A–G</span></strong><span class="citation-34882 citation-34883 citation-34884 citation-34885 citation-34886 citation-34887 citation-end-34887">, in boxes 31–36 on your answer sheet.</span></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"> </div>
<p> </p>
<p id="p-rc_43e24471eb447ed7-527" data-path-to-node="8,0,0"></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Some people are against rewilding as it reduces the amount of crops that could provide much needed nourishment.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "It may not be easy to get city residents to take part in rewilding.", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Rewilding does not necessarily lead to a landscape thickly covered in trees.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "It is acceptable to turn fields which do not yield many crops into natural spaces for people to enjoy.", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "The support of people living in the area is needed to make the authorities take rewilding seriously.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "There is evidence that people get used to the idea of rewilding with time.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Charlie Burrell", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Leo Linnartz", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "George Monbiot", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Frans Vera", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "David Balharry", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "Wouter Helmer", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "Elaine Gilligan", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. Some people are against rewilding as it reduces the amount of crops… — {A: Charlie Burrell}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Many criticise rewilding for <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">abandoning productive farmland</strong> when the world’s population is growing.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Burrell thuật lại quan điểm của những người chỉ trích rằng việc tái hoang dã là bỏ bê đất canh tác có năng suất (giảm lượng hoa màu/crops).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. It may not be easy to get city residents to take part in rewilding. — {G: Elaine Gilligan}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…doubts whether it is seen as important in <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">large urban areas like Birmingham</strong>.” (Đoạn 8)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Gilligan lo ngại về việc kết nối người dân ở các thành phố lớn (urban areas) với phong trào này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. Rewilding does not necessarily lead to a landscape thickly covered in trees. — {D: Frans Vera}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…proved that ‘natural’ grazing creates a <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">more dynamic landscape</strong>, a constantly changing pattern of <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">open glades and wooded groves</strong>.” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vera đã phá bỏ niềm tin cũ cho rằng tái hoang dã sẽ tạo ra rừng rậm dày đặc (<em data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">dense forest</em>). Thay vào đó, nó là một cảnh quan động có các khoảng trống.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. It is acceptable to turn fields which do not yield many crops into natural spaces… — {F: Wouter Helmer}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “They leave the <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">less profitable lands</strong> to become <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">adventure land</strong> for an increasingly urban population.” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Helmer cho rằng việc để những vùng đất ít lợi nhuận (yield many crops) trở thành khu vực trải nghiệm thiên nhiên cho người dân là một xu hướng tất yếu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. The support of people living in the area is needed to make the authorities take rewilding seriously. — {E: David Balharry}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…will only be championed by <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">policymakers and politicians</strong> when it is led by <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">local communities</strong>.” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Authorities” tương ứng với policymakers/politicians. Sự dẫn dắt của cộng đồng địa phương (local communities) là mấu chốt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. There is evidence that people get used to the idea of rewilding with time. — {B: Leo Linnartz}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…many Dutch objected to ‘nature development’ 30 years ago but rewilding principles are <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">now mainstream</strong>.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Linnartz nêu dẫn chứng tại Hà Lan: từ chỗ bị phản đối 30 năm trước, nay nó đã trở thành xu hướng chính (mainstream) — cho thấy mọi người đã dần quen và chấp nhận nó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('86910ab4-49e0-4ffb-bbea-0ec5d3b9e16e', 'e7f7a56e-885d-4e62-9ccd-a7d546efc04b', 'radio', 'Questions 37–40', '', '<p><span class="citation-34836">Choose the c</span><span class="citation-34835 citation-34836">orrect letter, </span><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="27"><span class="citation-34835 citation-34836">A, B, C</span></strong><span class="citation-34835 citation-34836"> or </span><strong data-path-to-node="12" data-index-in-node="38"><span class="citation-34835 citation-34836">D</span></strong><span class="citation-34835 citation-34836 citation-end-34836">.</span></p>
<p><span class="citation-34834 citation-end-34834">Choose the correct letter in boxes 37–40 on your answer sheet.</span></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A had clear financial reasons for rewilding his farm."}, {"option_text": "B is worried that his land now looks extremely untidy."}, {"option_text": "C has considerably increased the money he makes from his farm."}, {"option_text": "D was initially guided by other people who had let their land go wild."}], "question": "In the fifth paragraph, the writer points out that Burrell"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A They want to leave it a"}, {"option_text": "B Many want to take over running their families'' farms."}, {"option_text": "C They have developed new ways of interacting with it."}, {"option_text": "D Many are interested in building businesses on farmland."}], "question": "What does Helmer say about young people and the land?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A there are increasing problems with water pollution in cities."}, {"option_text": "B money needs to be invested to create more dams across rivers."}, {"option_text": "C modern agricultural methods mean rain washes away productive soil."}, {"option_text": "D more barriers are needed to prevent rivers flooding domestic homes."}], "question": "Ted Green is particularly concerned that"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A It will be very difficult to organise efficiently in large expanses of countryside."}, {"option_text": "B It may attract so much public interest that smaller projects get forgotten."}, {"option_text": "C It has caused problems for certain types of animals and insects in Britain."}, {"option_text": "D It may be a trend that will lose its popularity quite quickly."}], "question": "In the final paragraph, what point is made about rewilding?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. In the fifth paragraph, the writer points out that Burrell — {A} had clear financial reasons for rewilding his farm.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Knepp’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">unproductive soil</strong> meant Burrell could <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">not compete</strong> with globalised food production… Ecotourism there <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">makes as much profit</strong> as conventional farm did.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vì đất không hiệu quả nên Burrell không thể cạnh tranh về nông nghiệp, chuyển sang tái hoang dã và làm du lịch sinh thái là một quyết định thực tế vì lợi nhuận.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. What does Helmer say about young people and the land? — {C} They have developed new ways of interacting with it.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…becoming more relaxed with nature – it’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">hunting and gathering but hunting with a camera</strong> and gathering experiences.” (Đoạn 7)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thế hệ trẻ có mối quan hệ khác với thiên nhiên (không còn “chiến đấu” hàng ngày), họ tương tác bằng cách chụp ảnh và tìm kiếm trải nghiệm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Ted Green is particularly concerned that — {C} modern agricultural methods mean rain washes away productive soil.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…intensive farming can worsen flash flooding, and cause <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">fertile earth to be swept downriver</strong> and out to sea.” (Đoạn 9)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Canh tác thâm canh (intensive farming) làm lũ lụt tệ hơn và khiến đất màu mỡ (fertile earth) bị cuốn trôi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. In the final paragraph, what point is made about rewilding? — {B} It may attract so much public interest that smaller projects get forgotten.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…there’s a risk people will say, ‘Oh we don’t have to do any of <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">that old stuff</strong> [traditional protection of rare species on small nature reserves].’” (Đoạn cuối)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mối nguy là mọi người quá chú ý vào tái hoang dã mà bỏ qua việc bảo tồn truyền thống tại các khu bảo tồn nhỏ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1ea4a442-c248-4c39-b55b-a296ad2a9342', 'a5ed1950-3bcb-432a-a870-76f539f52ed6', 'radio', 'Questions 31-37', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information,<strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It is impossible to know how words used to be pronounced."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some languages appear to have changed more than others."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some changes in English were probably led by the middle classes."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Certain English sounds are difficult for all children to pronounce."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Scant is generally easier to pronounce than skamt."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The spelling of gnat is likely to change in the future."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The spelling of temporary no longer reflects its pronunciation."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. It is impossible to know how words used to be pronounced. -&gt; FALSE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> “These various kinds of evidence… can often give us a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">very good idea of the pronunciation of an earlier age</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định dù không thể chắc chắn tuyệt đối, nhưng các nguồn bằng chứng (cách đánh vần, từ mượn, ghi chép cổ) giúp chúng ta có một khái niệm “rất tốt” về cách phát âm xưa. Do đó, nói “không thể” là sai.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. Some languages appear to have changed more than others. -&gt; NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc thảo luận về <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">cách thức</em> (mechanisms) ngôn ngữ thay đổi, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">không hề so sánh</strong> tốc độ hoặc mức độ thay đổi giữa các ngôn ngữ khác nhau (ví dụ: tiếng Anh thay đổi nhiều hơn tiếng Nga hay không).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. Some changes in English were probably led by the middle classes. -&gt; TRUE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> “…probably carried elements of <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">middle-class pronunciation</strong> into upper-class speech.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết chỉ ra rằng sự gia tăng quyền lực và giàu có của tầng lớp trung lưu ở thế kỷ 17-18 đã mang các yếu tố phát âm của họ thâm nhập vào tầng lớp thượng lưu, dẫn đến sự thay đổi trong cách phát âm tiếng Anh được chấp nhận.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Certain English sounds are difficult for all children to pronounce. -&gt; NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> “the imitation of children is imperfect… never reproduce it exactly.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói trẻ em bắt chước “không hoàn hảo”, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">không nêu tên cụ thể</strong> bất kỳ âm tiết nào là “khó đối với tất cả trẻ em”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Scant is generally easier to pronounce than skamt. -&gt; TRUE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> “the word scant was once skamt… <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">Greater efficiency has hereby been achieved</strong>, because /n/ and /t/ are articulated in the same place…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Greater efficiency” (hiệu quả cao hơn) chính là “easier to pronounce” (dễ phát âm hơn). Việc phát âm /n/ và /t/ tại cùng một vị trí (đầu lưỡi chạm nướu) giúp tiết kiệm nỗ lực hơn là chuyển từ vị trí môi (/m/) sang nướu (/t/).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. The spelling of gnat is likely to change in the future. -&gt; NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến việc các âm câm (như [k] trong <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">knight</em>) ảnh hưởng đến cách phát âm, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">không có dự đoán</strong> nào về việc thay đổi cách đánh vần (spelling) của từ “gnat” trong tương lai.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. The spelling of temporary no longer reflects its pronunciation. -&gt; TRUE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> “…temporary, which in Britain is often pronounced as if it were <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">tempory</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khi người Anh phát âm là “tempory”, họ đã lược bỏ một âm tiết so với cách viết đầy đủ. Vì vậy, âm thanh phát ra không còn phản ánh (no longer reflects) chính xác tất cả các chữ cái có trong cách đánh vần “temporary”.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('327dabd2-34c9-461b-a63f-903e7d9a010f', '7751ed0c-8fd8-402d-b2fb-59fb94be2f8a', 'fillup', ' Questions 31–40', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p><em>Complete the notes below.</em></p>
<p><em>Write </em><strong><em>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</em></strong><em> for each answer.</em></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GASTROPODS (SNAILS AND SLUGS)</strong></p>
<p><strong>Evolution</strong></p>
<p>– minerals in the bodies of gastropods are like those in the {sea}</p>
<p>– fossils date back 500 million years</p>
<p><strong>Physical features</strong></p>
<p>– single, muscular foot</p>
<p>– radula (used for feeding)</p>
<p>– Shell (snails only)</p>
<p>– size: British shells range from 1.5-50 mm</p>
<p>– form: most shells coil to the {right}</p>
<p>– some shells have ribs, spines or {hair}</p>
<p>– they have various colours and patterns</p>
<p><strong>Feeding habits</strong></p>
<p>– mainly feed on rotting plants, fungi or algae</p>
<p>– some eat live animals, e.g. shield slugs eat {worms}</p>
<p><strong>Predators</strong></p>
<p>– birds, frogs, flies</p>
<p>– humans – snails were probably introduced to Britain as food in the {1ST Century}</p>
<p>– many gastropods have particular types of {defences|defenses} itself slippery …, e.g. glutinous snail makes</p>
<p><strong>Habitats</strong></p>
<p>– gastropods prefer dampness and shade</p>
<p>– {dry} conditions are worst</p>
<p>– biggest variety is found in old, natural habitats, e.g. {forests} and meadowland</p>
<p>– highly specialized species live in unusual habitats, e.g. blind snail lives entirely below the {ground}</p>
<p>– good indicators of the quality of the {environment}</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h2 data-path-to-node=\"2\">PART 4</h2>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Good morning everyone. In this module, we&#8217;ve been looking at various field survey methods and now I&#8217;m going to give you a brief introduction to the specific organism that we&#8217;ll be focusing on during our first field trip, and that&#8217;s the gastropod.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">Gastropods are invertebrates—their organisms without a backbone—and they&#8217;re more commonly known as snails, or if they haven&#8217;t got a shell, slugs. Now in terms of their evolution, gastropods go back a long way. As with other primitive animals, the minerals in their body fluids are very similar to the mineral composition of the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"328\">(31) sea</strong></span>, indicating that they began life there; and their fossilized remains have been found in rocks dating back at least 500 million years.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Looking at the physical features of the gastropods, well, they all have one muscular foot for swimming or walking. This foot is lubricated with mucus, and it&#8217;s this that leaves the sticky trail that you see behind snails and slugs. They also have an organ called a radula, which they use for feeding. Then of course the snails, though not the slugs, have a shell. In terms of their dimensions, snail shells in Britain range from the dwarf snail, which is 1.5 millimeters long, to the Roman snail, whose shell can be as big as 50 millimeters.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">As well as size variations, you get a lot of differences in the form of snail shells. For example, the majority coil to the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">(32) right</strong></span>, but there are a few that coil to the left. Then some shells, for instance the plated snail, have regularly spaced ribs, while the prickly snail has prominent spines. There are even a number of species with <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"342\">(33) hair</strong></span> on their shells. Colours on the shells also vary as do patterns, so appearances are really varied.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Okay, let&#8217;s turn now to feeding habits. Most of you who are gardeners will know to your cost that some gastropods eat healthy plants, but you may not realize that these are the minority. Most species feed on rotting plants, or they eat fungi and algae. Some species eat dead animals, and there are some that are actually carnivorous—they prey on live animals. For example, the shield slug feeds on <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"398\">(34) worms</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">And apart from their own feeding habits, I should point out that gastropods themselves have plenty of predators. Birds and frogs are the main ones, but there&#8217;s even an entire family of flies that have specialized in preying on gastropods. And of course last but not least, I should mention human predators. It was the Romans who probably first introduced edible snails into Britain during the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"393\">(35) 1st century</strong></span>, and they are still eaten today. In fact, the collection of wild snails for cooking has caused local extinctions of one species, which is also under threat internationally.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">So there are lots of predators, but to protect themselves, gastropods have often developed special <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">(36) defences</strong></span>. I&#8217;ll just give you one example: the glutinous snail avoids predators by folding its mantle over its shell and turning itself into a very slippery blob of jelly.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">Well turning now to gastropod habitats. Most species like dampness and shade. In general, both very hot and very cold weather is bad for gastropods, but <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"153\">(37) dry</strong></span> conditions are the least favourable. Snails cope with this by withdrawing into their shells, and often they form a thick film of mucus over the mouth of their shell to minimize loss of water.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Habitats with a long stable history tend to support the biggest range of gastropod species. So for instance, long-established <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">(38) forests</strong></span> usually support more species than newer plantations of trees, and old natural meadowland is much better than land which has recently been farmed. And there is a small number of highly specialized species that live in unusual habitats. For instance, the blind snail spends its whole life buried under the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"443\">(39) ground</strong></span>. It&#8217;s been reported living at depths of 2 meters and particularly likes the cavities in old buried bones apparently, but species like these are exceptional.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">But wherever they live, gastropods are often sensitive to pollution and they don&#8217;t thrive in areas contaminated by agrochemicals. This means that they are a reliable indication of how healthy our <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #fbeeb8;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"196\">(40) environment</strong></span> is. Now at this point I&#8217;d like to consider habitat management in relation&#8230;</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8c0fe5c6-7ba2-442d-9cf1-6c72728460c5', '22bf7b2d-7bb8-4bb9-94b2-53ae26e05bb5', 'fillup', 'Question 1-10', '<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER </strong>for each answer.</p>
<p data-section-id="cxwu64" data-start="212" data-end="247"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-start="216" data-end="247">Hinchingbrooke Country Park</strong></span></p>
<p><strong data-start="249" data-end="261">The park</strong><br data-start="261" data-end="264">Area: {69} hectares<br data-start="291" data-end="294">Habitats: wetland, grassland and woodland<br data-start="335" data-end="338">Wetland: lakes, ponds and a {stream}<br data-start="378" data-end="381">Wildlife includes birds, insects and animals</p>
<p data-section-id="2x48h5" data-start="434" data-end="488"><strong data-start="438" data-end="488">Subjects studied in educational visits include</strong></p>
<p>Science: children look at {data} about plants, etc.<br data-start="547" data-end="550">Geography: includes learning to use a {map} and compass<br data-start="612" data-end="615">History: changes in land use<br data-start="643" data-end="646">Leisure and tourism: mostly concentrates on the park’s {visitors}<br data-start="713" data-end="716">Music: children make {sounds} with natural materials, and experiment with rhythm and speed</p>
<p data-section-id="ipxxp2" data-start="819" data-end="865"><strong data-start="823" data-end="865">Benefits of outdoor educational visits</strong></p>
<p>They give children a feeling of {freedom} that they may not have elsewhere.<br data-start="945" data-end="948">Children learn new {skills} and gain self-confidence.</p>
<p data-section-id="1vvjbtr" data-start="1014" data-end="1038"><strong data-start="1018" data-end="1038">Practical issues</strong></p>
<p>Cost per child: £ {4.95}<br data-start="1070" data-end="1073">Adults, such as {leaders}, free</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"213\"><strong data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"128\">SALLY:</strong> Good morning. Hinchingbrooke Country Park, Sally speaking. I’m one of the rangers.</p>\n<p data-start=\"215\" data-end=\"387\"><strong data-start=\"215\" data-end=\"224\">JOHN:</strong> Oh hello. My name’s John Chapman, and I’m a teaching assistant at a local primary school. I’ve been asked to arrange a visit to the park for two of our classes.</p>\n<p data-start=\"389\" data-end=\"434\"><strong data-start=\"389\" data-end=\"399\">SALLY:</strong> OK. What would you like to know?</p>\n<p data-start=\"436\" data-end=\"544\"><strong data-start=\"436\" data-end=\"445\">JOHN:</strong> Well, I’m new to this area, so perhaps you could tell me something about the park first, please.</p>\n<p data-start=\"546\" data-end=\"800\"><strong data-start=\"546\" data-end=\"556\">SALLY:</strong> Of course. Altogether the park covers 170 acres, that’s <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(1) 69</strong></span> hectares. There are three main types of habitat: wetland, grassland and woodland. The woods are well established and varied, with an oak plantation, and other areas of mixed species.</p>\n<p data-start=\"802\" data-end=\"820\"><strong data-start=\"802\" data-end=\"811\">JOHN:</strong> Right.</p>\n<p data-start=\"822\" data-end=\"1119\"><strong data-start=\"822\" data-end=\"832\">SALLY:</strong> The wetland is quite varied, too. The original farmland was dug up around 40 years ago to extract gravel. Once this work was completed, the gravel pits filled with water, forming the two large lakes. There are also several smaller ones, ponds and a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(2) </strong><strong>stream</strong></span> that flows through the park.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1121\" data-end=\"1216\"><strong data-start=\"1121\" data-end=\"1130\">JOHN:</strong> OK, so I suppose with these different habitats there’s quite a variety of wildlife.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1218\" data-end=\"1340\"><strong data-start=\"1218\" data-end=\"1228\">SALLY:</strong> There certainly is – a lot of different species of birds and insects, and also animals like deer and rabbits.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1342\" data-end=\"1422\"><strong data-start=\"1342\" data-end=\"1351\">JOHN:</strong> And I understand you organise educational visits for school parties.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1424\" data-end=\"1526\"><strong data-start=\"1424\" data-end=\"1434\">SALLY:</strong> That’s right. We can organise a wide range of activities and adapt them to suit all ages.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1528\" data-end=\"1588\"><strong data-start=\"1528\" data-end=\"1537\">JOHN:</strong> Can you give me some examples of the activities?</p>\n<p data-start=\"1590\" data-end=\"1767\"><strong data-start=\"1590\" data-end=\"1600\">SALLY:</strong> Well, one focus is on science, where we help children to discover and study plants, trees and insects. They also collect and analyse<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (3) data </strong></span>about the things they see.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1769\" data-end=\"1786\"><strong data-start=\"1769\" data-end=\"1778\">JOHN:</strong> Uhuh.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1788\" data-end=\"1948\"><strong data-start=\"1788\" data-end=\"1798\">SALLY:</strong> Another focus is on geography. The park is a great environment to learn and practise reading a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(4) map</strong></span> and using a compass to navigate around the park.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1950\" data-end=\"2004\"><strong data-start=\"1950\" data-end=\"1959\">JOHN:</strong> Do you do anything connected with history?</p>\n<p data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2150\"><strong data-start=\"2006\" data-end=\"2016\">SALLY:</strong> Yes, we do. For instance, the children can explore how the use of the land has changed over time. Then there’s leisure and tourism.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2152\" data-end=\"2211\"><strong data-start=\"2152\" data-end=\"2161\">JOHN:</strong> That focuses on your <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(5) visitors</span></strong>, I would imagine.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2213\" data-end=\"2483\"><strong data-start=\"2213\" data-end=\"2223\">SALLY:</strong> Yes, mostly. The children find out about them, their requirements, the problems they may cause and how we manage these. And another subject we cover is music: here the children experiment with natural materials to create <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(6) sounds</strong></span> and explore rhythm and tempo.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2485\" data-end=\"2514\"><strong data-start=\"2485\" data-end=\"2494\">JOHN:</strong> That must be fun!</p>\n<p data-start=\"2516\" data-end=\"2559\"><strong data-start=\"2516\" data-end=\"2526\">SALLY:</strong> Most children really enjoy it.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2561\" data-end=\"2740\"><strong data-start=\"2561\" data-end=\"2571\">SALLY:</strong> And of course, all the activities are educational, too. Learning outside the classroom encourages children to be creative, and to explore and discover for themselves.</p>\n<p data-start=\"116\" data-end=\"223\"><strong data-start=\"116\" data-end=\"125\">JOHN:</strong> I would imagine they get a sense of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(7) freedom</strong></span> that might not be a normal part of their lives.</p>\n<p data-start=\"225\" data-end=\"418\"><strong data-start=\"225\" data-end=\"235\">SALLY:</strong> That’s right. And very often the children discover that they can do things they didn’t know they could do, and they develop new<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (8) skills</strong></span>. This gives them greater self-confidence.</p>\n<p data-start=\"420\" data-end=\"586\"><strong data-start=\"420\" data-end=\"429\">JOHN:</strong> It sounds great. So, what about the practical side of it? How much does it cost for a full-day visit? We would expect to bring between 30 and 40 children.</p>\n<p data-start=\"588\" data-end=\"865\"><strong data-start=\"588\" data-end=\"598\">SALLY:</strong> If there are over 30, it costs <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(9) £4.95</span></strong> for each child who attends on the day. We invoice you afterwards, so you don’t pay for children who can’t come because of sickness, for example. There’s no charge for <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(10) leaders</span></strong> and other adults – as many as you want to bring.</p>\n<p data-start=\"867\" data-end=\"1037\"><strong data-start=\"867\" data-end=\"876\">JOHN:</strong> That sounds very fair. Well, thanks for all the information. I’ll need to discuss it with my colleagues, and I hope to get back to you soon to make a booking.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1039\" data-end=\"1100\"><strong data-start=\"1039\" data-end=\"1049\">SALLY:</strong> We’ll look forward to hearing from you. Goodbye.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1102\" data-end=\"1137\"><strong data-start=\"1102\" data-end=\"1111\">JOHN:</strong> Goodbye, and thank you.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('81a52fe3-bdba-457f-b5ff-826e27510d4f', 'a5ed1950-3bcb-432a-a870-76f539f52ed6', 'matching', 'Questions 38-40', '', '<p>Look at the following sentences and the list of statements below.</p>
<p>Match each statement with the correct sentence, A-D.</p>', 'matching_name', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "large-scale change"}, {"optionText": "influence of one language on another"}, {"optionText": "minimisation of effort"}, {"optionText": "imitation of prestigious group"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "The b sound changing to a p sound at the end of words", "correctAnswer": "A"}, {"questionPart": "The melodic pronunciation of Welsh English", "correctAnswer": "B"}, {"questionPart": "The disappearance of the t sound in Christmas", "correctAnswer": "C"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. The b sound changing to a p sound at the end of words -&gt; A (large-scale change)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> “…all the [b] consonants in a certain position (for example at the end of a word) may change into [p] consonants. Such <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">regular changes</strong> are often called <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"174\">sound laws</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc thay đổi từ âm [b] sang [p] trên toàn bộ các từ có vị trí tương tự là một ví dụ về <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">quy luật âm thanh (sound laws)</strong>. Đặc điểm cốt lõi của quy luật này là sự thay đổi diễn ra trên diện rộng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"205\">large-scale</strong>) và có tính hệ thống trong một ngôn ngữ ở một giai đoạn nhất định.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. The melodic pronunciation of Welsh English -&gt; B (influence of one language on another)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Dựa trên kiến thức ngôn ngữ học trong bài):</strong> Bài đọc đề cập đến việc “the effect of one language on another” (sự ảnh hưởng của ngôn ngữ này lên ngôn ngữ khác) là một nguyên nhân gây biến đổi.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cách phát âm có ngữ điệu (melodic) của tiếng Anh giọng Wales (Welsh English) là kết quả trực tiếp từ sự ảnh hưởng của tiếng Wales (tiếng mẹ đẻ) lên tiếng Anh. Đây là minh chứng cho việc các đặc điểm ngữ âm của một ngôn ngữ thâm nhập và làm thay đổi một ngôn ngữ khác khi chúng tiếp xúc với nhau.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. The disappearance of the t sound in Christmas -&gt; C (minimisation of effort)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E &amp; F):</strong> “…the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">principle of ease</strong>, or <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">minimisation of effort</strong>. …At one time there was a [t] in words like castle and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">Christmas</strong>… Consonant-clusters are often simplified.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc lược bỏ âm [t] trong từ <em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">Christmas</em> giúp cụm phụ âm trở nên đơn giản hơn. Điều này giúp người nói phát âm từ đó trôi chảy và tốn ít công sức hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">minimisation of effort</strong>). Đây là cơ chế tự nhiên của ngôn ngữ nhằm đạt được sự hiệu quả tối đa trong giao tiếp.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a3425c8f-869c-4e59-bd2f-4850de7f4bce', '293151fe-9c91-4259-a746-2b999c02deb4', 'radio', 'Questions 1–6', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Applicants to the department must have previously studied art history."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Students can choose two optional courses instead of the Theory and Methods course."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The course organisers had more problems collecting art objects from some historical periods than others."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Theory and Methods course focuses on the way art is made and perceived"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Students will be able to do any of the optional courses that are listed."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Students may be able to take an unlisted course if they get the appropriate approval."}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"5\">1. Applicants to the department must have previously studied art history.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (General Information) “We welcome applicants from a broad range of backgrounds and <strong>do not require students to have a first degree in art history</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khóa học không yêu cầu sinh viên phải có bằng cấp đầu tiên về lịch sử nghệ thuật, mâu thuẫn với nhận định rằng họ <em>phải</em> (<em>must</em>) học trước đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"7\">2. Students can choose two optional courses instead of the Theory and Methods course.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (General Information) “In addition to a <strong>compulsory course on Theory and Methods</strong>, students take <strong>two one-term optional courses</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khóa học Lý thuyết và Phương pháp (<em>Theory and Methods</em>) là <strong>bắt buộc</strong> (<em>compulsory</em>). Sinh viên phải học khóa này <em>và</em> hai khóa tự chọn, không phải thay thế khóa bắt buộc bằng hai khóa tự chọn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"9\">3. The course organisers had more problems collecting art objects from some historical periods than others.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (General Information) “Images and objects produced in many contexts – ranging from the scientific to the popular – have been brought together to show how visual styles at different periods and in different places can be understood…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói rằng các đối tượng nghệ thuật đã được thu thập từ nhiều bối cảnh và thời kỳ khác nhau, nhưng <strong>không có thông tin</strong> nào nói về <strong>vấn đề</strong> (<em>problems</em>) hay khó khăn trong việc thu thập từ các thời kỳ lịch sử.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"11\">4. The Theory and Methods course focuses on the way art is made and perceived.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Theory and Methods) “The course is organised around a series of issues that relate to the <strong>production of art and people’s responses to it</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> “Sản xuất nghệ thuật” (<em>production of art</em>) tương đương với cách nghệ thuật được tạo ra (<em>is made</em>), và “phản ứng của mọi người” (<em>people’s responses</em>) tương đương với cách nghệ thuật được cảm nhận (<em>is perceived</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"13\">5. Students will be able to do any of the optional courses that are listed.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Choosing Courses) “The optional courses listed below are <strong>not available every year</strong> and prospective students are advised to check on the availability of specific courses.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các khóa học không có sẵn hàng năm (<em>not available every year</em>), và có thể có <strong>hạn chế</strong> (<em>restrictions</em>) trong việc kết hợp, mâu thuẫn với việc sinh viên có thể học <strong>bất kỳ</strong> (<em>any</em>) khóa học nào.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"15\">6. Students may be able to take an unlisted course if they get the appropriate approval.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Choosing Courses) “Students wishing to take a course that <strong>does not appear in the list</strong> but is offered by the Faculty of History will need to get <strong>permission from the relevant Course Tutor</strong>. An application should then be made by the candidate’s supervisor.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Khóa học không có trong danh sách (<em>unlisted course</em>) có thể được theo học nếu sinh viên nhận được <strong>sự cho phép</strong> (<em>permission/appropriate approval</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5c8887c4-efeb-4910-97d5-c0628435c70f', 'd141a56e-3f93-4058-9d43-cf0a4a985df7', 'radio', 'Questions 11–15', '', '<p data-start="98" data-end="135">Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</p>
<p data-start="137" data-end="172"><strong data-start="137" data-end="172">Stanthorpe Twinning Association</strong></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A going to a theme park."}, {"option_text": "B experiencing a river trip."}, {"option_text": "C visiting a cheese factory."}], "question": "During the visit to Malatte, in France, members especially enjoyed"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A A tree will be planted."}, {"option_text": "B A garden seat will be bought."}, {"option_text": "C A footbridge will be built."}], "question": "What will happen in Stanthorpe to mark the 25th anniversary of the Twinning Association?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A the film show"}, {"option_text": "B the pancake evening"}, {"option_text": "C the cookery demonstration"}], "question": "Which event raised most funds this year?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A take them for a walk round the town."}, {"option_text": "B go to a local restaurant."}, {"option_text": "C have a meal at home."}], "question": "For the first evening with the French visitors host families are advised to"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A listen to a concert."}, {"option_text": "B watch a match."}, {"option_text": "C take part in a competition."}], "question": "On Saturday evening there will be the chance to"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"114\" data-end=\"374\">It’s great to see so many members of the Twinning Association here tonight. Since the twinning link between our two towns, Stanthorpe here in England and Malatte in France, was established, the relationship between the towns has gone from strength to strength.</p>\n<p data-start=\"376\" data-end=\"734\">Last month, 25 members of the association from Stanthorpe spent a week in Malatte. Our hosts had arranged a great programme. We learned how cheese is produced in the region and had the chance to taste local products. The theme park trip had to be cancelled, but we all had a great time on <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(11) the final boat trip down the river – that was the real highlight.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"736\" data-end=\"1118\">This is a special year for the Association because it’s 25 years since we were founded. In Malatte, they’re planning to mark this by building a footbridge in the municipal park. We’ve been discussing what to do here and <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(12) </strong></span><strong data-start=\"956\" data-end=\"1019\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">we’ve decided to plant a poplar tree in the museum gardens</span>.</strong> We considered buying a garden seat to put there, but the authorities weren’t happy with that idea.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1120\" data-end=\"1458\">In terms of fundraising to support our activities, we’ve done very well. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(13) </strong></span><strong data-start=\"1193\" data-end=\"1259\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">Our pancake evening was well attended and made record profits</span>.</strong> And everyone enjoyed the demonstration of French cookery, which was nearly as successful. Numbers for our film show were limited because of the venue so we’re looking for somewhere bigger next year.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1460\" data-end=\"1944\">We’re looking forward to welcoming our French visitors here next week, and I know that many of you here will be hosting individuals or families. The coach from France will arrive at 5 pm on Friday. Don’t try to do too much that first evening as they’ll be tired, so <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(14) </span></strong><strong data-start=\"1726\" data-end=\"1788\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">have dinner in the house or garden rather than eating out</span>.</strong> The weather looks as if it’ll be OK so you might like to plan a barbecue. Then the next morning’s market day in town, and that’s always a good place to go.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1946\" data-end=\"2105\">On Saturday evening, we’ll all meet up at the football club, where once again<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (15) we’ll have Toby Sharp and his band performing English and Scottish country songs.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"2107\" data-end=\"2579\">Now on Sunday, we’ll be taking our visitors to Farley House. You may not all be familiar with it, so here’s a map to help you. You can see the car park at the bottom of the map. There’s an excellent farm shop in the grounds where our visitors can buy local produce – it’s <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(16) </span></strong><strong data-start=\"2379\" data-end=\"2443\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">in the old stables, which is the first building you come to</span>.</strong> They’re built round a courtyard, and the shop’s <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">in the far corner on the left.</span></strong> There’s also a small café on the right as you go in.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2604\" data-end=\"2825\">I know that one or two of our visitors may not be all that mobile. The main entrance to the house has a lot of steps so you might want to use the disabled entry. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(17) This is on the far side of the house from the car park.</span></strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2827\" data-end=\"3033\">Children will probably be most interested in the adventure playground. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(18) That’s at the northern end of the larger lake, in a bend on the path that leads to the lake. </span></strong>There’s lots for children to do there.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3035\" data-end=\"3296\">There are a number of lovely gardens near the house. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(19) The kitchen gardens are rectangular and surrounded by a wall. They’re to the north-east of the house, quite near the smaller lake.</strong></span> They’re still in use and have a great collection of fruit and vegetables.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3298\" data-end=\"3637\">The Temple of the Four Winds is a bit more of a walk – but it’s worth it. Take the path from the car park and go past the western side of the stables and the house. Then<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (20) when the path forks, take the right-hand path. Go up there with the woods on your left and the temple is right at the end. There are great views over the whole area.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"3639\" data-end=\"3654\">Ok, so that’s …</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dd1849d5-7c03-4e1a-8921-dd225a08b0e5', 'a09725c8-dc9c-44a2-aa7a-484b2bd3c423', 'matching', 'Questions 27–30', NULL, '<p>Look at the following people (Questions 27-30) and the list of claims below.</p>
<p>Match each person with the correct claim, A-G.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. People overlook changes that happen during eye movements."}, {"optionText": "B. At times, we fail to notice something because we choose to deceive ourselves."}, {"optionText": "C. Retaining every image and memory would hinder our ability to function effectively."}, {"optionText": "D. Sometimes, people overlook the significance of a crucial figure in a scene."}, {"optionText": "E. We misunderstand what we see because we rely on our imagination."}, {"optionText": "F. We don''t have complete control over what captures our attention."}, {"optionText": "G. Imagining a scene and physically being there impact our visual processes in similar ways."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Daniel Dennett", "correctAnswer": "C. Retaining every image and memory would hinder our ability to function effectively.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "John Grimes", "correctAnswer": "A. People overlook changes that happen during eye movements.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Stephen Kosslyn", "correctAnswer": "G. Imagining a scene and physically being there impact our visual processes in similar ways.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Kevin O''Regan", "correctAnswer": "F. We don''t have complete control over what captures our attention.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"4\">Câu 27: Daniel Dennett</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">C</strong> (Việc lưu trữ mọi hình ảnh và ký ức sẽ cản trở khả năng hoạt động hiệu quả của chúng ta).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…philosopher Daniel Dennett argued that our brains only store a few key details about the world, which is why we can function effectively.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dennett cho rằng não bộ chỉ lưu trữ những chi tiết then chốt thay vì mọi chi tiết hình ảnh để tiết kiệm tài nguyên nhận thức, giúp con người hoạt động hiệu quả hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"6\">Câu 28: John Grimes</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">A</strong> (Mọi người bỏ qua những thay đổi xảy ra trong quá trình cử động mắt).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…John Grimes… showed that people who were presented with computer-generated images… failed to notice changes made while their eyes were, for example, scanning the scene or blinking.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu của Grimes tập trung vào việc con người không nhận ra sự thay đổi khi mắt đang quét (scanning) hoặc chớp (blinking).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"8\">Câu 29: Stephen Kosslyn</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">G</strong> (Việc tưởng tượng một cảnh và thực tế có mặt ở đó tác động đến quá trình thị giác theo cách tương tự).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…Stephen Kosslyn… demonstrated that imagining a scene activates parts of the visual cortex similarly to actually seeing it.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Kosslyn chứng minh rằng việc tưởng tượng kích hoạt vỏ não thị giác tương tự như khi nhìn thật, ủng hộ giả thuyết não bộ tự lấp đầy các khoảng trống thông tin.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"10\">Câu 30: Kevin O’Regan</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">F</strong> (Chúng ta không có quyền kiểm soát hoàn toàn đối với những gì thu hút sự chú ý của mình).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“According to O’Regan, our sense of controlling what we see is also an illusion… our change detection mechanisms automatically drag our attention to various stimuli.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> O’Regan (cùng với sự ủng hộ của Susan Blackmore) tin rằng việc ta nghĩ mình kiểm soát cái nhìn là ảo tưởng; thực tế, các cơ chế tự động sẽ kéo sự chú ý của ta về phía các kích thích.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6d986d83-5ef2-4916-b649-8b0659be8569', 'd141a56e-3f93-4058-9d43-cf0a4a985df7', 'matrix', 'Questions 16–20', '', '<p data-start="99" data-end="121">Label the map below.</p>
<p data-start="123" data-end="182">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="149" data-end="156">A–H</strong>, next to Questions 16–20.</p>
<p data-start="123" data-end="182"><img src="data:image/png;base64," width="500" height="422" loading="lazy"></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Farm shop", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "Disabled entry", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Adventure playground ", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Kitchen gardens", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "The Temple of the Four Winds", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f50a7306-ea6d-4c53-8920-a567cc6ce435', 'a09725c8-dc9c-44a2-aa7a-484b2bd3c423', 'radio', 'Questions 31–35', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "One expert expressed regret for having underemphasized his argument in a publication."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "We overlook insignificant items that come into our view."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Our eyes are only at risk of being deceived when they are in motion."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Research into cognitive errors might potentially save lives."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The aging process increases the need to fill in gaps in our visual perception."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"14\">Câu 31: Một chuyên gia bày tỏ sự hối tiếc vì đã nhấn mạnh quá ít lập luận của mình trong một ấn phẩm.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…Dennett was pleased: ‘In hindsight, I wish I had been bolder, as the effects are more pronounced than I originally claimed.’”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “wish I had been bolder” (ước gì đã táo bạo hơn) thể hiện sự hối tiếc vì đã đưa ra khẳng định nhẹ nhàng hơn thực tế trong ấn phẩm trước đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"16\">Câu 32: Chúng ta bỏ qua những mục không quan trọng lọt vào tầm mắt.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…we tend to ignore elements in our visual field that seem unimportant, such as a repeated word or line in a text.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết xác nhận con người có xu hướng phớt lờ các yếu tố “unimportant” (không quan trọng) trong thị trường của mình.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"18\">Câu 33: Mắt chúng ta chỉ có nguy cơ bị lừa khi chúng đang chuyển động.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Subsequently, it was discovered that our eyes don’t even need to be moving to be deceived.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định mắt “không cần phải chuyển động” vẫn có thể bị đánh lừa qua các thí nghiệm với hình ảnh biến mất và xuất hiện lại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"20\">Câu 34: Nghiên cứu về các lỗi nhận thức có khả năng cứu sống con người.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It’s more than just academic interest that has spurred research into these cognitive errors.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản đề cập đến các tai nạn giao thông chết người do lỗi chú ý của lái xe, cho thấy nghiên cứu này có ứng dụng thực tiễn để giảm thiểu tai nạn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"22\">Câu 35: Quá trình lão hóa làm tăng nhu cầu lấp đầy các khoảng trống trong nhận thức thị giác.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Toàn bộ bài đọc không đề cập đến “quá trình lão hóa” (aging process) hay mối liên hệ của nó với việc nhận thức thị giác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('26bda0d1-066b-43ea-97ac-664812068761', '53d6e3a3-9589-46fc-bd5c-b49210cced68', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21–22', '', '<p data-start="154" data-end="186">Choose <strong data-start="161" data-end="168">TWO</strong> letters, <strong data-start="178" data-end="185">A–E</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="188" data-end="266">Which <strong>TWO</strong> things did Colin find most satisfying about his bread reuse project?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A receiving support from local restaurants"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "B finding a good way to prevent waste"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C overcoming problems in a basic process"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D experimenting with designs and colours"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E learning how to apply 3-D printing"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"109\" data-end=\"158\"><strong data-start=\"109\" data-end=\"119\">COLIN:</strong> I haven’t seen you for a bit, Marie.</p>\n<p data-start=\"160\" data-end=\"208\"><strong data-start=\"160\" data-end=\"170\">MARIE:</strong> No, I’ve been busy with my project.</p>\n<p data-start=\"210\" data-end=\"321\"><strong data-start=\"210\" data-end=\"220\">COLIN:</strong> You’re making a vegan alternative to eggs, aren’t you? Something that doesn’t use animal products?</p>\n<p data-start=\"323\" data-end=\"505\"><strong data-start=\"323\" data-end=\"333\">MARIE:</strong> Yes. I’m using chickpeas. I had two main aims when I first started looking for an alternative to eggs, but actually I’ve found chickpeas have got more advantages, right.</p>\n<p data-start=\"507\" data-end=\"610\"><strong data-start=\"507\" data-end=\"517\">COLIN:</strong> But how about your project on reusing waste food – you were looking at bread, weren’t you?</p>\n<p data-start=\"612\" data-end=\"860\"><strong data-start=\"612\" data-end=\"622\">MARIE:</strong> Yes. It’s been hard work, but I’ve enjoyed it. <strong data-start=\"670\" data-end=\"779\">The basic process was quite straightforward – breaking the stale bread down to a paste then reforming it.</strong> But you were using 3-D printing, weren’t you, to make the paste into biscuits?</p>\n<p data-start=\"862\" data-end=\"1133\"><strong data-start=\"862\" data-end=\"872\">COLIN:</strong> Yeah, I’d used that before, but in this project, <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(21) I had time to play around with different patterns for the biscuits and finding how I could add fruit and vegetables to make them more appealing colours, and I was really pleased with what I managed to produce.</span></strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"1135\" data-end=\"1274\"><strong data-start=\"1135\" data-end=\"1145\">MARIE:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(22) It must’ve been a great feeling to make something appealing out of bits of old bread that would’ve been thrown away otherwise</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1276\" data-end=\"1421\"><strong data-start=\"1276\" data-end=\"1286\">COLIN:</strong> It was. And I’m hoping that some of the restaurants in town will be interested in the biscuits. I’m going to send them some samples.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1423\" data-end=\"1585\"><strong data-start=\"1423\" data-end=\"1433\">MARIE:</strong> I came across something on the internet yesterday that might interest you. It was a company that’s developed touch-sensitive sensors for food labels.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1587\" data-end=\"1603\"><strong data-start=\"1587\" data-end=\"1597\">COLIN:</strong> Mm?</p>\n<p data-start=\"1605\" data-end=\"1890\"><strong data-start=\"1605\" data-end=\"1615\">MARIE:</strong> It’s a special sort of label on the food package. When the label’s smooth, the food’s fresh and then when you can feel bumps on the label, that means the food’s gone bad. It started off as a project to help visually impaired people know whether food was fit to eat or not.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1892\" data-end=\"1937\"><strong data-start=\"1892\" data-end=\"1902\">COLIN:</strong> Interesting. So just solid food?</p>\n<p data-start=\"1939\" data-end=\"2086\"><strong data-start=\"1939\" data-end=\"1949\">MARIE:</strong> No, things like milk and juices as well. But actually, <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(23) I thought it might be really good for drug storage in hospitals and pharmacies.</span></strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2088\" data-end=\"2258\"><strong data-start=\"2088\" data-end=\"2098\">COLIN:</strong> <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">Right</span></strong>. And coming back to food, maybe it’d be possible to use it for other things besides freshness. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(24) Like how many kilograms a joint of meat is, for example.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"2265\" data-end=\"2318\"><strong data-start=\"2265\" data-end=\"2275\">MARIE:</strong> Yes, there’s all sorts of possibilities.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2320\" data-end=\"2440\"><strong data-start=\"2320\" data-end=\"2330\">COLIN:</strong> I was reading an article about food trends predicting how eating habits might change in the next few years.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2442\" data-end=\"2566\"><strong data-start=\"2442\" data-end=\"2452\">MARIE:</strong> Oh – things <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(25) like more focus on local products?</span></strong> That seems so obvious, but perhaps we’ll look in different ways.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2568\" data-end=\"2631\"><strong data-start=\"2568\" data-end=\"2578\">COLIN:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>Yes, they need to be more produce to address that.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"2633\" data-end=\"2692\"><strong data-start=\"2633\" data-end=\"2643\">MARIE:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>And somehow motivate consumers to change, yes.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"2694\" data-end=\"2917\"><strong data-start=\"2694\" data-end=\"2704\">COLIN:</strong> One thing everyone’s aware of is <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(26) the need for a reduction in unnecessary packaging</strong></span> – but what about everything you buy in supermarkets is still covered in plastic. The government needs to do something about it.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2919\" data-end=\"2963\"><strong data-start=\"2919\" data-end=\"2929\">MARIE:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>Absolutely, it’s got to change.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"2965\" data-end=\"3050\"><strong data-start=\"2965\" data-end=\"2975\">COLIN:</strong> Do you think there’ll be more interest in gluten- and lactose-free food?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3052\" data-end=\"3198\"><strong data-start=\"3052\" data-end=\"3062\">MARIE:</strong> For people with allergies or food intolerances? I don’t know. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(27) Lots of people I know have been buying that type of food for years now.</span></strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"3200\" data-end=\"3270\"><strong data-start=\"3200\" data-end=\"3210\">COLIN:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>Yes, even if they haven’t been diagnosed with an allergy.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"3272\" data-end=\"3553\"><strong data-start=\"3272\" data-end=\"3282\">MARIE:</strong> That’s right. One thing I’ve noticed is the number of branded products related to celebrity chefs – people watch them cooking on TV and then buy things like spice mixes or frozen foods with the chef’s name on… <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(28) I bought something like that once – but I won’t again.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"3555\" data-end=\"3723\"><strong data-start=\"3555\" data-end=\"3565\">COLIN:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>Yeah, I bought a ready-made spice mix for chicken which was supposed to be used by a chef I’d seen on television, and it didn’t actually taste of anything.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"3725\" data-end=\"3813\"><strong data-start=\"3725\" data-end=\"3735\">MARIE:</strong> Mm. Did the article mention ‘ghost kitchens’ used to produce takeaway food?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3815\" data-end=\"3846\"><strong data-start=\"3815\" data-end=\"3825\">COLIN:</strong> No. What are they?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3848\" data-end=\"4070\"><strong data-start=\"3848\" data-end=\"3858\">MARIE:</strong> Well, they might have the name of a restaurant, but actually they’re a cooking facility just for delivery meals – the public don’t ever go there. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(29) But people aren’t aware of that – it’s all kept very quiet.</span></strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"4072\" data-end=\"4153\"><strong data-start=\"4072\" data-end=\"4082\">COLIN:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>So people don’t realise the food’s not actually from the restaurant?</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"4155\" data-end=\"4174\"><strong data-start=\"4155\" data-end=\"4165\">MARIE:</strong> Right.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4176\" data-end=\"4333\"><strong data-start=\"4176\" data-end=\"4186\">COLIN:</strong> Did you know more and more people are using all sorts of different mushrooms now, to take different health concerns? Things like heart problems?</p>\n<p data-start=\"4335\" data-end=\"4395\"><strong data-start=\"4335\" data-end=\"4345\">MARIE:</strong> Mm. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(30) They might be taking a bit of a risk there.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"4397\" data-end=\"4465\"><strong data-start=\"4397\" data-end=\"4407\">COLIN:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>Yes, it’s hard to know which varieties are safe to eat.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"4467\" data-end=\"4495\"><strong data-start=\"4467\" data-end=\"4477\">MARIE:</strong> Anyway maybe now…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('39be77bc-5f25-4e16-b2c2-085f00108025', 'a09725c8-dc9c-44a2-aa7a-484b2bd3c423', 'matching', 'Questions 36–40', NULL, '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, A-G, below.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A is not backed by scientific evidence."}, {"optionText": "B is provided by memory."}, {"optionText": "C has been especially fruitful in recent times."}, {"optionText": "D causes us to overlook other details."}, {"optionText": "E has sparked significant public debate."}, {"optionText": "F is challenging for us to accept."}, {"optionText": "G helps us see the overall picture more clearly."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Concentrating on a particular aspect of an activity or scene ", "correctAnswer": "D causes us to overlook other details.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "The fact that we make visual errors", "correctAnswer": "F is challenging for us to accept.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "The part of the picture that we fail to see clearly", "correctAnswer": "B is provided by memory.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "The idea that we see everything in our visual field", "correctAnswer": "A is not backed by scientific evidence.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Research into the nature of human vision", "correctAnswer": "C has been especially fruitful in recent times.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\">Câu 36</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">D: causes us to overlook other details.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“‘Inattentional blindness’ refers to not noticing a feature of a scene when you aren’t paying attention to it.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khi chúng ta tập trung vào một khía cạnh cụ thể của hoạt động (như đếm số lần chuyền bóng trong thí nghiệm gorilla), chúng ta sẽ không chú ý đến các đặc điểm khác, dẫn đến việc bỏ qua các chi tiết quan trọng (overlook other details).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"4\">Câu 37</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">F: is challenging for us to accept.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“When the tape was replayed… they easily saw the gorilla. Some even doubted it was the same video.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc chúng ta mắc lỗi thị giác rõ ràng (không thấy con gorilla) thường rất khó để người tham gia chấp nhận (challenging to accept), đến mức họ nghi ngờ rằng đoạn video đã bị thay đổi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"6\">Câu 38</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">B: is provided by memory.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“‘The illusion that we see ‘everything’ is partly due to filling in gaps with memory,’ he says.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Chuyên gia Stephen Kosslyn giải thích rằng bộ não chúng ta tạo ra cảm giác nhìn thấy toàn cảnh bằng cách sử dụng trí nhớ (memory) để lấp đầy những phần hoặc chi tiết mà mắt không thực sự thu nhận rõ ràng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"8\">Câu 39</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">A: is not backed by scientific evidence.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Rather than logging every detail of the visual scene, says Simons, we are actually highly selective. Our impression of seeing everything is just that.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ý tưởng cho rằng chúng ta nhìn thấy mọi thứ trong tầm mắt chỉ là một ấn tượng/ảo giác. Thực tế khoa học cho thấy mắt rất chọn lọc (highly selective) và không hề ghi lại mọi chi tiết như chúng ta vẫn lầm tưởng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"10\">Câu 40</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">C: has been especially fruitful in recent times.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“When considered with a large number of recent experimental results, this phenomenon suggests we ‘see’ far less than we think we do.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “recent experimental results” (các kết quả thí nghiệm gần đây) cho thấy các nghiên cứu về bản chất thị giác con người đã mang lại nhiều kết quả phong phú và tiến triển mạnh mẽ (fruitful) trong thời gian gần đây.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9a992fde-84c7-4596-89e9-dc82c9119cbf', '7aadd5b2-a63b-4b58-9c43-bd16f49a1669', 'radio', 'Questions 21–26', '<p data-start="107" data-end="148"><strong data-start="107" data-end="148">Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</strong></p>
<p data-start="150" data-end="343"> </p>
', '<p data-start="107" data-end="148"><strong data-start="107" data-end="148">Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</strong></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. was not familiar to their module leader."}, {"content": "B. had not been chosen by other students."}, {"content": "C. did not prove to be difficult to research."}], "question": "Finn was pleased to discover that their topic"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. theatres pay companies to produce them."}, {"content": "B. few theatre-goers buy them nowadays."}, {"content": "C. they contain far more adverts than previously."}], "question": "Maya says a mistaken belief about theatre programmes is that"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. were difficult for audiences to obtain."}, {"content": "B. were given out free of charge."}, {"content": "C. were seen as a kind of contract."}], "question": "Finn was surprised that, in early British theatre, programmes"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. promoted their own plays."}, {"content": "B. performed plays outdoors."}, {"content": "C. had to tour with their plays."}], "question": "Maya feels their project should include an explanation of why companies of actors"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. were more original."}, {"content": "B. were more colourful."}, {"content": "C. were more informative."}], "question": "Finn and Maya both think that, compared to nineteenth-century programmes, those from the eighteenth century"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. very few theatre programmes were printed in the USA."}, {"content": "B. British theatre programmes failed to develop for so long."}, {"content": "C. theatre programmes in Britain copied fashions from the USA."}], "question": "Maya doesn’t fully understand why, in the twentieth century,"}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>1. Lịch sử và Đặc điểm Chương trình Sân khấu (Questions 21–26)<br /> </p>\n<p>MAYA: So, Finn, I&#8217;ve done as much as I can for our project on theatre programmes.</p>\n<p>MAYA: How&#8217;s your research coming along?</p>\n<p>FINN: Okay, Maya.</p>\n<p>FINN: I didn&#8217;t know theatre programmes are called playbills in the USA till I started looking into the topic. (Question 21)</p>\n<p>FINN: Even though I struggled to find many useful websites, I&#8217;m glad we picked this subject.</p>\n<p>FINN: No one else on the course is doing the same as us, although it is one of the research areas of the module convener.</p>\n<p>MAYA: That might actually put some people off.</p>\n<p>FINN: I suppose so.</p>\n<p>FINN: Anyway, I hadn&#8217;t realised there are actually companies specialising in creating theatre programmes. (Question 22)</p>\n<p>MAYA: Yes, they&#8217;re quite common nowadays.</p>\n<p>MAYA: Contrary to what many people think, theatres don&#8217;t hire people to do the programmes.</p>\n<p>MAYA: In fact, companies buy the rights to publish programmes on the theatre&#8217;s behalf and then make their money selling advertising space within the programme booklet.</p>\n<p>FINN: It must be easier for theatres to do it that way.</p>\n<p>MAYA: Yes.</p>\n<p>FINN: I remember reading something about programmes in early British theatre.</p>\n<p>FINN: It said that the cast was always very important. (Question 23)</p>\n<p>MAYA: Yes.</p>\n<p>MAYA: Audiences were very familiar with leading actors and big names would draw huge crowds.</p>\n<p>FINN: But I hadn&#8217;t realised that if the programme named a famous actor, that&#8217;s who the public expected to perform.</p>\n<p>FINN: And if that didn&#8217;t happen, people accused the theatre of breaking their agreement with the audience.</p>\n<p>FINN: They would demand refunds and if they didn&#8217;t get them, there were riots.</p>\n<p>MAYA: Outrageous!</p>\n<p>MAYA: That&#8217;d never happen now.</p>\n<p>FINN: No, people are too polite, even when they&#8217;re disappointed if the star of the show misses a performance.</p>\n<p>MAYA: We should definitely include that information about early audiences in our project.</p>\n<p>MAYA: I also think it&#8217;s important to mention that lots of ordinary people at that time were illiterate, so theatre programmes were of limited value in advertising plays. (Question 24)</p>\n<p>MAYA: When a company of actors arrived in a town, they&#8217;d parade around the streets in their costumes, beating drums and announcing their upcoming performances.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>FINN: Interesting.</p>\n<p>FINN: I couldn&#8217;t imagine that happening now either.</p>\n<p>MAYA: There&#8217;s also an interesting comparison to make between 18th and 19th century programmes.</p>\n<p>FINN: Wasn&#8217;t it in the 19th century that theatre programmes started to resemble programmes today?</p>\n<p>MAYA: Yes, and unlike programmes from the 18th century, they always used colour. (Question 25)</p>\n<p>FINN: And there was a greater variety of designs.</p>\n<p>FINN: But personally, I think 18th century programmes were superior because they told the theatre-goers so many things, including about the actors.</p>\n<p>MAYA: And about the writer, the plot, and sometimes the history of the play.</p>\n<p>FINN: That&#8217;s right.</p>\n<p>FINN: What should we say about theatre programmes in the 20th century?</p>\n<p>MAYA: I reckon the most important thing is the dramatic change they underwent during World War II. (Question 26)</p>\n<p>FINN: When the government imposed restrictions on the use of paper.</p>\n<p>MAYA: Yeah, but that was only in the UK.</p>\n<p>MAYA: In the USA, programmes, or rather playbills, continued to be published in the same format.</p>\n<p>FINN: While here in the UK, programmes became merely a single sheet of paper folded to create four pages for text.</p>\n<p>MAYA: What I don&#8217;t really get is that after the war, they didn&#8217;t go back to being more than one sheet or change in any way for over 25 years.</p>\n<p>MAYA: I know there were paper shortages after the war, but only for five or ten years.</p>\n<p>FINN: Hmm, strange.</p>\n<p> <br /> </p>\n<p>2. Các Mẫu Chương trình Đặc biệt (Questions 27–30)<br /> </p>\n<p>MAYA: I&#8217;ve got some pictures of programmes we could include on the slides for our presentation.</p>\n<p>FINN: I&#8217;ve found a couple too, Maya.</p>\n<p>FINN: Let&#8217;s go through and see what we think.</p>\n<p>MAYA: Um, ah, this is an old one for a play called Rui Blas.</p>\n<p>FINN: Hmm, never heard of that.</p>\n<p>FINN: But the programme looks very decorative. (Question 27)</p>\n<p>MAYA: Good enough to put in a frame on the wall.</p>\n<p>MAYA: The images are just beautiful.</p>\n<p>MAYA: Finn, what did you find?</p>\n<p>FINN: I&#8217;ve got some pages from a programme for Man of La Mancha.</p>\n<p>FINN: I thought this was a good programme to show, not because of the pictures, but because it contains articles written by members of the theatre company, so we can learn how the production was created and the thoughts and feelings of the cast. (Question 28)</p>\n<p>MAYA: Good.</p>\n<p>MAYA: I&#8217;ve got a copy of a programme that&#8217;s now in a museum.</p>\n<p>MAYA: It&#8217;s for The Tragedy of Jane Shaw, and it&#8217;s said to be the earliest surviving document to have been printed on Australia&#8217;s first printing press. (Question 29)</p>\n<p>FINN: Fantastic!</p>\n<p>MAYA: Another programme to talk about is for The Sailors&#8217; Festival.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>MAYA: It comes from the British Library&#8217;s digitised collection of programmes that was started a few years ago. (Question 30)</p>\n<p>MAYA: It already comprises over 200,000 programmes, which is amazing!</p>\n<p>FINN: Huh, wish I&#8217;d known about it while I was doing my research!</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e5b6ba38-5c15-4bef-a7f8-21fb4c9c5ead', '8f28f354-3d19-4cac-a974-b68fe7c138cd', 'fillup', 'Questions 7-13', '<p>Answer the questions below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer</p>
<p>Apart from exchange rates, which factor has had a negative impact on New Zealand’s forestry<br />
exports? {shipping costs}</p>
<p>Which part of New Zealand’s economy does the forestry industry rank third in?  {export sector}</p>
<p>According to the New Zealand forestry industry, what could be the size of its workforce by<br />
2025? {60000 people}</p>
<p>What kind of timber product is available in large amounts from renewable forests in New<br />
Zealand? {softwood}</p>
<p>Which aspect of timber production are New Zealand’s main customers increasingly concerned<br />
about? {sustainability}</p>
<p>Outside the southern hemisphere, who are New Zealand forestry’s main competitors? {scandinavian countries}</p>
<p>Which group of products is New Zealand’s forestry industry now having to compete with? {wood substitutes}</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Apart from exchange rates, which factor has had a negative impact on New Zealand’s forestry exports?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: shipping costs</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, câu 1: <em data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“…until affected by the exchange fluctuations and <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">shipping costs</strong> of recent years.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngoài biến động tỷ giá (exchange fluctuations/rates), chi phí vận chuyển (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">shipping costs</strong>) là yếu tố gây tác động tiêu cực đến xuất khẩu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Which part of New Zealand’s economy does the forestry industry rank third in?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: export sector</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, câu 2: <em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The forestry industry is New Zealand’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">third largest export sector</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngành lâm nghiệp đứng thứ ba trong <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">lĩnh vực xuất khẩu</strong> của nền kinh tế New Zealand.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. According to the New Zealand forestry industry, what could be the size of its workforce by 2025?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: 60000 people</strong> (hoặc <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">60,000</strong>)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 8, câu cuối: <em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“…by 2025 the forestry sector could be… employing <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">60000 people</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản dự báo đến năm 2025, ngành này có thể tạo việc làm cho <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">60.000 người</strong> (đây chính là quy mô lực lượng lao động – workforce).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. What kind of timber product is available in large amounts from renewable forests in New Zealand?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: softwood</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 9, câu 1: <em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“One competitive advantage that New Zealand has is its ability to source large quantities of <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"119\">softwood</strong> from renewable forests.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> New Zealand có khả năng cung cấp một lượng lớn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">large quantities/amounts</strong>) loại gỗ mềm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">softwood</strong>) từ các khu rừng có thể tái tạo.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Which aspect of timber production are New Zealand’s main customers increasingly concerned about?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: sustainability</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 9, câu 2: <em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Consumers in several key wood markets are becoming more worried about <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">sustainability</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khách hàng tại các thị trường trọng điểm (main customers) đang ngày càng lo ngại về tính bền vững (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">sustainability</strong>) của việc sản xuất gỗ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Outside the southern hemisphere, who are New Zealand forestry’s main competitors?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: scandinavian countries</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 9, câu cuối: <em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“…and in the northern hemisphere, <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">Scandinavian countries</strong> have all expanded their forest…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Outside the southern hemisphere” tương ứng với “northern hemisphere” (Bán cầu Bắc). Đối thủ chính ở khu vực này là các <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">quốc gia Scandinavia</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Which group of products is New Zealand’s forestry industry now having to compete with?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: wood substitutes</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn cuối, câu 1: <em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“…New Zealand faces competition from goods such as <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">wood substitutes</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngoài các đối thủ sản xuất gỗ, New Zealand còn phải cạnh tranh với nhóm các sản phẩm thay thế gỗ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">wood substitutes</strong>) như khung thép cho nhà ở.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a297b1f4-01b8-489f-9de3-acdef4e5d3c8', '53d6e3a3-9589-46fc-bd5c-b49210cced68', 'matching', 'Questions 25–30', '', '<p data-start="101" data-end="171">What is the students’ opinion about each of the following food trends?</p>
<p data-start="173" data-end="272">Choose <strong data-start="180" data-end="187">SIX</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong data-start="239" data-end="246">A–H</strong>, next to Questions 25–30.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Food trends</strong></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Use of local products {D Retailers should do more to encourage this.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Reduction in unnecessary packaging {G There should be stricter regulations about this.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Gluten-free and lactose-free food {C This already seems to be widespread.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Use of branded products related to celebrity chefs {B This may have disappointing results.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Development of ‘ghost kitchens’ for takeaway food {F Most people know little about this.}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Use of mushrooms for common health concerns {H This could be dangerous.}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A This is only relevant to young people."}, {"optionText": "B This may have disappointing results."}, {"optionText": "C This already seems to be widespread."}, {"optionText": "D Retailers should do more to encourage this."}, {"optionText": "E More financial support is needed for this."}, {"optionText": "F Most people know little about this."}, {"optionText": "G There should be stricter regulations about this."}, {"optionText": "H This could be dangerous."}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('486218ae-bdb7-4f46-bac1-c688f651b88c', '811e3325-3a30-4d56-82cf-baf34d66d493', 'radio', 'Questions 27–32', '', '<p>Choose<strong> YES</strong> if the statement is true,<strong>NO</strong> if the statement is false,<strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if the information is not given in the passage</p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Grimm brothers believed they would achieve international fame."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Grimm brothers were forced to work in secret."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some parents today still think Grimm fairy tales are not suitable for children."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The first edition of Grimm’s fairy tales sold more widely in England than in Germany."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Adults like reading Grimm’s fairy tales for reasons different from those of children."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Grimm brothers based the story “Cinderella” on the life of Dorothea Viehmann"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. The Grimm brothers believed they would achieve international fame. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Such lasting <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">fame would have shocked the humble Grimms</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói rằng sự nổi tiếng bền vững này sẽ làm anh em nhà Grimm khiêm tốn phải <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">kinh ngạc (shocked)</strong>. Điều này trái ngược với việc họ “tin rằng” mình sẽ đạt được sự nổi tiếng quốc tế.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. The Grimm brothers were forced to work in secret. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 1 có nói họ làm việc khi Đức bị Napoleon xâm lược và muốn bảo tồn truyền thống đang bị đe dọa.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói họ là những học giả “nghiện việc” (workaholic) làm việc trong một căn hộ chật hẹp, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">không hề có thông tin</strong> nào nói họ bị “ép buộc phải làm việc trong bí mật” (forced to work in secret).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. Some parents today still think Grimm fairy tales are not suitable for children. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Even <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">today some protective parents shy from the Grimms’ tales</strong> because of their reputation for <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">violence</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Shy from” (né tránh) đồng nghĩa với việc họ nghĩ những câu chuyện này không phù hợp (not suitable) cho trẻ em vì yếu tố bạo lực. Thông tin này khớp hoàn toàn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. The first edition of Grimm’s fairy tales sold more widely in England than in Germany. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“English publishers led the way, issuing high-quality picture books…”</em> và đoạn 1 nói <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">“the collection sold modestly in Germany”</em>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nói ấn bản đầu tiên bán rất chậm ở Đức và các nhà xuất bản Anh dẫn đầu trong việc in sách tranh, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">không có sự so sánh cụ thể</strong> về số lượng bản bán ra của “ấn bản đầu tiên” (first edition) giữa Anh và Đức.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. Adults like reading Grimm’s fairy tales for reasons different from those of children. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> * Trẻ em thích vì: <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">“handsome lads and beautiful damsels… magic… triumph over giants”</em> (phép thuật, cái thiện thắng cái ác).</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,1,0,0\">Người lớn (phụ huynh) thích vì: <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">“they approve of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">finger-wagging lessons</strong> inserted into the stories: keep your promises, don’t talk to strangers…”</em> (các bài học đạo đức, giáo dục).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trẻ em đọc vì sự kỳ ảo và mơ mộng, còn người lớn đọc vì mục đích giáo dục hành vi. Hai lý do này là hoàn toàn khác nhau (different reasons).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. The Grimm brothers based the story “Cinderella” on the life of Dorothea Viehmann. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Among her [Dorothea Viehmann] treasure was <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">“Aschenputtel” – Cinderella</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dorothea Viehmann là một trong những <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">người kể chuyện</strong> (storytellers) cho anh em nhà Grimm. Bà là người kể lại câu chuyện Cinderella cho họ ghi chép, chứ không phải anh em nhà Grimm lấy cuộc đời bà để viết nên nhân vật Cinderella. (Dựa trên lời kể khác với dựa trên cuộc đời).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3c7e6ebd-4198-4a6b-a19e-30498b0cc7c7', '811e3325-3a30-4d56-82cf-baf34d66d493', 'radio', 'Questions 33-35', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B, C</strong> or <strong>D</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. Literacy levels of the population increased."}, {"option_text": "B. The development of printing technology made it easier to publish."}, {"option_text": "C. Schools were open to children."}, {"option_text": "D. People were fond of collecting super picture books."}], "question": "In paragraph 4, what changes happened at that time in Europe?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. They made the stories shorter."}, {"option_text": "B. They used more oral language."}, {"option_text": "C. The content of the tales became less violent."}, {"option_text": "D. They found other origins of the tales."}], "question": "What changes did the Grimm Brothers make in later editions?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. She wrote stories."}, {"option_text": "B. She discussed the stories with them."}, {"option_text": "C. She translated a popular book for the brothers using her talent for languages."}, {"option_text": "D. She told the oral stories that were based on traditional Italian stories."}], "question": "What did Marie Hassenpflug contribute to the Grimm’s Fairy tales?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. In paragraph 4, what changes happened at that time in Europe? — {A. Literacy levels of the population increased.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3 &amp; 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“…all to satisfy a <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">newly literate audience</strong> seeking virtuous material for the nursery.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “newly literate audience” (nhóm công chúng mới biết chữ) ám chỉ rằng tại thời điểm đó ở châu Âu, trình độ biết chữ của người dân đã tăng lên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">literacy levels increased</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. What changes did the Grimm Brothers make in later editions? — {C. The content of the tales became less violent.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3 &amp; 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">“Once the Brothers Grimm sighted this new public, they set about <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">refining and softening their tales</strong>… cruel mothers became nasty stepmothers, unmarried lovers were made chaste…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để phù hợp với công chúng mới là trẻ em và phụ huynh, hai anh em đã “refining and softening” (tinh chỉnh và làm mềm mỏng hóa) các câu chuyện. Việc biến mẹ đẻ độc ác thành mẹ kế hay giảm bớt các tình tiết nhạy cảm chính là làm cho nội dung bớt bạo lực/thô ráp hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"276\">less violent/softened</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. What did Marie Hassenpflug contribute to the Grimm’s Fairy tales? — {D. She told the oral stories that were based on traditional Italian stories.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Marie’s wonderful stories <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">blended motifs from the oral tradition and from Perrault’s</strong> influential 1697 book… Many of these <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"145\">had been adapted from earlier Italian tales</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Marie Hassenpflug là một người kể chuyện (told the oral stories). Những câu chuyện của bà là sự pha trộn giữa truyền thống truyền miệng và sách của Perrault, vốn có nguồn gốc từ các câu chuyện của Ý (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"212\">based on traditional Italian stories</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9dc2c49b-020a-43a3-ab9b-1b50a24f0f05', 'd155afd2-835b-406c-bb92-3d4713c107e0', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<p>Write <strong data-start="138" data-end="166">ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9971%;" border="1"><colgroup> <col style="width: 99.8607%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<div class="flex flex-col text-sm pb-25">
<article class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" tabindex="-1" data-turn-id="request-692808c1-5324-8321-9241-cf1905753e43-29" data-testid="conversation-turn-299" data-scroll-anchor="true" data-turn="assistant">
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto pb-10 [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="86f1a168-068e-4525-be87-bcb275489092" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling">
<p style="text-align: left;" data-start="190" data-end="213"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-start="194" data-end="213">Help for carers</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="215" data-end="308">Local councils can arrange practical support to help those caring for elderly people at home.</p>
<p data-start="310" data-end="336">This can give the carer:</p>
<ul data-start="337" data-end="393">
<li data-start="337" data-end="372">
<p data-start="339" data-end="372">time for other responsibilities</p>
</li>
<li data-start="373" data-end="393">
<p data-start="375" data-end="393">a <strong data-start="377" data-end="393">{break}</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="400" data-end="436"><strong data-start="404" data-end="436">Assessment of mother’s needs</strong></p>
<p data-start="438" data-end="471">This may include discussion of:</p>
<ul data-start="472" data-end="860">
<li data-start="472" data-end="521">
<p data-start="474" data-end="521">how much <strong data-start="483" data-end="499">{time}</strong> the caring involves</p>
</li>
<li data-start="522" data-end="705">
<p data-start="524" data-end="564">what types of tasks are involved, e.g.</p>
<ul data-start="567" data-end="705">
<li data-start="567" data-end="589">
<p data-start="569" data-end="589">help with dressing</p>
</li>
<li data-start="592" data-end="631">
<p data-start="594" data-end="631">helping her have a <strong data-start="613" data-end="629">{shower}</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="634" data-end="646">
<p data-start="636" data-end="646">shopping</p>
</li>
<li data-start="649" data-end="671">
<p data-start="651" data-end="671">helping with meals</p>
</li>
<li data-start="674" data-end="705">
<p data-start="676" data-end="705">dealing with <strong data-start="689" data-end="705">{money}</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="707" data-end="860">
<p data-start="709" data-end="768">any aspects of caring that are especially difficult, e.g.</p>
<ul data-start="771" data-end="860">
<li data-start="771" data-end="799">
<p data-start="773" data-end="799">loss of <strong data-start="781" data-end="797">{memory}</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="802" data-end="826">
<p data-start="804" data-end="826"><strong data-start="804" data-end="820">{lifting}</strong> her</p>
</li>
<li data-start="829" data-end="860">
<p data-start="831" data-end="860">preventing a <strong data-start="844" data-end="860">{fall}</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="867" data-end="921"><strong data-start="871" data-end="921">Types of support that may be offered to carers</strong></p>
<ul data-start="923" data-end="1088" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">
<li data-start="923" data-end="975">
<p data-start="925" data-end="975">transport costs, e.g. cost of a <strong data-start="957" data-end="973">{taxi}</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="976" data-end="1029">
<p data-start="978" data-end="1029">car-related costs, e.g. fuel and <strong data-start="957" data-end="973">{insurance}</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1030" data-end="1053">
<p data-start="1032" data-end="1053">help with housework</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1054" data-end="1088" data-is-last-node="">
<p data-start="1056" data-end="1088" data-is-last-node="">help to reduce <strong data-start="1011" data-end="1027">{stress}</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mt-3 w-full empty:hidden"> </div>
</div>
</div>
</article>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"0\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: HELP FOR CARERS</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> It’s really good to see you, Tom. Since I had to give up work, I feel I’m losing touch with my friends and colleagues.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> We really miss you in the office – we were all so sorry you had to leave. But you must be relieved to have more time to look after your mother. How is she?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> Well, she’s very cheerful but she needs a lot of help.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> Have you tried to get any support from the local council?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> No, I didn’t know I could.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> Yes, they offer different kinds of practical support. They realise that carers sometimes need time for all the other responsibilities they have apart from the person they’re caring for, and also that they sometimes need a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"227\">(1) break</strong></span></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> Absolutely. Ok, so tell me more. How do I go about getting this support?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> Well, you’d have to have an assessment of your mother’s needs. That means someone would come round and talk to you about the situation and what you need. So for a start they’d want to know the amount of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"208\">(2) time</strong></span> you spend looking after your mother every day.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> Oh.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> Then they’ll probably ask you what sorts of tasks you do for your mother during the day. Things like if she needs help with getting dressed, for example.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> Right. I help her with that, and also I help her get into the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">(3) shower</strong></span> in the morning.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> Yes, that sort of thing. They’ll probably ask you if you do the shopping for her, and help her at mealtimes. And whether she can cope using <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"145\">(4) money</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> Yes, that’s becoming a bit of a problem. She used to be very good at it, but not any more.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> And be ready to tell them about anything you find particularly difficult about caring for your mother.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> So recently I’ve noticed she’s started to have quite bad problems with her <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">(5) memory</strong></span>… if I wasn’t there, I think she’d forget to eat, for example. And often she doesn’t seem quite sure what day it is.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> Yes, tell them about that. And are there any physical difficulties you have caring for her? <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">(6) Lifting</strong></span> her, for example?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> Yes. She’s quite heavy, and I’m afraid of hurting my back – I’d be in real trouble if that happened.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> They can give you advice about that, and also about how to avoid the possibility of your mum having a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">(7) fall</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> Great. So once they’ve done this assessment, if I’m eligible, what happens next?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> Well, they might support you financially. So they might help you with transport costs, like if you have to get a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">(8) taxi</strong></span> to take your mother for an appointment, for example.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> I usually drive her myself actually. So could I claim for the petrol?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> You could, and you can claim for the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">(9) insurance</strong></span> too.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> Oh, right.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> And if you need help with the housework, they can arrange for someone to come along once or twice a week. And one other thing, I hope you don’t mind me saying this, but it’s important you look after yourself, and it seems to me you’re under quite a bit of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(10) stress</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> I am, yes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">TOM:</strong> Well, tell the council, because they may be able to give you some advice on how to minimise it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAROL:</strong> Really? Though actually I feel so much better having talked to you. I’ll get in touch with the council straight away. Now shall we…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ce9ced65-07aa-4ca2-b750-ac01ff2717ca', '811e3325-3a30-4d56-82cf-baf34d66d493', 'matching', 'Questions 36-40', '', '<p data-path-to-node="2">Write the correct letter, <strong>A-H</strong>, in boxes 36-40 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_sentence_endings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "reflect what life was like at that time"}, {"optionText": "help children deal with their problems"}, {"optionText": "demonstrate the outdated system"}, {"optionText": "tell of the simplicity of life in the German countryside"}, {"optionText": "encourage people to believe that they can do anything"}, {"optionText": "recognize the heroes in the real life"}, {"optionText": "contribute to the belief in nature power"}, {"optionText": "avoid details about characters’ social settings."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Heinz Rolleke said the Grimm’s tales are “German” because the tales", "correctAnswer": "D"}, {"questionPart": "Heinz Rolleke said the abandoned children in tales", "correctAnswer": "A"}, {"questionPart": "Bernhard Lauer said the writing style of the Grimm brothers is universal because they", "correctAnswer": "H"}, {"questionPart": "Jack Zipes said the pursuit of happiness in the tales means they", "correctAnswer": "E"}, {"questionPart": "Bruno Bettelheim said the therapeutic value of the tales means that the fairy tales", "correctAnswer": "B"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. Heinz Rolleke said the Grimm’s tales are “German” because the tales — {D. tell of the simplicity of life in the German countryside}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“How German are the Grimm tales? Very, says scholar Heinz Rolleke. Love of the underdog, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"109\">rustic simplicity [simplicity of life in the countryside]</strong>, creative energy—these are Teutonic [German] traits.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Rolleke khẳng định tính “Đức” của truyện nằm ở sự giản dị mộc mạc (rustic simplicity), một đặc điểm tiêu biểu của người Teuton (Đức).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Heinz Rolleke said the abandoned children in tales — {A. reflect what life was like at that time}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Throughout Europe, children were often neglected and abandoned, like Hansel and Gretel… ‘The cruelty in the stories was not the Grimm’s fantasy’, Rolleke points out. ‘<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"190\">It reflected the law-and-order system of the old times [what life was like at that time]</strong>‘.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những đứa trẻ bị bỏ rơi hay sự tàn khốc trong truyện không phải là hư cấu mà nó phản ánh đúng thực trạng xã hội và hệ thống luật pháp thời bấy giờ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Bernhard Lauer said the writing style of the Grimm brothers is universal because they — {H. avoid details about characters’ social settings.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Bernhard Lauer points to the ‘universal style’ of the writing, you have <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">no concrete descriptions of the land, or the clothes, or the forest, or the castles</strong>. It makes the stories <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">timeless and placeless</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Phong cách “phổ quát” (universal) của truyện là do tác giả lược bỏ các chi tiết cụ thể về địa điểm, trang phục hay bối cảnh xã hội (social settings), giúp câu chuyện có thể xảy ra ở bất cứ đâu, vào bất cứ thời đại nào.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Jack Zipes said the pursuit of happiness in the tales means they — {E. encourage people to believe that they can do anything}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…says Jack Zipes… ‘They show a <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">striving for happiness</strong> that none of us knows but that we sense is <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">possible</strong>. We can identify with the heroes… and <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"171\">become in our mind the masters and mistresses of our own destinies [believe they can do anything]</strong>.’”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc mưu cầu hạnh phúc giúp người đọc tin rằng mọi thứ đều khả thi và chính họ có thể làm chủ vận mệnh của mình.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. Bruno Bettelheim said the therapeutic value of the tales means that the fairy tales — {B. help children deal with their problems}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Bruno Bettelheim famously promoted the <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">therapeutic [value]</strong>… children find they can <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">master their anxieties [deal with their problems]</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Giá trị trị liệu (therapeutic value) của truyện cổ tích giúp trẻ em đối mặt và giải quyết những nỗi lo âu/vấn đề tâm lý của chính mình thông qua các hình tượng biểu trưng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6445299d-6da4-4d83-82bb-a5c1a2f2b7cd', '769406ff-78bd-4e57-a8fb-ad8337a1c3f5', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p data-start="148" data-end="188">Write <strong data-start="154" data-end="171">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-section-id="hvyc45" data-start="195" data-end="215"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-start="199" data-end="215">Céide Fields</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="217" data-end="291">• an important Neolithic archaeological site in the northwest of Ireland</p>
<p data-section-id="3kzbv0" data-start="298" data-end="315"><strong data-start="302" data-end="315">Discovery</strong></p>
<p data-start="317" data-end="423">• In the 1930s, a local teacher realised that stones beneath the bog surface were once {walls}</p>
<p data-start="425" data-end="690">• His {son} became an archaeologist and undertook an investigation of the site:</p>
<p data-start="425" data-end="690">– a traditional method used by local people to dig for <span data-start="570" data-end="587">{fuel} </span>was used to identify where stones were located<br data-start="634" data-end="637">– carbon dating later proved the site was Neolithic</p>
<p>• Items are well preserved in the bog because of a lack of {oxygen}</p>
<p data-section-id="cv09n1" data-start="777" data-end="802"><strong data-start="781" data-end="802">Neolithic farmers</strong></p>
<p>• Houses were {rectangular}  in shape and had a hole in the roof</p>
<p data-start="875" data-end="985">• Neolithic innovations include:<br data-start="907" data-end="910">– cooking indoors<br data-start="927" data-end="930">– pots used for storage and to make<strong> </strong>{lamps}</p>
<p data-start="987" data-end="1062">• Each field at Céide was large enough to support a big {family}</p>
<p data-start="1064" data-end="1199">• The fields were probably used to restrict the grazing of animals – no evidence of structures to house them during {winter}</p>
<p data-section-id="17g0f34" data-start="1206" data-end="1248"><strong data-start="1210" data-end="1248">Reasons for the decline in farming</strong></p>
<p data-start="1250" data-end="1292">• a decline in<strong> </strong>{soil} quality</p>
<p data-start="1294" data-end="1330">• an increase in {rain}</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('de7719df-259b-4fc4-8dbf-db09a8b7f73f', '52bd0edf-ba85-4e40-bd49-de57166b37ce', 'radio', 'QUESTIONS 1-5', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": " In Robert FitzRoy’s time, weather forecasting was a respected skill"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "When FitzRoy retired from the navy, he had already had a successful career at sea"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "FitzRoy faced competition from other applicants for the chief statistician’s job"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The British Parliament supported the idea of regular weather forecasts in 1854"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": " Progress in technology made it a good time for publicly available weather forecasting to begin"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. In Robert FitzRoy’s time, weather forecasting was a respected skill</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> “…in those days predicting the weather had gained a reputation <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">similar to astrology or fortune-telling</strong>. The few people who attempted it had become a <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"171\">national joke</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định vào thời của FitzRoy, dự báo thời tiết bị coi thường, bị đánh đồng với bói toán (fortune-telling). Những người thực hiện nó thường bị coi là “trò cười cho cả nước” (national joke) khi dự báo sai. Do đó, nó <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"237\">không</strong> phải là một kỹ năng được tôn trọng (respected skill).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. When FitzRoy retired from the navy, he had already had a successful career at sea</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> “His background was faultless, most famously his <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">captaining of the ship HMS Beagle</strong> on Charles Darwin’s voyage around the world… When FitzRoy retired from active service as an <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">admiral</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc ông từng là thuyền trưởng của con tàu nổi tiếng HMS Beagle và nghỉ hưu với quân hàm Đô đốc (admiral) — cấp bậc rất cao trong hải quân — chứng minh rằng ông đã có một sự nghiệp đi biển thành công và lẫy lừng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. FitzRoy faced competition from other applicants for the chief statistician’s job</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> “He subsequently <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">secured a job as chief statistician</strong> at the Meteorological Department…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ cho biết ông đã đảm nhận công việc trưởng ban thống kê sau khi nghỉ hưu. Văn bản <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">không đề cập</strong> đến việc có những ứng viên khác hay ông có phải cạnh tranh với ai để có được vị trí này hay không. Thông tin về “sự cạnh tranh” hoàn toàn thiếu vắng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. The British Parliament supported the idea of regular weather forecasts in 1854</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> “…the British Government was <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">not impressed</strong> with the idea… and the suggestion by one Member of Parliament for this was <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"142\">met with laughter</strong> from the other MPs.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mặc dù Nghị viện (Parliament) đã chi tiền thành lập Cục Khí tượng vào năm 1854, nhưng mục đích ban đầu chỉ là để lập bản đồ hàng hải an toàn. Khi có ý kiến đề xuất làm dự báo thời tiết thường xuyên, các nghị sĩ đã cười nhạo (met with laughter) và không hề ủng hộ ý tưởng này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Progress in technology made it a good time for publicly available weather forecasting to begin</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> “This was just the right moment for a national forecasting service. …the invention of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">electric telegraph and Morse code</strong> in 1844 gave <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">instant communication</strong> for the first time.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc xác nhận đây là “thời điểm thích hợp” (right moment) nhờ sự tiến bộ của công nghệ, cụ thể là máy điện báo và mã Morse giúp truyền tin tức thời giữa các trạm, kết hợp với các thiết bị đo đạc chính xác hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d41bf293-aabc-4e21-8ee7-856643f10edc', '155cd71b-f2ec-44fc-98b9-82d8cbd4374b', 'matching', 'Questions 20-23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following people (Questions 20-23) and the list of opinions below.<br />
Match each person with the correct opinion, <strong>A-G.</strong></p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A Incineration does not encourage responsible attitudes to waste disposal."}, {"optionText": "B Recycling can sometimes create serious problems for the future."}, {"optionText": "C Greater consumerism leads to higher levels of waste."}, {"optionText": "D Proper systems are needed for the recycling of environmentally-friendly products."}, {"optionText": "E Landfill is better for the environment than incineration."}, {"optionText": "F Incineration of waste is now relatively harmless to the environment."}, {"optionText": "G Efforts to reduce waste may affect profits for some types of companies."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Ted Michaels", "correctAnswer": "F Incineration of waste is now relatively harmless to the environment.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Joergen Fenhann", "correctAnswer": "C Greater consumerism leads to higher levels of waste.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Joan Marc Simon", "correctAnswer": "D Proper systems are needed for the recycling of environmentally-friendly products.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Tim Burns", "correctAnswer": "G Efforts to reduce waste may affect profits for some types of companies.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Ted Michaels: F (Incineration of waste is now relatively harmless to the environment.)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the output from these facilities is now <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">minuscule</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ông tin rằng nhờ công nghệ lọc mới, lượng khí thải từ lò đốt rác hiện nay là cực nhỏ (không đáng kể/không gây hại).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Joergen Fenhann: C (Greater consumerism leads to higher levels of waste.)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The more you develop, the more you produce, buy and throw away.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự phát triển và tiêu dùng càng cao thì lượng rác thải ra càng nhiều.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Joan Marc Simon: D (Proper systems are needed for the recycling of environmentally-friendly products.)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…without the right mechanisms in place ‘nothing guarantees that this bottle will end up being properly collected and treated…’”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dù thiết kế sản phẩm tốt đến đâu, nếu không có hệ thống/cơ chế thu gom đúng cách thì vẫn không thể tái chế hiệu quả.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Tim Burns: G (Efforts to reduce waste may affect profits for some types of companies.)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…if you do that, then that’s money the retailers don’t get…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc người dân giảm mua sắm để giảm rác thải sẽ trực tiếp làm giảm doanh thu/lợi nhuận của các nhà bán lẻ.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('08870c06-c5a1-4af9-bb53-9f6fea191355', '52bd0edf-ba85-4e40-bd49-de57166b37ce', 'fillup', 'Questions 6–13', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the passage for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write"><strong>February 1861: Storm warning service</strong><br>• FitzRoy received weather reports produced by ships using reliable {instruments}<br>• simultaneous weather reports were taken daily<br>• storm warnings were telegraphed to  {ports }  along the shore<br>• signals for ships were displayed using raised { flags  }<br>• the storm warning service was the greatest development in sea safety since the  {lifeboat}   was introduced
<p><strong>August 1861: Public weather forecasting service</strong><br>• very popular in The Times newspaper<br>• frequently used by the English Queen for safe trips to a favourite { island  }<br>• FitzRoy’s forecasts were popular with fishermen but not with boat  {owners}<br>• in modern times FitzRoy’s  {name}   is used for a marine area<br>• FitzRoy produced a  {book }  which was respected by the scientific community</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. instruments</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “…FitzRoy’s innovation was to issue ships with standardised <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">instruments</strong> which allowed for accurate weather reports.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để có báo cáo chính xác, FitzRoy đã cung cấp cho các con tàu những thiết bị/dụng cụ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">instruments</strong>) đo đạc tiêu chuẩn thay vì để họ dùng các đồ dùng không đồng nhất.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. ports</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “…FitzRoy could telegraph warnings to <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">ports</strong> on the coast…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các cảnh báo về bão sắp tới được gửi bằng điện báo từ London đến các cảng biển (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">ports</strong>) dọc theo bờ biển để thông báo kịp thời cho tàu bè.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. flags</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “…where an ingenious system of <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">flags</strong> was hoisted up high for passing ships to read.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tại các cảng, người ta sử dụng một hệ thống các lá cờ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">flags</strong>) kéo lên cao để các tàu đi ngang qua có thể nhận diện tín hiệu nguy hiểm từ xa.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. lifeboat</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “This represented the biggest advance in shipping safety after the introduction of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">lifeboat</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hệ thống của FitzRoy được đánh giá là bước tiến quan trọng nhất trong an toàn hàng hải kể từ sau khi thuyền cứu sinh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">lifeboat</strong>) ra đời.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. island</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “…to get a forecast for the sea crossing over the Solent to an <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">island</strong> which she liked to visit…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nữ hoàng Anh thường xem dự báo để di chuyển an toàn đến hòn đảo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">island</strong>) yêu thích của bà ở lepas bờ biển phía Nam.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. owners</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “The <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">owners</strong> of fishing vessels, however, were not supportive of FitzRoy’s forecasts…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong khi ngư dân ủng hộ vì an toàn, thì các chủ tàu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">owners</strong>) lại ghét dự báo này vì nó thường làm trì hoãn lịch trình di chuyển của tàu, gây thiệt hại kinh tế.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. name</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> “…with the honour of an area of sea being given his <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">name</strong> in the shipping forecast…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để vinh danh FitzRoy, tên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">name</strong>) của ông đã được đặt cho một vùng biển trong các bản tin dự báo hàng hải hiện đại.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. book</strong>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,3,1\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> “…late in his life he published a <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">book</strong> about weather forecasting which was recognized by other scientists to be well ahead of its time.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cuối đời, ông đã để lại di sản là một cuốn sách (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">book</strong>) về dự báo thời tiết, tác phẩm được các nhà khoa học sau này thừa nhận là vượt xa thời đại bấy giờ.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0f70da23-f711-4ddc-aa69-c886b4a19555', '6724fea2-58e5-4d49-b6f5-e97ea571208f', 'fillup', 'Questions 5–8', '<p>Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 5–8 on your answer sheet.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>These days, museum visitors tend to be referred to as {customers}.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Museum curators now need {public relation skills} rather than academic qualifications.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The linking of a range of public institutions that entertain the public is known as {museology}.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>There is discussion about whether museums can be regarded in the same way as other {tourist attractions}.</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. These days, museum visitors tend to be referred to as {customers}. — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In addition, the visiting public have become known as <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">customers</strong> rather than visitors…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Referred to as” (được gọi là) đồng nghĩa với “become known as”. Bài đọc khẳng định công chúng đến thăm bảo tàng giờ đây được coi là khách hàng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">customers</strong>) thay vì chỉ là khách tham quan thông thường.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Museum curators now need {public relations skills} rather than academic qualifications. — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…being a museum director no longer requires an Arts degree—but <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">public relations skills</strong> are essential if the museum is going to compete…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Academic qualifications” (bằng cấp học thuật) ở đây tương ứng với “Arts degree”. Ngược lại, kỹ năng quan hệ công chúng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">public relations skills</strong>) lại trở nên thiết yếu (essential/need) trong bối cảnh cạnh tranh hiện nay.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. The linking of a range of public institutions that entertain the public is known as {museology}. — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The convergence of museums, the heritage industry, tourism, profit-making, and pleasure-giving has resulted in the new <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">‘museology.’</strong>“</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “The linking of a range of public institutions” (Sự liên kết/hội tụ của các tổ chức công) chính là cụm “The convergence of museums, heritage industry…”. Kết quả của sự hội tụ này được gọi là tân bảo tàng học (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"223\">museology</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. There is discussion about whether museums can be regarded in the same way as other {tourist attractions}. — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“This has given rise to much debate about whether it is appropriate to see museums primarily as <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">tourist attractions</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Discussion” (thảo luận) tương ứng với “debate” (tranh luận). Câu hỏi đang đặt ra là liệu có phù hợp hay không khi xem bảo tàng như là các điểm thu hút khách du lịch (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"179\">tourist attractions</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0522a3e6-89cf-4a94-a4c7-404a01d23f76', 'bbf91301-5bb1-4a15-8465-c0a0f209930a', 'radio', 'Questions 37–40', '', '<p id="p-rc_61cc019b7715c22d-152" data-path-to-node="16,0,0"><span class="citation-17214">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="16,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-17214">YES</span></strong><span class="citation-17214 citation-end-17214"> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer,<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="139"><!----></sup></span><strong data-path-to-node="16,1,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-17213">NO</span></strong><span class="citation-17213"> if the statement cont</span><span class="citation-17212 citation-17213 citation-end-17213">radicts the <sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="140"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-17212 citation-end-17212">claims of the writer,<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="141"><!----></sup></span><strong data-path-to-node="16,2,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-17211">NOT GIVEN</span></strong><span class="citation-17211 citation-end-17211"> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="142"><!----></sup></span></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Campaigns designed to correct misinformation will fail to achieve their purpose if people are unable to understand them."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Attempts to teach elementary school students about misinformation have been opposed."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It may be possible to overcome the problem of misinformation in a relatively short period."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The need to keep up with new information is hugely exaggerated in today’s world."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Campaigns designed to correct misinformation will fail to achieve their purpose if people are unable to understand them. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"For corrective campaigns to be persuasive, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">audiences need to be able to comprehend them</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Persuasive\" (có tính thuyết phục/thành công) đòi hỏi khán giả phải \"comprehend\" (hiểu/lĩnh hội) được thông điệp. Nếu không hiểu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"142\">unable to understand</strong>), các chiến dịch này sẽ không đạt được mục đích (fail to achieve their purpose).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Attempts to teach elementary school students about misinformation have been opposed. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"That some audiences might be unaware of the potential for misinformation also suggests the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">utility of media literacy efforts as early as elementary school</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả có nhắc đến sự hữu ích (utility) của việc dạy về tin giả ngay từ cấp tiểu học. Tuy nhiên, bài đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến việc các nỗ lực này có bị phản đối (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"174\">opposed</strong>) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. It may be possible to overcome the problem of misinformation in a relatively short period. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"The journey forward undoubtedly will be a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">long and arduous one</strong>... we will need coordinated efforts <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">over time</strong>, rather than any singular <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"156\">one-time panacea</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định hành trình phía trước rất dài và gian nan (long and arduous), cần nỗ lực bền bỉ theo thời gian, chứ không phải là một giải pháp tức thời hay trong thời gian ngắn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"194\">short period</strong>). Thông tin này trái ngược hoàn toàn với câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. The need to keep up with new information is hugely exaggerated in today’s world. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Misinformation arises as a result of human fallibility and <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">human information needs</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả có nhắc đến nhu cầu thông tin của con người (human information needs) là một trong những nguyên nhân phát sinh tin giả. Tuy nhiên, bài đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">không hề đưa ra nhận định</strong> liệu nhu cầu này có đang bị thổi phồng quá mức (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"233\">exaggerated</strong>) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('44834889-d842-4c39-bf9c-4c673c582e0e', 'f7d78399-9bb7-430b-9bf4-d4a2e260e48c', 'matching', ' Questions 14-20', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has seven paragraphs.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct number, <strong>i-x</strong>, in boxes <strong>14-20.</strong></p>
<p><strong>List of Headings</strong></p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i Why it is necessary to explain the meaning of the word celebrity"}, {"optionText": "ii The influence of non-human celebrities on societies"}, {"optionText": "iii The impact of broadcasting on concepts of celebrity"}, {"optionText": "iv Creativity having greater value"}, {"optionText": "v Admiration for physical achievement"}, {"optionText": "vi The advantages of celebrity status in the ancient world"}, {"optionText": "vii A result of hardship"}, {"optionText": "viii Literacy and widespread celebrity"}, {"optionText": "ix Attitudes of celebrities towards the media"}, {"optionText": "x The original definition of celebrity"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Paragraph 1: [x] The original definition of celebrity</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Từ khóa:</strong> “roots” (nguồn gốc), “derived from the Latin word” (bắt nguồn từ từ Latin), “meaning” (ý nghĩa).</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này giải thích nguồn gốc ngôn ngữ học của từ “celebrity” và ý nghĩa ban đầu của nó trong lịch sử.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Paragraph 2: [ii] The influence of non-human celebrities on societies</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Từ khóa:</strong> “deities” (thần linh), “immortals” (những vị thần bất tử), “myths” (thần thoại).</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Non-human” (không phải con người) ở đây chính là các vị thần Hy Lạp và La Mã. Xã hội cổ đại coi thần linh là những đối tượng nổi tiếng đầu tiên và theo dõi đời tư của họ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Paragraph 3: [v] Admiration for physical achievement</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Từ khóa:</strong> “athletes” (vận động viên), “Olympic Games”, “gladiators” (võ sĩ giác đấu), “superhuman strength” (sức mạnh siêu phàm).</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Physical achievement” (thành tựu thể chất) ám chỉ sức mạnh và khả năng thi đấu của các vận động viên và võ sĩ cổ đại.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Paragraph 4: [vii] A result of hardship</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Từ khóa:</strong> “Dark Ages” (Thời kỳ Đen tối), “war, disease and food shortages” (chiến tranh, dịch bệnh và thiếu đói), “little else to be excited about”.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong thời kỳ khó khăn (hardship), con người không còn gì để giải trí nên họ tìm thấy sự phấn khích từ cuộc đời của các nhân vật tôn giáo.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Paragraph 5: [iv] Creativity having greater value</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Từ khóa:</strong> “Renaissance” (Thời Phục hưng), “appreciation for the arts” (trân trọng nghệ thuật), “artists” (nghệ sĩ).</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thời kỳ này, sự sáng tạo (creativity) được đề cao, khiến các nghệ sĩ trở nên nổi tiếng hơn cả giới chính trị hay tôn giáo.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Paragraph 6: [viii] Literacy and widespread celebrity</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Từ khóa:</strong> “publishing” (ngành in ấn), “people who could read” (những người biết đọc), “newspapers” (báo chí), “spread further” (lan rộng hơn).</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhờ việc người dân biết chữ (literacy) và công nghệ in ấn phát triển, sự nổi tiếng mới có thể lan rộng (widespread) trên phạm vi toàn cầu.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Paragraph 7: [iii] The impact of broadcasting on concepts of celebrity</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Từ khóa:</strong> “radio”, “film”, “television” (truyền hình), “broadcast” (phát sóng), “reality television”.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các phương tiện phát sóng (broadcasting) đã thay đổi định nghĩa về sự nổi tiếng: từ việc phải có tài năng sang việc chỉ cần có ngoại hình và xuất hiện trên truyền hình thực tế.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e29157d1-3ddc-4a59-89f9-c178bbc55ab5', 'f7d78399-9bb7-430b-9bf4-d4a2e260e48c', 'matrix', 'Questions 21-23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following statements (Questions 21-23) and the list of historical periods Europe below.</p>
<p>Choose each statement with the correct historical period, <strong>А</strong>, <strong>В</strong>, <strong>C</strong> or <strong>D</strong>.</p>', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of options", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "A wide variety of people achieve a brief period of fame.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": " Stories are invented about celebrities’ lives.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "The fame of rulers is starting to diminish.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Ancient times", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Dark Ages", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Renaissance", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Modern era", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. A wide variety of people achieve a brief period of fame. (Nhiều đối tượng khác nhau đạt được sự nổi tiếng trong thời gian ngắn).</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">D. Modern era</strong> (Kỷ nguyên hiện đại).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> “The emergence of reality television shows… allowed <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">all kinds of people</strong> with little ability to enjoy a <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">short burst of fame</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> * “A wide variety of people” đồng nghĩa với “all kinds of people”.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,0,0\">“Brief period of fame” đồng nghĩa với “short burst of fame”.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,1,1,0\">Sự xuất hiện của truyền hình thực tế trong kỷ nguyên hiện đại cho phép bất kỳ ai cũng có thể nổi tiếng chớp nhoáng mà không cần tài năng xuất chúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Stories are invented about celebrities’ lives. (Những câu chuyện được thêu dệt về đời tư của người nổi tiếng).</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">A. Ancient times</strong> (Thời cổ đại).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> “The celebrities of the ancient world were the powerful and awesome <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">deities</strong>… This need to know led to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">creation of myths</strong>, which personalized the gods and involved them in ancient celebrity scandals…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,1,0,0\">“Stories are invented” chính là việc “creation of myths” (sáng tạo ra các câu thần thoại).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,1,1,0\">Thời cổ đại, người dân tò mò về đời tư của các vị thần (non-human celebrities) nên đã thêu dệt nên các câu chuyện thần thoại xoay quanh những scandal của họ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. The fame of rulers is starting to diminish. (Sự nổi tiếng của những nhà cầm quyền bắt đầu giảm bớt).</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">C. Renaissance</strong> (Thời kỳ Phục hưng).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> “During… the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">Renaissance</strong> period as it is known, <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">interest in ruling figures faded</strong>… artists began to surpass political and religious individuals…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,0,0\">“Rulers” đồng nghĩa với “ruling figures” (các nhà cầm quyền).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,1,0\">“Diminish” (giảm bớt) đồng nghĩa với “faded” (phai nhạt dần).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,1,2,0\">Ở thời Phục hưng, người dân bắt đầu bớt quan tâm đến các nhà vua, chính trị gia và chuyển sang hâm mộ các nghệ sĩ sáng tạo.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9c2bb6e2-988c-4dab-b10d-6b864b29a951', 'f7d78399-9bb7-430b-9bf4-d4a2e260e48c', 'fillup', 'Questions 24-26', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the passage for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>Celebrities achieve a global status</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">The development of the publishing industry in the 1700s signalled the beginning of international fame. A growing number of people could read, which meant they had the chance to become informed about their favourite figures by reading {newspapers.}</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">This exposure to celebrities expanded further when radio and television became popular, and it was mass media attention that resulted in higher status and fame for some celebrities. The recent rise of reality television has also meant that a person’s {appearance}<strong> </strong>rather than their talent can bring fame. With this type of television programme, fame may be entirely dependent on the response of the {audience}<strong>.</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. …reading {newspapers}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> “Suddenly, the lives of authors, politicians, war heroes, and other celebrities could now be read about in <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">newspapers</strong> around the world.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ ra rằng khi tỉ lệ người biết đọc tăng lên và công nghệ in ấn phát triển vào thế kỷ 18, công chúng có thể tìm hiểu thông tin chi tiết về thần tượng của họ thông qua việc đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">báo chí (newspapers)</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. …person’s {appearance} rather than their talent can bring fame</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> “The emergence of reality television shows… allowed all kinds of people with little ability to enjoy a short burst of fame… All you needed, it seemed, was an attractive <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"193\">appearance</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong kỷ nguyên truyền hình thực tế, tài năng hay khả năng đặc biệt (“talent” / “ability”) không còn là yếu tố quan trọng nhất. Thay vào đó, chỉ cần một ngoại hình (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"177\">appearance</strong>) bắt mắt là đủ để trở nên nổi tiếng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. …entirely dependent on the response of the {audience}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> “Today, reality television programmers make it possible to be famous… simply for being, with the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"119\">audience</strong> deciding whether someone deserves to become a celebrity or not.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khác với sự nổi tiếng dựa trên thành tựu thực tế, sự nổi tiếng từ truyền hình thực tế hiện nay phụ thuộc hoàn toàn vào phản ứng và quyết định của <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">khán giả (audience)</strong> — những người bình chọn hoặc quan tâm đến sự hiện diện của người đó.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cd894ef5-07b2-4fa7-84cc-a250615e8798', '9c785f96-eb67-439a-b7ea-d01f8f297493', 'fillup', 'Questions 18–22', '<p data-start="72" data-end="105">Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p data-start="107" data-end="165">Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="171" data-end="280">The stormwater-management programme in Miami Beach has involved the installation of efficient {pumps}.</p>
<p data-start="286" data-end="402">The construction of {dams} was the first stage of a project to ensure the success of mangroves in Indonesia.</p>
<p data-start="408" data-end="544">As a response to rising floodwaters in the Mekong Delta, a not-for-profit organisation has been building houses that can {float  }.</p>
<p data-start="550" data-end="690">Rising sea levels in Bangladesh have made it necessary to introduce various {crops} that are suitable for areas of high salt content.</p>
<p data-start="696" data-end="777" data-is-last-node="">A project in LA has increased the number of {trees} on the city’s streets.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>18. pumps<br />(Đoạn: “&#8230;the city has set up new pumps that can remove up to 75,000 litres of water per minute.”)<br />→ Chương trình quản lý nước mưa ở Miami lắp đặt pumps (máy bơm hiệu quả). → pumps.</p>\n<p> <br />19. dams<br />(Đoạn: “&#8230;building semi-permeable dams, made from bamboo poles and brushwood, to mimic the role of mangrove roots…”)<br />→ Giai đoạn đầu của dự án trồng rừng ngập mặn là xây dựng dams (đập bán thấm). → dams.</p>\n<p> <br />20. float<br />(Đoạn: “&#8230;building houses that can float.”)<br />→ Tổ chức phi lợi nhuận xây nhà có thể nổi để thích ứng với ngập lụt ở đồng bằng Mekong. → float.</p>\n<p> <br />21. crops<br />(Đoạn: “&#8230;cultivating naturally salt-tolerant crops in the region.”)<br />→ Ở Bangladesh, họ đưa vào các loại cây trồng (crops) chịu mặn cao. → crops.</p>\n<p> <br />22. trees<br />(Đoạn: “&#8230;the planting of trees and the installation of a ‘cool pavement’ system&#8230;”)<br />→ Dự án ở LA giúp tăng số lượng cây xanh (trees) trên đường phố. → trees.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('034ac464-8b09-42b7-9b7c-0dc76ab1fddb', 'df332c92-4c48-41fb-ace5-f8a71801e0cc', 'radio', 'Questions 38-40', '', '<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Choose<strong> YES i</strong>f the statement agrees with the claims of the writer <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</span></p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The termite mound appears to process its refuse material internally."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Dr Soar’s reconstruction involves scanning a single photograph of a complete mound into acomputer."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "New information about termite architecture could help people deal with future energy crises."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('eda55a24-0506-4f1b-ac1b-4d1c5173da5c', 'bf21653d-4ada-4141-af4b-aca8e4c705fe', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–6', '<p data-start="107" data-end="205">Write <strong data-start="160" data-end="188">ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="107" data-end="205"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Guitar Group</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="230" data-end="262">Coordinator: Gary {Mathieson}</p>
<p data-start="264" data-end="285">Level: {beginners}</p>
<p data-start="287" data-end="367">Place: – the  {college}<br data-start="310" data-end="313">   – {New} Street<br data-start="336" data-end="339">   – First floor, Room T347</p>
<p data-start="369" data-end="409">Time: Thursday morning at {11}</p>
<p data-start="411" data-end="460">Recommended website: ‘The perfect 6 {instrument}’</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"170\" data-end=\"749\"><strong data-start=\"170\" data-end=\"180\">WOMAN:</strong> Hi Coleman, how are you?<br data-start=\"205\" data-end=\"208\"><strong data-start=\"208\" data-end=\"220\">COLEMAN:</strong> Good, thanks.<br data-start=\"234\" data-end=\"237\"><strong data-start=\"237\" data-end=\"247\">WOMAN:</strong> I wanted to have a chat with you because our friend Josh told me that you’ve joined a guitar group and it sounds interesting. I’d really like to learn to play.<br data-start=\"407\" data-end=\"410\"><strong data-start=\"410\" data-end=\"422\">COLEMAN:</strong> Why don’t you come along? I’m sure there’s room for another person.<br data-start=\"490\" data-end=\"493\"><strong data-start=\"493\" data-end=\"503\">WOMAN:</strong> Really? So – who runs the classes?<br data-start=\"538\" data-end=\"541\"><strong data-start=\"541\" data-end=\"553\">COLEMAN:</strong> He’s called a ‘coordinator’ – his name’s Gary <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(1) Mathieson.</strong></span><br data-start=\"610\" data-end=\"613\" data-is-only-node=\"\"><strong data-start=\"613\" data-end=\"623\">WOMAN:</strong> Let me note that down. Gary… How do you spell his surname?<br data-start=\"682\" data-end=\"685\"><strong data-start=\"685\" data-end=\"697\">COLEMAN:</strong> It’s M-A-T-H-I-E-S-O-N.<br data-start=\"721\" data-end=\"724\"><strong data-start=\"724\" data-end=\"734\">WOMAN:</strong> Right, thanks.</p>\n<p data-start=\"170\" data-end=\"749\"><strong data-start=\"756\" data-end=\"768\">COLEMAN:</strong> He’s retired, actually, but he’s a really nice guy and he used to play in a lot of bands.<br data-start=\"858\" data-end=\"861\"><strong data-start=\"861\" data-end=\"871\">WOMAN:</strong> Thanks. So how long have you been going?<br data-start=\"912\" data-end=\"915\"><strong data-start=\"915\" data-end=\"927\">COLEMAN:</strong> About a month now.<br data-start=\"946\" data-end=\"949\"><strong data-start=\"949\" data-end=\"959\">WOMAN:</strong> And could you play anything before you started?<br data-start=\"1007\" data-end=\"1010\"><strong data-start=\"1010\" data-end=\"1022\">COLEMAN:</strong> I knew a few chords, but that’s all.<br data-start=\"1059\" data-end=\"1062\"><strong data-start=\"1062\" data-end=\"1072\">WOMAN:</strong> I’m sure everyone will be better than me.<br data-start=\"1114\" data-end=\"1117\" data-is-only-node=\"\"><strong data-start=\"1117\" data-end=\"1129\">COLEMAN:</strong> That’s what I thought, too. When I first spoke to Gary on the phone, he said it was a class for <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(2) beginners</strong></span>, but I was still worried that everyone would be better than me, but we were all equally hopeless!<br data-start=\"1333\" data-end=\"1336\"><strong data-start=\"1336\" data-end=\"1346\">WOMAN:</strong> Oh, that’s reassuring. So where do you meet?<br data-start=\"1391\" data-end=\"1394\"><strong data-start=\"1394\" data-end=\"1406\">COLEMAN:</strong> Well, when I joined the group, they were meeting in Gary’s home, but as the group got bigger, he decided to book a room at the<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (3) college</strong></span> in town. I prefer going there.<br data-start=\"1572\" data-end=\"1575\"><strong data-start=\"1575\" data-end=\"1585\">WOMAN:</strong> I know that place. I used to go to tap dancing classes there when I was at secondary school. I haven’t been since, though, and I can’t remember what road it’s in… is it Lock Street?<br data-start=\"1767\" data-end=\"1770\"><strong data-start=\"1770\" data-end=\"1782\">COLEMAN:</strong> It’s just beyond there at the bottom of <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(4) New</span></strong> Street near the city roundabout.<br data-start=\"1859\" data-end=\"1862\"><strong data-start=\"1862\" data-end=\"1872\">WOMAN:</strong> Yes, of course.<br data-start=\"1888\" data-end=\"1891\"><strong data-start=\"1891\" data-end=\"1903\">COLEMAN:</strong> The guitar club is on the first floor in Room 1347.<br data-start=\"1955\" data-end=\"1958\"><strong data-start=\"1958\" data-end=\"1968\">WOMAN:</strong> Right. And when do you meet? Is it at the weekend?<br data-start=\"2019\" data-end=\"2022\"><strong data-start=\"2022\" data-end=\"2034\">COLEMAN:</strong> We meet on Thursdays. It used to be 10.30 and that suited me well, but now we meet at <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(5) 11</span></strong>. The class that’s in there before us asked if they could have the room for another 30 minutes.<br data-start=\"2218\" data-end=\"2221\"><strong data-start=\"2221\" data-end=\"2231\">WOMAN:</strong> Oh, I see. Well, I’d love to come, but I don’t have a guitar.<br data-start=\"2293\" data-end=\"2296\"><strong data-start=\"2296\" data-end=\"2308\">COLEMAN:</strong> Well, you can always buy a second-hand one. There’s a website called ‘The Perfect <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(6) Instrument</span></strong>’ that sells all kinds of guitars, violins and so on. I’m sure you’ll find something there.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2499\" data-end=\"3789\"><strong data-start=\"2499\" data-end=\"2509\">WOMAN:</strong> So what’s a typical lesson like with Gary?<br data-start=\"2552\" data-end=\"2555\"><strong data-start=\"2555\" data-end=\"2567\">COLEMAN:</strong> Well, he always starts by getting us to tune our guitars. That takes about five minutes.<br data-start=\"2656\" data-end=\"2659\"><strong data-start=\"2659\" data-end=\"2669\">WOMAN:</strong> Uhuh.<br data-start=\"2675\" data-end=\"2678\"><strong data-start=\"2678\" data-end=\"2690\">COLEMAN:</strong> Some people have an app they use, but others do it by <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(7) ear</strong></span>. Gary goes round and helps them. And while he’s doing that, he tells us what he’s going to do during the lesson.<br data-start=\"2861\" data-end=\"2864\"><strong data-start=\"2864\" data-end=\"2874\">WOMAN:</strong> Right.<br data-start=\"2881\" data-end=\"2884\"><strong data-start=\"2884\" data-end=\"2896\">COLEMAN:</strong> First, we usually spend about ten minutes doing some strumming.<br data-start=\"2960\" data-end=\"2963\" data-is-only-node=\"\"><strong data-start=\"2963\" data-end=\"2973\">WOMAN:</strong> So is that using… what are they called… plectrums?<br data-start=\"3024\" data-end=\"3027\"><strong data-start=\"3027\" data-end=\"3039\">COLEMAN:</strong> No – we just use our thumbs.<br data-start=\"3068\" data-end=\"3071\"><strong data-start=\"3071\" data-end=\"3081\">WOMAN:</strong> Much easier.<br data-start=\"3094\" data-end=\"3097\"><strong data-start=\"3097\" data-end=\"3109\">COLEMAN:</strong> Gary reminds us where to put our fingers for each chord and then we play them together. Sometimes we all just start laughing because we’re so bad at keeping time, so Gary starts <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(8) clapping</span></strong> to help us.<br data-start=\"3308\" data-end=\"3311\"><strong data-start=\"3311\" data-end=\"3321\">WOMAN:</strong> Do you learn to play any songs?<br data-start=\"3353\" data-end=\"3356\"><strong data-start=\"3356\" data-end=\"3368\">COLEMAN:</strong> Yes – we do at least one song with words and chords. I mean that’s harder than you think.<br data-start=\"3458\" data-end=\"3461\"><strong data-start=\"3461\" data-end=\"3471\">WOMAN:</strong> Oh, I’m sure it is!<br data-start=\"3491\" data-end=\"3494\"><strong data-start=\"3494\" data-end=\"3506\">COLEMAN:</strong> That part of the lesson takes about 15 minutes. He often brings a<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (9) recording</strong></span> of the song and plays it to us first. Then he hands out the song and if there’s a new chord in it, we practise that before we play it together – but really slowly.<br data-start=\"3746\" data-end=\"3749\"><strong data-start=\"3749\" data-end=\"3759\">WOMAN:</strong> Do you do any finger picking?</p>\n<p data-start=\"130\" data-end=\"790\"><strong data-start=\"130\" data-end=\"142\">COLEMAN:</strong> That’s the last ten minutes of the lesson, when we pick out the individual notes from a tune he’s made up. It’s always quite simple.<br data-start=\"275\" data-end=\"278\"><strong data-start=\"278\" data-end=\"288\">WOMAN:</strong> That must be hard, though.<br data-start=\"315\" data-end=\"318\"><strong data-start=\"318\" data-end=\"330\">COLEMAN:</strong> It is, but people like it because they can really concentrate and if we’re all playing well, it sounds quite impressive. The only trouble is that sometimes gets us to play one at a time – you know, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(10) alone.</strong></span><br data-start=\"535\" data-end=\"538\"><strong data-start=\"538\" data-end=\"548\">WOMAN:</strong> That’s scary.<br data-start=\"562\" data-end=\"565\" data-is-only-node=\"\"><strong data-start=\"565\" data-end=\"577\">COLEMAN:</strong> It is, but I’ve got used to it now. At the end he spends about five minutes telling us what to practise for the following week.<br data-start=\"705\" data-end=\"708\"><strong data-start=\"708\" data-end=\"718\">WOMAN:</strong> Well, thanks Coleman. I’ll go and have a look at that website, I think.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a571694d-75ed-4feb-9583-c80a5d00c358', 'bf21653d-4ada-4141-af4b-aca8e4c705fe', 'fillup', 'Questions 7–10', '<p>Complete the table below.<br data-start="126" data-end="129">Write <strong data-start="135" data-end="152">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 2px; width: 90.0965%; height: 427.031px; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);" border="1">
<thead>
<tr style="height: 61.375px;">
<th style="border-color: #000000; width: 24.3349%;">
<p>Time</p>
</th>
<th style="border-color: #000000; width: 31.1686%;">
<p>Activity</p>
</th>
<th style="border-color: #000000; width: 44.5028%;">
<p>Notes</p>
</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 61.375px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 24.3349%;">
<p>5 minutes</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 31.1686%;">
<p>tuning guitars</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 44.5028%;">
<p>using an app or by {ear}</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 80.9688px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 24.3349%;">
<p>10 minutes</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 31.1686%;">
<p>strumming chords using our thumbs</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 44.5028%;">
<p>keeping time while the teacher is<strong> </strong>{clapping}</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 61.375px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 24.3349%;">
<p>15 minutes</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 31.1686%;">
<p>playing songs</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 44.5028%;">
<p>often listening to a<strong> </strong>{recording} of a song</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 80.9688px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 24.3349%;">
<p>10 minutes</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 31.1686%;">
<p>playing single notes and simple tunes</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 44.5028%;">
<p>playing together, then<strong> </strong>{alone}</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 80.9688px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 24.3349%;">
<p>5 minutes</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 31.1686%;">
<p>noting things to practise at home</p>
</td>
<td style="border-color: #000000; width: 44.5028%;"> </td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('780686e8-7ea9-4839-8e95-6ca8712e580e', 'b6f4eafe-b628-406b-826a-ee9ebda141c8', 'radio', 'Questions 11–16', '', '<p data-start="129" data-end="188">Choose the correct letter, A, B or C.</p>
<p data-section-id="1bytfpe" data-start="195" data-end="234"><strong data-start="199" data-end="234">Working as a lifeboat volunteer</strong></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. He was eager to develop a hobby."}, {"option_text": "B. He wanted to work shorter hours."}, {"option_text": "C. He found his job in website design unsatisfying."}], "question": "What made David leave London and move to Northsea?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. a local organisation."}, {"option_text": "B. a local resident."}, {"option_text": "C. the local council."}], "question": "The Lifeboat Institution in Northsea was built with money provided by"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. might be colour blind."}, {"option_text": "B. was rather short-sighted."}, {"option_text": "C. had undergone eye surgery."}], "question": "In his health assessment, the doctor was concerned about the fact that David"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. five minutes."}, {"option_text": "B. six to eight minutes."}, {"option_text": "C. eight and a half minutes."}], "question": "After arriving at the lifeboat station, they aim to launch the boat within "}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. who will be the members of his crew."}, {"option_text": "B. what equipment it will be necessary to take."}, {"option_text": "C. if the lifeboat should be launched."}], "question": "As a ‘helmsman’, David has the responsibility of deciding"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. gives talks on safety at sea."}, {"option_text": "B. helps with fundraising."}, {"option_text": "C. recruits new volunteers."}], "question": "As well as going out on the lifeboat, David"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"150\" data-end=\"593\">I never really planned to be a lifeboat volunteer when I came to live in Northsea. I’d been working in London as a website designer, but although that was interesting, I didn’t like city life.<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (11) I’d been really keen on boats as a teenager, and I thought if I went to live by the sea, I might be able to pursue that interest a bit more in my free time.</strong></span> Then I found that the lifeboat institution was looking for volunteers, so I decided to apply.</p>\n<p data-start=\"595\" data-end=\"968\">The lifeboat institution building here in Northsea’s hard to miss, it’s one of the largest in the country. It was built 15 years ago with <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(12) funds provided by a generous member of the public who’d lived here all her life</span></strong>. As the lifeboat institution is a charity that relies on that kind of donation, rather than funding provided by the government, that was a huge help to us.</p>\n<p data-start=\"970\" data-end=\"1308\">When I applied, I had to have a health assessment. The doctors were particularly interested in my vision. I used to be short-sighted, so I had to wear glasses, but I’d had laser eye surgery two years earlier so that was OK. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(13) They gave me tests for colour blindness and they thought I might have a problem there, </span></strong>but it turned out I was OK.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1310\" data-end=\"1655\">When the coastguard gets an alert, all the volunteers are contacted and rush to the lifeboat station. Our target’s to get there in five minutes, then <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(14) we try to get the boat off the dock and out to sea in another six to eight minutes</strong></span>. Our team’s proud that we usually achieve that – the average time across the country’s eight and a half minutes.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1657\" data-end=\"2058\">I’ve recently qualified as what’s called a ‘helmsman’, which means I have the ultimate responsibility for the lifeboat. I have to check that the equipment we use is in working order – the crew have special life jackets that can support up to four people in the water. And <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(15) it’s ultimately my decision whether it’s safe to launch the boat.</strong></span> But it’s very rare not to launch it, even in the worst weather.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2060\" data-end=\"2475\">As well as going out on the lifeboat, my work involves other things too. A lot of people underestimate how quickly conditions can change at sea, so <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(16) I speak to youth groups and sailing clubs in the area about the sorts of problems that sailors and swimmers can have </strong></span>if the weather suddenly gets bad. We also have a lot of volunteers who organise activities to raise money for us, and we couldn’t manage without them.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2477\" data-end=\"3117\">The training we get is a continuous process, focusing on technical competence and safe handling techniques, <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(17) and it’s given me the confidence to deal with extreme situations without panicking</span></strong>. I was glad I’d done a first aid course before I started, as that’s a big help with the casualty care activities we do. We’ve done a lot on how to deal with ropes and tie knots – that’s an essential skill. After a year, I did a one-week residential course, led by specialists. They had a wave-tank where they could create extreme weather conditions – so <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(18) we could get experience at what to do if the boat turned over in a storm at night, for example.</span></strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"3124\" data-end=\"3195\">Since I started, I’ve had to deal with a range of emergency situations.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3197\" data-end=\"3730\">But the work’s hugely motivating. It’s not just about saving lives – I’ve learned a lot about the technology involved. My background in IT’s been useful here, and I can use my expertise to help other volunteers.<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong> (19) They’re a great group – we’re like a family really,</strong></span> which helps when you’re dragging yourself out of bed on a cold stormy night. But actually,<strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> (20) it’s the colder months that can be the most rewarding time</span></strong>. That’s when the incidents tend to be more serious, and you realise that you can make a huge difference to the outcome.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3732\" data-end=\"3774\">So if any of you listeners are interested…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3a308f36-ace3-4178-b9a7-b426cb1f27c6', 'b6f4eafe-b628-406b-826a-ee9ebda141c8', 'checkbox', 'Questions 17 and 18', '', '<p data-start="554" data-end="582">Choose <strong data-start="561" data-end="568">TWO</strong> letters, A–E.</p>
<p data-start="584" data-end="660">Which <strong data-start="590" data-end="597">TWO</strong> things does David find most motivating about the work he does?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A. working as part of a team"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. experiences when working in winter"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C. being thanked by those he has helped"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D. the fact that it keeps him fit"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "E. the chance to develop new equipment"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('62def40f-6831-4850-8509-feb0c074d582', 'b6f4eafe-b628-406b-826a-ee9ebda141c8', 'checkbox', 'Questions 19 and 20', '', '<p data-start="554" data-end="582">Choose <strong data-start="561" data-end="568">TWO</strong> letters, A–E.</p>
<p data-start="584" data-end="660">Which <strong data-start="590" data-end="597">TWO</strong> things does David find most motivating about the work he does?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "A. working as part of a team"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "B. experiences when working in winter"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "C. being thanked by those he has helped"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "D. the fact that it keeps him fit"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E. the chance to develop new equipment"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0d058fef-d18c-4a93-ba41-34ee68a4614a', 'bd926770-044b-433e-9496-4b7bcae6fd23', 'radio', 'Questions 21–24', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>or <strong>C</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. limited in scope."}, {"option_text": "B. hard to research."}, {"option_text": "C. boring for listeners."}], "question": "At first, Don thought the topic of recycling footwear might be too"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. how popular they are among young people."}, {"option_text": "B. how suitable they are for school."}, {"option_text": "C. how quickly they wear out."}], "question": "When discussing trainers, Bella and Don disagree about"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. they no longer fit."}, {"option_text": "B. she no longer likes them."}, {"option_text": "C. they are no longer in fashion."}], "question": "Bella says that she sometimes recycles shoes because"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. Public consumption of footwear has risen."}, {"option_text": "B. Less footwear is recycled now than in the past."}, {"option_text": "C. People dispose of more footwear than they used to."}], "question": "What did the article say that confused Don?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"133\" data-end=\"2103\"><strong data-start=\"133\" data-end=\"143\">BELLA:</strong> Hi Don – did you get the copy of the article on recycling footwear that I emailed you?<br data-start=\"230\" data-end=\"233\"><strong data-start=\"233\" data-end=\"241\">DON:</strong> Yes – it’s here… I’ve had a look at it.<br data-start=\"281\" data-end=\"284\"><strong data-start=\"284\" data-end=\"294\">BELLA:</strong> So do you think it’s a good topic for our presentation?<br data-start=\"350\" data-end=\"353\"><strong data-start=\"353\" data-end=\"361\">DON:</strong> Well, before I started reading, I thought recycling footwear, well, although it’s quite interesting, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(21) perhaps there isn’t enough to say about it,</strong></span> cos we put shoes in recycling bins, they go to charity shops and that’s about it.<br data-start=\"588\" data-end=\"591\"><strong data-start=\"591\" data-end=\"601\">BELLA:</strong> …but there’s much more to it than that.<br data-start=\"641\" data-end=\"644\"><strong data-start=\"644\" data-end=\"652\">DON:</strong> I realise that now and I’m keen to research the topic more.<br data-start=\"712\" data-end=\"715\"><strong data-start=\"715\" data-end=\"725\">BELLA:</strong> That’s great.<br data-start=\"739\" data-end=\"742\" data-is-only-node=\"\"><strong data-start=\"742\" data-end=\"750\">DON:</strong> One of the things I didn’t realise until I read the article was just how many pairs of trainers get recycled!<br data-start=\"860\" data-end=\"863\"><strong data-start=\"863\" data-end=\"873\">BELLA:</strong> Well, a lot of young people wear them all the time now. They’ve become more popular than ordinary shoes.<br data-start=\"978\" data-end=\"981\"><strong data-start=\"981\" data-end=\"989\">DON:</strong> I know. I guess they are very hard-wearing, but <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(22) don’t they look a bit casual for school uniform? I don’t think they’re right for that.</span></strong><br data-start=\"1124\" data-end=\"1127\"><strong data-start=\"1127\" data-end=\"1137\">BELLA:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>Actually, I think some of them look quite smart on pupils</strong></span>… better than a scruffy old pair of shoes.<br data-start=\"1237\" data-end=\"1240\"><strong data-start=\"1240\" data-end=\"1248\">DON:</strong> So do you keep shoes a long time?<br data-start=\"1282\" data-end=\"1285\"><strong data-start=\"1285\" data-end=\"1295\">BELLA:</strong> Yes, though I do tend to wear my old pairs for doing dirty jobs like cleaning the house.<br data-start=\"1384\" data-end=\"1387\"><strong data-start=\"1387\" data-end=\"1395\">DON:</strong> I must admit, I’ve <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(23) recycled some perfectly good shoes, that haven’t gone out of fashion and still fit, just because they don’t look great on me any more</strong></span>. That’s awful isn’t it?<br data-start=\"1572\" data-end=\"1575\"><strong data-start=\"1575\" data-end=\"1585\">BELLA:</strong> I think it’s common because there’s so much choice. The article did say that recent sales of footwear have increased enormously.<br data-start=\"1714\" data-end=\"1717\"><strong data-start=\"1717\" data-end=\"1725\">DON:</strong> That didn’t surprise me.<br data-start=\"1750\" data-end=\"1753\"><strong data-start=\"1753\" data-end=\"1763\">BELLA:</strong> No. But then it said that <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(24) the amount of recycled footwear has falle</strong>n. It’s 6 per cent now compared to a previous level of 11 per cent. That doesn’t seem to make sense.</span><br data-start=\"1931\" data-end=\"1934\"><strong data-start=\"1934\" data-end=\"1942\">DON:</strong> That’s because not everything goes through the recycling process. Some footwear just isn’t good enough to re-sell, for one reason or another, and gets rejected.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2110\" data-end=\"2637\"><strong data-start=\"2110\" data-end=\"2120\">BELLA:</strong> So let’s find some examples in the article of footwear that was rejected for recycling. OK. I think there are some in the interview with the recycling manager. Yeah – here it is.<br data-start=\"2299\" data-end=\"2302\"><strong data-start=\"2302\" data-end=\"2310\">DON:</strong> Hmm. Let’s start with the ladies’ high-heeled shoes. What did he say about those?<br data-start=\"2392\" data-end=\"2395\"><strong data-start=\"2395\" data-end=\"2405\">BELLA:</strong> He said they were probably expensive – the material was suede and they were being in colour – it looked like someone had only worn them once, but in a very wet field so <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(25) the heels were too stained with mud and grass to re-sell them.</span></strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"2644\" data-end=\"3512\"><strong data-start=\"2644\" data-end=\"2654\">BELLA:</strong> OK… and the leather ankle boots. What was wrong with them?<br data-start=\"2713\" data-end=\"2716\"><strong data-start=\"2716\" data-end=\"2724\">DON:</strong> Apparently, the heels were worn – but that wasn’t the problem. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(26) One of the shoes was a much lighter shade than the other one</span></strong> – it had obviously been left in the sun. I suppose even second-hand shoes should look the same!<br data-start=\"2946\" data-end=\"2949\"><strong data-start=\"2949\" data-end=\"2959\">BELLA:</strong> Sure. Then there were the red baby shoes.<br data-start=\"3001\" data-end=\"3004\"><strong data-start=\"3004\" data-end=\"3012\">DON:</strong> Oh yes – we’re told to tie shoes together when we put them in a recycling bin, but people often don’t bother.<br data-start=\"3122\" data-end=\"3125\"><strong data-start=\"3125\" data-end=\"3135\">BELLA:</strong> <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(27) You’d think it would have been easy to find the other, but it wasn’t</span></strong>. That was a shame because they were obviously new.<br data-start=\"3255\" data-end=\"3258\"><strong data-start=\"3258\" data-end=\"3266\">DON:</strong> The trainers were interesting. He said they looked like they’d been worn by a marathon runner.<br data-start=\"3361\" data-end=\"3364\"><strong data-start=\"3364\" data-end=\"3374\">BELLA:</strong> Yeah – weren’t they split?<br data-start=\"3401\" data-end=\"3404\" data-is-only-node=\"\"><strong data-start=\"3404\" data-end=\"3412\">DON:</strong> Not exactly. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(28) One of the soles was so worn under the foot that you could put your finger through it.</span></strong></p>\n<p data-start=\"3519\" data-end=\"4687\"><strong data-start=\"3519\" data-end=\"3529\">BELLA:</strong> Well, we could certainly use some of these examples in our presentation to explain why so many pairs of shoes that people take to recycling centres or bins get thrown into landfill.<br data-start=\"3711\" data-end=\"3714\"><strong data-start=\"3714\" data-end=\"3722\">DON:</strong> Mmm. What did you think about the project he set up to avoid this by making new shoes out of the good parts of old shoes?<br data-start=\"3844\" data-end=\"3847\"><strong data-start=\"3847\" data-end=\"3857\">BELLA:</strong> It sounded like a good idea. They get so many shoes, they should be able to match parts. I wasn’t surprised that it failed, though. I mean who wants to buy second-hand shoes really? Think of all the germs you could catch!<br data-start=\"4079\" data-end=\"4082\"><strong data-start=\"4082\" data-end=\"4090\">DON:</strong> Well, people didn’t refuse them for that reason, did they? <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(29) It was because the pairs of shoes weren’t identical.</strong></span><br data-start=\"4202\" data-end=\"4205\"><strong data-start=\"4205\" data-end=\"4215\">BELLA:</strong> They still managed to ship them overseas, though.<br data-start=\"4265\" data-end=\"4268\"><strong data-start=\"4268\" data-end=\"4276\">DON:</strong> That’s another area we need to discuss.<br data-start=\"4316\" data-end=\"4319\"><strong data-start=\"4319\" data-end=\"4329\">BELLA:</strong> You know I used to consider this topic from my own perspective, by thinking about my own recycling behaviour without looking at the bigger picture. So much happens once shoes leave the recycling area.<br data-start=\"4530\" data-end=\"4533\" data-is-only-node=\"\"><strong data-start=\"4533\" data-end=\"4541\">DON:</strong> It’s not as simple as you first think, and <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(30) we can show that by taking a very different approach to it.</span></strong><br data-start=\"4644\" data-end=\"4647\"><strong data-start=\"4647\" data-end=\"4657\">BELLA:</strong> Absolutely. So let’s discuss…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e19226b6-65e2-488f-b577-b4c6597f47f0', '95df4288-21b5-4a60-a5e5-1eddf6b5282e', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–7', '<p>Complete the <span class="citation-21477 citation-21478">notes below.</span><span class="citation-21477 citation-21478 citation-end-21478"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="1"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21477 citation-end-21477"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="2"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-21475 citation-21476">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="33"><span class="citation-21475 citation-21476">ONE WORD ONLY</span></strong><span class="citation-21475 citation-21476 citation-end-21476"> from the passage for each answer.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="3"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21475 citation-end-21475"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="4"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-21473 citation-21474 citation-end-21474">Write your answers in boxes 1–7 on your answer sheet.</span></p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; height: 2px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 2px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.8776%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;" data-path-to-node="4"><strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-21471 citation-21472 citation-end-21472"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Britain’s Industrial Revolution</span><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="7"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21471 citation-end-21471"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="8"><!----></sup></span></strong></p>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-184" data-path-to-node="5"><strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-21468 citation-21469 citation-21470 citation-end-21470">Steam power<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="9"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21468 citation-21469 citation-end-21469"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="10"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21468 citation-end-21468"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="11"><!----></sup></span></strong></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="6">
<li>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-185" data-path-to-node="6,0,0"><span class="citation-21465 citation-21466 citation-21467">Newcomen’s steam engine was used in mines to </span><strong data-path-to-node="6,0,0" data-index-in-node="45"><span class="citation-21465 citation-21466 citation-21467 citation-end-21467">remove wat<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="12"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21465 citation-21466">er</span></strong><span class="citation-21465 citation-21466 citation-end-21466">.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="13"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21465 citation-end-21465"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="14"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-186" data-path-to-node="6,1,0"><span class="citation-21463 citation-21464 citation-end-21464">In Watt and <sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="15"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21463">Boulton’s steam </span><span class="citation-21461 citation-21462 citation-21463">engine, the movement of the {piston}</span><span class="citation-21461 citation-21462 citation-21463 citation-end-21463"> was linked to a gear system.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="16"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21461 citation-21462 citation-end-21462"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="17"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21461 citation-end-21461"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="18"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-187" data-path-to-node="6,2,0"><span class="citation-21458 citation-21459 citation-21460">A greater supply of {coal}</span><span class="citation-21458 citation-21459 citation-21460 citation-end-21460"> was required to power steam engines<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="19"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21458 citation-21459 citation-end-21459">.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="20"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21458 citation-end-21458"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="21"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-188" data-path-to-node="7"><strong data-path-to-node="7" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-21456 citation-21457 citation-end-21457">Textile industry<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="22"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21456 citation-end-21456"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="23"><!----></sup></span></strong></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="8">
<li>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-189" data-path-to-node="8,0,0"><span class="citation-21454 citation-21455">Before the Industrial Revolution, spinners and weavers worked </span><span class="citation-21453 citation-21454 citation-21455">at home and in {workshops}</span><span class="citation-21453 citation-21454 citation-21455 citation-end-21455"> .<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="24"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21453 citation-21454 citation-end-21454"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="25"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21453 citation-end-21453"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="26"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-190" data-path-to-node="8,1,0"><span class="citation-21450 citation-21451 citation-21452 citation-end-21452">Not a<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="27"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21450 citation-21451">s much {labour|labor}</span><span class="citation-21450 citation-21451 citation-end-21451"> was<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="28"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21450 citation-end-21450"> needed to produce cloth once the spinning jenny and power loom were invented.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="29"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-191" data-path-to-node="9"><strong data-path-to-node="9" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-21449 citation-end-21449">Iron industry<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="30"><!----></sup></span></strong></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="10">
<li>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-192" data-path-to-node="10,0,0"><span class="citation-21448">Smelting </span><span class="citation-21447 citation-21448">of iron ore with coke resulted in material that was better {quality}</span><span class="citation-21447 citation-21448 citation-end-21448"> .<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="31"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21447 citation-end-21447"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="32"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-193" data-path-to-node="10,1,0"><span class="citation-21445 citation-21446 citation-end-21446">Demand for iron increased w<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="33"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21445">ith the growth of the {railways}</span><span class="citation-21445 citation-end-21445">.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="34"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-194" data-path-to-node="11"><strong data-path-to-node="11" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-21444 citation-end-21444">Communications<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="35"><!----></sup></span></strong></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="12">
<li>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-195" data-path-to-node="12,0,0"><span class="citation-21442 citation-21443 citation-end-21443">Cooke and Wheatstone patented the first telegraphy system.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="36"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21442 citation-end-21442"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="37"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-196" data-path-to-node="12,1,0"><span class="citation-21440 citation-21441 citation-end-21441">The telegraphy system was used to prevent loc<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="38"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21440 citation-end-21440">omotives colliding.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="39"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-197" data-path-to-node="13"><strong data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-21439 citation-end-21439">Urbanisation<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="40"><!----></sup></span></strong></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="14">
<li>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-198" data-path-to-node="14,0,0"><span class="citation-21438 citation-end-21438">Small towns turned into cities very quickly.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="41"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_464724625e004079-199" data-path-to-node="14,1,0"><span class="citation-21437 citation-end-21437">The new cities were dirty, crowded and lacked sufficie<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="42"><!----></sup></span>nt {sanitation} .</p>
