', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>1. So sánh Công ty Thuê Nội thất (Questions 1–5)<br /> </p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Good morning.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Hi, this is Shelley Meyer.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: I&#8217;m renting your house on Archwood Avenue.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: I&#8217;m due to move in next week.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Oh yes, hello Ms. Meyer.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: What can I do for you?</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: When I viewed the house, I told you I&#8217;ll most probably need to rent some furniture, at least until I know whether my temporary work contract is going to be made permanent.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Yes, of course, I remember.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: And I said I could give you some information about furniture rental companies in the city.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: That&#8217;s right.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Well, the biggest company is called Peak Rentals. (Company 1)</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: I&#8217;ve recommended them to other people and have always heard positive reports about them.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Could you give me an idea of their costs?</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Sure.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: I actually have one of their brochure here.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: It says the monthly price per room starts at $105 and goes up to $239. (Question 1)</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: That depends on which rooms you need furniture for, of course.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Sure.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: It&#8217;s just to get a general idea of how much it&#8217;s going to cost.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: And you said you had some positive feedback about this company?</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Yes.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: People have mentioned that the furniture from Peak Rentals is more modern than any of the other companies. (Question 2)</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: And also, once you place an order, the furniture will be delivered to you in just one or two days.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: That would be really helpful.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Oh, and the brochure says that there&#8217;s a special offer at the moment.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: If you rent living room furniture, I believe that&#8217;s a set of chairs and a TV table, you&#8217;ll also get a lamp at no extra cost. (Question 3)</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Okay, but you know, that price range you gave is more than I was hoping to pay.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Then you could try Aaron and Oliver. (Company 2)</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Sorry.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: What and Oliver?</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Aaron. (Question 4)</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Double A-R-O-N.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Okay.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Are they cheaper?</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: I&#8217;d say they&#8217;re a mid-price company.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: But if you chose them, you need to be aware that they charge an extra 12% every month in case of damage. (Question 5)</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Oh, I see.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: I&#8217;d have to do the math carefully then.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Right.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: But one helpful thing is that they also do cleaning for customers.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: For the furniture?</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: For the house.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Oh, I see.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: I probably won&#8217;t need that.</p>\n<p> <br /> </p>\n<p>2. Các Công ty Thuê Nội thất Khác (Questions 6–10)<br /> </p>\n<p>LANDLORD: There&#8217;s another company called Larch Furniture. (Company 3)</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: It&#8217;s quite new and it has the lowest prices in town. (Question 6)</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: That&#8217;s for both furniture and also electronic equipment.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Well, that would be good.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: I&#8217;m not bringing much with me and I won&#8217;t have much time to go shopping after I start my job.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: There are two things you need to know about Larch Furniture.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: First of all, you have to take out insurance on the furniture and you need to organize that yourself. (Question 7)</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: That wouldn&#8217;t be too hard.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Also, you can&#8217;t take out a contract for less than six months. (Question 8)</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: But I figure that might not be a problem for you.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: You&#8217;re renting the house for 12 months after all, aren&#8217;t you?</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Yes, okay, well&#8230;</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: Sorry to interrupt.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: I just thought of another furniture rental company.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: It&#8217;s called Space Rentals and it&#8217;s located very near to the house. (Company 4)</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Okay.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: I don&#8217;t have any information about their charges, so it&#8217;s best to use their app to find out what it would cost you to use them. (Question 9)</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Okay, thanks.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: I&#8217;ll do that.</p>\n<p>LANDLORD: One good thing about that company is that if you don&#8217;t like the furniture once it&#8217;s delivered, you can request exchanges, as long as you do that within a week of receiving it. (Question 10)</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: That sounds really great.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: Okay, well, thanks very much.</p>\n<p>SHELLEY: That&#8217;s so helpful.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4d10e802-8229-4b72-a3c3-ad2c996e8d07', 'bd926770-044b-433e-9496-4b7bcae6fd23', 'matching', 'Questions 25–28', '', '<p data-start="980" data-end="1080">What reasons did the recycling manager give for rejecting footwear, according to the students?</p>
<p data-start="1082" data-end="1153">Choose <strong data-start="1089" data-end="1097">FOUR</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, A–F.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Footwear</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>the high-heeled shoes  {the shoes were too dirty}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>the ankle boots  {the colour of one shoe had faded}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>the baby shoes  {one shoe was missing}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>the trainers  {one shoe had a hole in it}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "one shoe was missing"}, {"optionText": "the colour of one shoe had faded"}, {"optionText": "one shoe had a hole in it"}, {"optionText": "the shoes were brand new"}, {"optionText": "the shoes were too dirty"}, {"optionText": " the stitching on the shoes was broken"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('51991d47-e7f4-4a3d-a1ad-ed9f6841e447', '1ad5ae28-6cc0-40b5-b7d6-bfc2ed1d3b92', 'fillup', 'Questions 27-30 ', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>It is known that the pronunciation of language changes over time. The changes include large-scale regularities known as {sound laws}. There are several possible causes for change. Firstly, there is the effect of one language on another. Secondly, there is the role of { fashion}. The speech of certain groups has prestige, and is imitated by others. It has also been suggested that some changes are introduced by  {children}, who are unable to imitate speech in an exact way. Finally, there is a factor referred to as the { principle of ease}, by which the effort necessary to produce words is reduced.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. {sound laws}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Such regular changes are often called <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">sound laws</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài tóm tắt đề cập đến “large-scale regularities” (những quy luật diện rộng). Trong bài đọc, tác giả định nghĩa những thay đổi có hệ thống này (ví dụ: tất cả các âm [b] chuyển thành [p]) là các <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"206\">quy luật âm thanh</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. {fashion}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It is also possible that <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">fashion</strong> plays a part in the process of change. …one person imitates another, and people with the most prestige are most likely to be imitated…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngôn ngữ thay đổi do xu hướng xã hội. Con người có xu hướng bắt chước cách phát âm của những nhóm có địa vị cao (prestige). Tác giả gọi yếu tố dẫn dắt sự bắt chước này là <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"183\">thời trang/xu hướng</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. {children}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…the argument is that the imitation of <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">children</strong> is imperfect: they copy their parents’ speech, but never reproduce it exactly.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một nguyên nhân khác được đưa ra là do <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">trẻ em</strong>. Vì trẻ em không thể bắt chước chính xác (imperfect imitation/unable to imitate in an exact way) giọng nói của người lớn, những sai lệch này tích tụ dần dẫn đến sự thay đổi ngôn ngữ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. {principle of ease}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“One such force which is often invoked is the <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">principle of ease</strong>, or minimization of effort.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đây là cơ chế sinh học. Con người luôn muốn giảm thiểu nỗ lực (minimization of effort) khi nói. <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">Nguyên tắc dễ dàng</strong> giúp giải thích tại sao các âm khó phát âm thường bị biến đổi hoặc lược bỏ để việc giao tiếp trở nên trơn tru hơn.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bf76a0fd-7b2b-41ab-af74-38393cec7077', '1ad5ae28-6cc0-40b5-b7d6-bfc2ed1d3b92', 'radio', 'Questions 31-37', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information,<strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It is impossible to know how words used to be pronounced."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some languages appear to have changed more than others."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some changes in English were probably led by the middle classes."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Certain English sounds are difficult for all children to pronounce."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Scant is generally easier to pronounce than skamt."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The spelling of gnat is likely to change in the future."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The spelling of temporary no longer reflects its pronunciation."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. It is impossible to know how words used to be pronounced. -&gt; FALSE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> “These various kinds of evidence… can often give us a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">very good idea of the pronunciation of an earlier age</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định dù không thể chắc chắn tuyệt đối, nhưng các nguồn bằng chứng (cách đánh vần, từ mượn, ghi chép cổ) giúp chúng ta có một khái niệm “rất tốt” về cách phát âm xưa. Do đó, nói “không thể” là sai.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. Some languages appear to have changed more than others. -&gt; NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc thảo luận về <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">cách thức</em> (mechanisms) ngôn ngữ thay đổi, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">không hề so sánh</strong> tốc độ hoặc mức độ thay đổi giữa các ngôn ngữ khác nhau (ví dụ: tiếng Anh thay đổi nhiều hơn tiếng Nga hay không).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. Some changes in English were probably led by the middle classes. -&gt; TRUE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> “…probably carried elements of <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">middle-class pronunciation</strong> into upper-class speech.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết chỉ ra rằng sự gia tăng quyền lực và giàu có của tầng lớp trung lưu ở thế kỷ 17-18 đã mang các yếu tố phát âm của họ thâm nhập vào tầng lớp thượng lưu, dẫn đến sự thay đổi trong cách phát âm tiếng Anh được chấp nhận.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Certain English sounds are difficult for all children to pronounce. -&gt; NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> “the imitation of children is imperfect… never reproduce it exactly.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói trẻ em bắt chước “không hoàn hảo”, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">không nêu tên cụ thể</strong> bất kỳ âm tiết nào là “khó đối với tất cả trẻ em”.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Scant is generally easier to pronounce than skamt. -&gt; TRUE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> “the word scant was once skamt… <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">Greater efficiency has hereby been achieved</strong>, because /n/ and /t/ are articulated in the same place…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Greater efficiency” (hiệu quả cao hơn) chính là “easier to pronounce” (dễ phát âm hơn). Việc phát âm /n/ và /t/ tại cùng một vị trí (đầu lưỡi chạm nướu) giúp tiết kiệm nỗ lực hơn là chuyển từ vị trí môi (/m/) sang nướu (/t/).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. The spelling of gnat is likely to change in the future. -&gt; NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến việc các âm câm (như [k] trong <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">knight</em>) ảnh hưởng đến cách phát âm, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">không có dự đoán</strong> nào về việc thay đổi cách đánh vần (spelling) của từ “gnat” trong tương lai.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. The spelling of temporary no longer reflects its pronunciation. -&gt; TRUE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> “…temporary, which in Britain is often pronounced as if it were <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">tempory</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khi người Anh phát âm là “tempory”, họ đã lược bỏ một âm tiết so với cách viết đầy đủ. Vì vậy, âm thanh phát ra không còn phản ánh (no longer reflects) chính xác tất cả các chữ cái có trong cách đánh vần “temporary”.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('60cabedc-1fdc-4301-813e-135e650c4bef', '1ad5ae28-6cc0-40b5-b7d6-bfc2ed1d3b92', 'matching', 'Questions 38-40', NULL, '<p>Look at the following sentences and the list of statements below.</p>
<p>Match each statement with the correct sentence, A-D.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "large-scale change"}, {"optionText": "influence of one language on another"}, {"optionText": "minimisation of effort"}, {"optionText": "imitation of prestigious group"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "The b sound changing to a p sound at the end of words", "correctAnswer": "large-scale change", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "The melodic pronunciation of Welsh English", "correctAnswer": "influence of one language on another", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "The disappearance of the t sound in Christmas", "correctAnswer": "minimisation of effort", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. The b sound changing to a p sound at the end of words -&gt; A (large-scale change)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> “…all the [b] consonants in a certain position (for example at the end of a word) may change into [p] consonants. Such <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">regular changes</strong> are often called <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"174\">sound laws</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc thay đổi từ âm [b] sang [p] trên toàn bộ các từ có vị trí tương tự là một ví dụ về <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">quy luật âm thanh (sound laws)</strong>. Đặc điểm cốt lõi của quy luật này là sự thay đổi diễn ra trên diện rộng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"205\">large-scale</strong>) và có tính hệ thống trong một ngôn ngữ ở một giai đoạn nhất định.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. The melodic pronunciation of Welsh English -&gt; B (influence of one language on another)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Dựa trên kiến thức ngôn ngữ học trong bài):</strong> Bài đọc đề cập đến việc “the effect of one language on another” (sự ảnh hưởng của ngôn ngữ này lên ngôn ngữ khác) là một nguyên nhân gây biến đổi.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cách phát âm có ngữ điệu (melodic) của tiếng Anh giọng Wales (Welsh English) là kết quả trực tiếp từ sự ảnh hưởng của tiếng Wales (tiếng mẹ đẻ) lên tiếng Anh. Đây là minh chứng cho việc các đặc điểm ngữ âm của một ngôn ngữ thâm nhập và làm thay đổi một ngôn ngữ khác khi chúng tiếp xúc với nhau.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. The disappearance of the t sound in Christmas -&gt; C (minimisation of effort)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E &amp; F):</strong> “…the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">principle of ease</strong>, or <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">minimisation of effort</strong>. …At one time there was a [t] in words like castle and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">Christmas</strong>… Consonant-clusters are often simplified.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc lược bỏ âm [t] trong từ <em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">Christmas</em> giúp cụm phụ âm trở nên đơn giản hơn. Điều này giúp người nói phát âm từ đó trôi chảy và tốn ít công sức hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">minimisation of effort</strong>). Đây là cơ chế tự nhiên của ngôn ngữ nhằm đạt được sự hiệu quả tối đa trong giao tiếp.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2e2e63c0-f2b5-44e0-baf0-6054f7d764fb', '04fbc88d-a307-444b-9b12-cd4a9196b0df', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', '', '<p data-start="105" data-end="307">Choose <strong data-start="112" data-end="120">TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong data-start="192" data-end="201">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong data-start="258" data-end="271">NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "An inspection fee on fish oil was introduced in New York in 1818"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Samuel Judd argued that the inspection fee should exclude whale oil"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Judd had been in trouble with city officials before the inspection fee disagreement"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Many New Yorkers were interested in the court case at the time"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Traditionally, non-human creatures had been classified in one of three groups"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Generally speaking, ordinary people thought fish were the lowest form of life"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Whales were excluded from the Linnaean system in 1818"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. An inspection fee on fish oil was introduced in New York in 1818. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “In 1818 a whale became the subject of a controversial court case… The case involved an <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">old law</strong> requiring those who sold fish oil to pay a fee…” (Đoạn 1)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói phí kiểm định được <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">giới thiệu (ra đời)</strong> vào năm 1818. Thực tế, bài đọc nói đây là một <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"109\">đạo luật cũ (old law)</strong>, năm 1818 chỉ là thời điểm xảy ra vụ kiện.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Samuel Judd argued that the inspection fee should exclude whale oil. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…Samuel Judd refused to pay the inspection fee… claiming that <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">no inspection was necessary because it was whale oil</strong>, and whales were not fish.” (Đoạn 1)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Judd tranh luận rằng không cần kiểm định vì đó là dầu cá voi (không thuộc phạm vi luật về dầu cá). Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc ông muốn loại trừ (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">exclude</em>) dầu cá voi khỏi danh sách đóng phí.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Judd had been in trouble with city officials before the inspection fee disagreement. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ tập trung vào vụ kiện về phí dầu cá. <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">Không có thông tin</strong> nào nói về việc trước đây Judd có từng gặp rắc rối với chính quyền thành phố hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Many New Yorkers were interested in the court case at the time. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Indeed, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">public debate in New York sparked off by the trial was sensational</strong>.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “sensational” (gây vang dội/giật gân) và “public debate” chứng minh rằng có rất nhiều người dân quan tâm đến vụ kiện này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Traditionally, non-human creatures had been classified in one of three groups. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…all non-human creatures had been organised according to the categories of <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">birds, beasts and fish</strong>.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đúng là theo truyền thống, các loài vật được chia thành 3 nhóm chính: chim, thú và cá.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Generally speaking, ordinary people thought fish were the lowest form of life. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nói về việc người dân coi cá voi là cá vì chúng sống dưới biển, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến việc họ có coi cá là “dạng sống thấp kém nhất” (<em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">lowest form of life</em>) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Whales were excluded from the Linnaean system in 1818. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Barely half a century old in 1818, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">Linnaean system controversially classified whales as mammals</strong>…” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hệ thống Linnaean <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">bao gồm</strong> cá voi và xếp chúng vào nhóm thú (mammals), chứ không phải loại trừ (<em data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">excluded</em>) chúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6fcdfcfb-500e-4e11-a4ca-8371ac1ffeb8', '04fbc88d-a307-444b-9b12-cd4a9196b0df', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–13', '<p>Complete the notes.</p>
<p>Write<strong> ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the text for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="1157" data-end="1186"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>The Trial of December 1818</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="1188" data-end="1209"><strong>The Personalities</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1211" data-end="1433">
<li data-start="1211" data-end="1268">
<p>Samuel Mitchill worked as a congressman and a {lecturer}.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1269" data-end="1336">
<p>The defence wanted Mitchill to present the biology of the case.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1337" data-end="1433">
<p>William Sampson called {whalers} as witnesses in order to appeal to the common sense of the jury.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1435" data-end="1452"><strong>The Arguments</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1454" data-end="1667">
<li data-start="1454" data-end="1526">
<p>Sampson’s case was based on the consequences for humans if Judd won.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1527" data-end="1599">
<p>Mitchill admitted that scientists had disputes about classification.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1600" data-end="1667">
<p>New Yorkers disliked Mitchill because his ideas came from {Europe}.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1669" data-end="1684"><strong>Conclusions</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1686" data-end="1914">
<li data-start="1686" data-end="1785">
<p>In the end it was statements from local {merchants}, not Mitchill’s testimony which helped Judd win.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1786" data-end="1840">
<p>Whale oil made a good {fuel} because it was clean.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1841" data-end="1914">
<p>Judd’s case is relevant today, e.g. in the debate about Earth’s {climate}.</p>
</li>
</ul>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Samuel Mitchill worked as a congressman and a {lecturer}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…congressman Samuel Mitchill… was a renowned natural history <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">lecturer</strong> at the College of Physicians and Surgeons…” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. William Sampson called {whalers} as witnesses in order to appeal to the common sense of the jury.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…by asking plain-spoken <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">whalers</strong> to make their case before the jury.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để đối đầu với kiến thức bác học của Mitchill, luật sư Sampson đã mời những người thợ săn cá voi (whalers) làm chứng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. New Yorkers disliked Mitchill because his ideas came from {Europe}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…Sampson then claimed Mitchill’s beliefs had their origin in <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">Europe</strong> – something he rightly judged would infuriate the citizens…” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. In the end it was statements from local {merchants}, not Mitchill’s testimony which helped Judd win.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Ultimately, what won the case for Samuel Judd… In New York’s markets, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">merchants</strong> implicitly understood that whale oil and fish oil were not the same…” (Đoạn 7)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Whale oil made a good {fuel} because it was clean.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…whale oil could be used as a <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">fuel</strong> for lamps because it could be burned without giving off smoke…” (Đoạn 7)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dầu cá voi cháy sạch (không khói) nên làm <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">nhiên liệu (fuel)</strong> rất tốt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Judd’s case is relevant today, e.g. in the debate about Earth’s {climate}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Whether the issue today is the effects of human activity on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">climate</strong> of this planet…” (Đoạn 8)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('12b8ca5f-eac7-472e-9411-dbb3cd68b8fb', '284ceef3-1b2f-4733-a4e6-72e04bc90dc1', 'radio', 'Questions 25-26', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B</strong>, <strong>C </strong>or <strong>D</strong></p>
<p>Write the correct letter in boxes 25 and 26 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A No previous work had been done in this area."}, {"option_text": "B Earlier studies did not support his theory."}, {"option_text": "C Textbooks on this subject lacked specific detail."}, {"option_text": "D Currie''s initial theory had proven to be incorrect."}], "question": "What does the writer say about Cameron Currie''s research?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A has a white covering"}, {"option_text": "B is covered in wax."}, {"option_text": "C is poisonous to humans."}, {"option_text": "D has a substance useful to humans."}], "question": "Using a microscope, Currie was the first to discover that the body of attine ants"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. What does the writer say about Cameron Currie’s research? — {B} Earlier studies did not support his theory.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Currie felt there had to be a parasite… But <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">a century of ant research had provided no evidence for his idea</strong>. Textbooks describe how leaf-cutter ants scrupulously weed their gardens…” (Đoạn E)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Suốt 100 năm nghiên cứu trước đó không tìm thấy bằng chứng và sách giáo khoa cũng nói ngược lại ý của Currie, tức là các nghiên cứu trước đó không ủng hộ giả thuyết của ông.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. Using a microscope, Currie was the first to discover that the body of attine ants — {D} has a substance useful to humans.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…after examining it under a <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">microscope</strong>, Currie discovered… a particular kind of bacterium… the <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">source of half the antibiotics used in medicine</strong>.” (Đoạn H)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Currie dùng kính hiển vi để phát hiện ra lớp phủ trên thân kiến thực chất là vi khuẩn tạo ra <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">kháng sinh (antibiotics)</strong> – một chất cực kỳ hữu ích cho y học loài người.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ae0c18ea-4deb-465d-b8da-3a87fb0048d9', '3338fd2c-1510-4517-8f5c-3de72d6aa4a7', 'matching', 'Questions 14–19', '', '<p>Reading Passage 2 has six sections.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each section from the list of headings below.</p>', 'matching_headings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. Professions in which super-taskers are likely to be found"}, {"optionText": "ii. The effects of multi-tasking on neurological structure"}, {"optionText": "iii. A distinction between situations when people can and can’t multi-task"}, {"optionText": "iv. Real multi-tasking is nearly impossible"}, {"optionText": "v. Multi-tasking and gender"}, {"optionText": "vi. The neurological reasons for struggling to manage more things"}, {"optionText": "vii. The ability to multi-task is determined by people’s genes"}, {"optionText": "viii. Gender and the structure of the brain"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14: {iv. Real multi-tasking is nearly impossible}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…research shows that your <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">brain isn’t capable of paying close attention to more than one complex task at a time</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này khẳng định việc đa nhiệm thực sự (làm hai việc phức tạp cùng lúc) là gần như không thể đối với 97% dân số. Nó được gọi là một “mythical activity” (hoạt động huyền thoại/không có thật).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15: {iii. A distinction between situations when people can and can’t multi-task}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “It is true that you can check your email while eating… But <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">innate activities</strong> [walking, breathing] <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">do not require you to pay attention</strong>, whereas <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">activities such as reading… do require attention</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này phân biệt rõ ranh giới: chúng ta có thể làm hai việc cùng lúc nếu một việc là bản năng (không cần chú ý), nhưng không thể nếu cả hai việc đều đòi hỏi sự tập trung não bộ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16: {vi. The neurological reasons for struggling to manage more things}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…when people focused on a single thing, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">right and left sides of the prefrontal cortex work together</strong>. But when people attempt to perform two things… the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"172\">sides work independently</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này giải thích dưới góc độ thần kinh học (neurological): chúng ta gặp khó khăn vì não chỉ có hai thùy trán, khi làm hai việc thì chúng phải hoạt động độc lập, và nếu thêm việc thứ ba thì não sẽ bị quá tải.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17: {v. Multi-tasking and gender}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…uncovered <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">no differences in the ability to switch between tasks in the prefrontal cortices of men or women</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tiêu đề này rất rõ ràng vì đoạn văn tập trung so sánh khả năng đa nhiệm giữa nam và nữ (gender/sexes).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18: {i. Professions in which super-taskers are likely to be found}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">pilots</strong> of high-performance aircraft, <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">high-end chefs</strong>… and <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">elite doctors</strong>… might all be more likely to be super-taskers.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này liệt kê các ngành nghề (professions) mà những người siêu đa nhiệm (super-taskers) thường xuất hiện.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19: {vii. The ability to multi-task is determined by people’s genes}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The ability to multi-task probably <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">comes down to the DNA you inherit</strong>… You are either <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">born with the neural structure</strong>… or you aren’t.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn cuối khẳng định khả năng này do di truyền/gen (DNA/inherit/born with) quyết định chứ không hẳn do luyện tập.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9ce04ba5-e2d6-4747-be5e-b45bb196c7ab', 'bd926770-044b-433e-9496-4b7bcae6fd23', 'radio', 'Questions 29–30', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>or <strong>C</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. People believed the ‘new’ pairs of shoes were unhygienic."}, {"option_text": "B. There were not enough good parts to use in the old shoes."}, {"option_text": "C. The shoes in the ‘new’ pairs were not completely alike."}], "question": "Why did the project to make ‘new’ shoes out of old shoes fail?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. from a new angle."}, {"option_text": "B. with relevant images."}, {"option_text": "C. in a straightforward way."}], "question": "Bella and Don agree that they can present their topic"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5df7f092-c0ae-4675-a6b7-f5e63fbaa28d', 'de8e13ca-75a0-430e-8ef4-9a7c3b1083b1', 'matrix', 'Questions 19-23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following statements (Questions 19-23) and the list of people below.</p>
<p>Match each statement with the correct person, <strong>A-F</strong></p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of people", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "one species has a camouflage tactic that is not present from birth.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Species that live in an ancient environment have become very effective at camouflaging themselves", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Part of an animals is left behind to distract predators.", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "If it takes too long to find one kind of prey, animals will look for an alternative source food.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Camouflage can involve copying a threatening type of animals.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Professor Mark Elgar", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Palu Zborowski", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Professor Gisela Kaplan", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Dr Karen Cheney", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Henry Bates", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "Martyn Robinson", "categoryLetter": "F"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. One species has a camouflage tactic that is not present from birth.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C (Professor Gisela Kaplan)</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">C</strong>: “…says the frogmouth’s skill at camouflaging is <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">learned behaviour</strong>… the ability to choose a backdrop… <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">does not develop for 4-6 months</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Giáo sư Kaplan cho biết kỹ năng chọn nền ngụy trang của chim Tawny Frogmouth là do học hỏi mà có, chứ không phải có sẵn từ lúc mới sinh.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Species that live in an ancient environment have become very effective at camouflaging themselves.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: B (Paul Zborowski)</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">B</strong>: “It’s an <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">incredibly old habitat</strong> so the creatures have had a long time to adapt,’ Zborowski explains.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Zborowski cho rằng môi trường sống cổ xưa giúp các sinh vật có nhiều thời gian để tiến hóa kỹ năng ngụy trang hoàn hảo.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Part of an animal is left behind to distract predators.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: F (Martyn Robinson)</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">G</strong>: “Robinson explains that if attacked, the chameleon gecko will <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">drop off its tail</strong>, which will wriggle around on the ground… and the gecko can sneak away.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Robinson giải thích về cơ chế rụng đuôi của tắc kè để đánh lạc hướng kẻ thù.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. If it takes too long to find one kind of prey, animals will look for an alternative source food.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: A (Professor Mark Elgar)</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">A</strong>: “Camouflage <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">increases the search time</strong> and, as a consequence, the predator will simply <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">target another species</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Giáo sư Elgar giải thích rằng ngụy trang làm tăng thời gian tìm kiếm, khiến kẻ săn mồi nản lòng và đi tìm con mồi khác dễ thấy hơn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Camouflage can involve copying a threatening type of animal.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: E (Henry Bates)</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"16\">E</strong>: “<strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">Batesian mimicry</strong> refers to animals that gain protection from predators by <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">imitating a dangerous organism</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Henry Bates là người đưa ra thuyết bắt chước Batesian, trong đó loài hiền lành giả dạng loài nguy hiểm để tự vệ.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('62939640-9752-4869-b828-ed46e39c6f0f', 'fbd31dcd-62aa-40b7-8a5f-5bcd0f0d432d', 'radio', 'Questions 27–30', '', '<p data-start="21" data-end="65">Choose the correct letter, <strong data-start="48" data-end="64">A, B, C or D</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="67" data-end="132"> </p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. to indicate that his article will cover several scientific fields"}, {"option_text": "B. to stress how much physics has changed in 400 years"}, {"option_text": "C. to persuade the reader to take him seriously"}, {"option_text": "D. to point out that his notions are not new"}], "question": "Why does the writer refer to Locke and Newton in the first paragraph?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. It was too complex for his contemporaries to understand."}, {"option_text": "B. It involved criticism of the way people behaved in society."}, {"option_text": "C. People felt that it devalued the accepted concept of humanity."}, {"option_text": "D. People assumed that it was intended as a joke."}], "question": "According to the writer, why was Freud''s theory of the unconscious mocked?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. how realistic most people''s memories are."}, {"option_text": "B. how hard it is to tell dreaming and waking apart."}, {"option_text": "C. how unusual it is to mistake a perception for a memory."}, {"option_text": "D. how valuable knowledge of the past can be."}], "question": "The writer describes Mr S failing to get up in order to demonstrate"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. Perception involves much more than the data collected by the eyes."}, {"option_text": "B. Learning to see as an adult can be a time-consuming process."}, {"option_text": "C. Science is failing to devote enough attention to sight."}, {"option_text": "D. Human perception is remarkably reliable."}], "question": "What point is the writer making in the text as a whole?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. D — to point out that his notions are not new</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Two of the great British men of the 17th century, the philosopher John Locke and the physicist Isaac Newton, were both aware that objects are not coloured...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả đưa ra các cột mốc lịch sử từ tận thế kỷ 17 nhằm nhấn mạnh rằng những khái niệm về việc vật thể và ánh sáng vốn dĩ không có màu sắc không phải là những khám phá mới mẻ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"189\">not new</strong>), mà chúng đã được các vĩ nhân nhận thức từ 400 năm trước.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. C — People felt that it devalued the accepted concept of humanity.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“...Freud’s notion of the unconscious, which was also initially treated with derision because it undermined the notion of humans as pre-eminently rational beings...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thuyết vô thức của Freud bị chế giễu (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">mocked / treated with derision</em>) vì nó làm lung lay, hạ thấp (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">undermined</em>) tư tưởng coi con người là sinh vật có lý trí tối cao và phải tự chịu trách nhiệm cho hành vi của mình. Việc này đồng nghĩa với việc làm giảm giá trị khái niệm được thừa nhận về nhân tính (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"311\">devalued the accepted concept of humanity</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. C — how unusual it is to mistake a perception for a memory.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Individual perceptions have a vividness that is rare for memories, which might be how we are able to separate them.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu chuyện ông Mr. S ngủ nướng do nhầm lẫn giữa việc \"nhìn thấy cái đồng hồ\" (thực tại) và \"nhớ về cái đồng hồ\" (quá khứ) là một trường hợp cực kỳ cá biệt. Tác giả mượn ví dụ này để phản đề rằng người bình thường rất hiếm khi nhầm lẫn như vậy (<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"256\">how unusual it is</strong>), nhờ vào độ sống động (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"298\">vividness</em>) của thị giác thực tế giúp ta phân định rõ ràng với ký ức.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. A — Perception involves much more than the data collected by the eyes.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Von Helmholtz thought that perceptions are unconscious inferences we make based on a combination of clues provided by the eyes and other senses, and knowledge of the world.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thông điệp bao quát toàn bài viết khẳng định rằng quá trình nhận thức thị giác (<em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">perception</em>) không đơn giản chỉ là những dữ liệu hình ảnh cơ học do mắt thu về, mà nó là sự tổng hòa phức tạp kết hợp với trải nghiệm xúc giác, kiến thức nền và ký ức trong bộ não.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a6157085-7734-4139-9dcd-4ad195ea5030', '95df4288-21b5-4a60-a5e5-1eddf6b5282e', 'radio', 'Questions 8–13', '', '<p><span class="citation-21433">Choose</span><strong data-path-to-node="18,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-21433"> TRUE</span></strong><span class="citation-21433"> if the statement agrees with </span><span class="citation-21431 citation-21432 citation-21433 citation-end-21433">the information<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="46"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21431 citation-21432 citation-end-21432"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="47"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21431 citation-end-21431"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="48"><!----></sup></span> <strong data-path-to-node="18,0" data-index-in-node="50"><span class="citation-21428 citation-21429 citation-21430">FALSE</span></strong><span class="citation-21428 citation-21429 citation-21430 citation-end-21430"> if the statement contradicts the i<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="49"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21428 citation-21429 citation-end-21429">nformation<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="50"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21428 citation-end-21428"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="51"><!----></sup></span> <strong data-path-to-node="18,0" data-index-in-node="101"><span class="citation-21426 citation-21427">NOT GIVEN</span></strong><span class="citation-21426 citation-21427 citation-end-21427"> if there is no information on this<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="52"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-21426 citation-end-21426"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="53"><!----></sup></span></p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Britain’s canal network grew rapidly so that more goods could be transported around the country."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Costs in the iron industry rose when the technique of smelting iron ore with coke was introduced."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Samuel Morse’s communication system was more reliable than that developed by William Cooke and Charles Wheatstone."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The economic benefits of industrialisation were limited to certain sectors of society."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some skilled weavers believed that the introduction of the new textile machines would lead to job losses."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There was some sympathy among local people for the Luddites who were arrested near Huddersfield."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Britain’s canal network grew rapidly so that more goods could be transported around the country. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"In addition, steam-powered boats and ships were widely used to carry goods along <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">Britain''s canals</strong> as well as across the Atlantic.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến việc dùng tàu hơi nước để chở hàng dọc theo các kênh đào (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">canals</strong>). Tuy nhiên, bài <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến việc mạng lưới kênh đào này có \"phát triển nhanh chóng\" (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"191\">grew rapidly</strong>) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. Costs in the iron industry rose when the technique of smelting iron ore with coke was introduced. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Chief among the new techniques was the smelting of iron ore with coke... This method was <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">cheaper</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định phương pháp luyện kim bằng than cốc này <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">rẻ hơn</strong> (cheaper), nghĩa là chi phí giảm xuống. Câu hỏi nói chi phí tăng lên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">rose</strong>) là sai hoàn toàn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. Samuel Morse’s communication system was more reliable than that developed by William Cooke and Charles Wheatstone. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_ab9949c6f73b206c-21\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"<span class=\"citation-74\">In 1837, British inventors William Cooke and Charles Wheatstone patented the first commercial telegraphy system. In the 1830s and 1840s, Samuel Morse and other inventors worked on </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"201\"><span class=\"citation-74\">their own versions</span></strong><span class=\"citation-74 citation-end-74\"> in the United Sta<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>tes.\"</em></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!---->\n<p> </p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nhắc đến cả hai hệ thống điện báo của Cooke-Wheatstone (Anh) và Samuel Morse (Mỹ), nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"109\">không có bất kỳ sự so sánh</strong> nào về việc hệ thống nào đáng tin cậy hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"179\">more reliable</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. The economic benefits of industrialisation were limited to certain sectors of society. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Although industrialisation... improved the standard of living for the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">middle and upper classes</strong>, many <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">poor people continued to struggle</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lợi ích kinh tế chỉ cải thiện đời sống cho tầng lớp trung lưu và thượng lưu, trong khi người nghèo vẫn chật vật. Điều này khớp với ý \"giới hạn ở một số thành phần nhất định trong xã hội\" (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"200\">limited to certain sectors</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Some skilled weavers believed that the introduction of the new textile machines would lead to job losses. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"A group of... Luddites were British <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">weavers</strong>... Many had spent years <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">learning their craft</strong>, and they <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">feared that unskilled machine operators were robbing them of their livelihood</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những người thợ dệt lành nghề (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">skilled weavers</strong>) lo sợ rằng những người vận hành máy không chuyên sẽ cướp đi kế sinh nhai của họ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">robbing them of their livelihood</strong>), tức là dẫn đến mất việc làm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"205\">job losses</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. There was some sympathy among local people for the Luddites who were arrested near Huddersfield. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 9):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"The unrest finally reached its peak in April 1812, when a few Luddites were shot during an attack on a mill <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">near Huddersfield</strong>. In the days that followed, other Luddites were <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"195\">arrested</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến việc các Luddites bị bắt tại Huddersfield, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến việc người dân địa phương có \"cảm thông\" (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">sympathy</strong>) với họ hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8ac33a1d-5577-4515-8c4a-90e8362cfcdd', '5d02f9c5-10ef-46d4-995f-7e62ba1356db', 'fillup', 'Questions 7-13', '<p>Complete&nbsp;the&nbsp;notes&nbsp;below.</p><p>Choose&nbsp;<strong>ONE&nbsp;WORD&nbsp;AND/OR&nbsp;A&nbsp;NUMBER</strong>&nbsp;from&nbsp;the&nbsp;passage&nbsp;for&nbsp;each&nbsp;answer.</p><p><strong>New&nbsp;Zealand’s&nbsp;kākāpō</strong></p><p><strong>A&nbsp;type&nbsp;of&nbsp;parrot:</strong></p><ul><li>diet&nbsp;consists&nbsp;of&nbsp;fern&nbsp;fronds,&nbsp;various&nbsp;parts&nbsp;of&nbsp;a&nbsp;tree&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>{bulbs}</strong></li><li>nests&nbsp;are&nbsp;created&nbsp;in&nbsp;<strong>{soil&nbsp;}</strong>&nbsp;where&nbsp;eggs&nbsp;are&nbsp;laid.</li></ul><p><strong>Arrival&nbsp;of&nbsp;Polynesian&nbsp;settlers</strong></p><ul><li>the&nbsp;<strong>{feathers}</strong>&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;kākāpō&nbsp;were&nbsp;used&nbsp;to&nbsp;make&nbsp;clothes.</li></ul><p><strong>Arrival&nbsp;of&nbsp;European&nbsp;colonisers</strong></p><ul><li><strong>{deer&nbsp;}</strong>&nbsp;were&nbsp;an&nbsp;animal&nbsp;which&nbsp;they&nbsp;introduced&nbsp;that&nbsp;ate&nbsp;the&nbsp;kākāpō’s&nbsp;food&nbsp;sources.</li></ul><p><strong>Protecting&nbsp;kākāpō</strong></p><ul><li>Richard&nbsp;Henry,&nbsp;a&nbsp;conservationist,&nbsp;tried&nbsp;to&nbsp;protect&nbsp;the&nbsp;kākāpō.</li><li>a&nbsp;definite&nbsp;sighting&nbsp;of&nbsp;female&nbsp;kākāpō&nbsp;on&nbsp;Rakiura&nbsp;Island&nbsp;was&nbsp;reported&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;year&nbsp;<strong>{1980&nbsp;}</strong></li><li>the&nbsp;Recovery&nbsp;Plan&nbsp;included&nbsp;an&nbsp;increase&nbsp;in&nbsp;<strong>{funding&nbsp;}</strong></li><li>a&nbsp;current&nbsp;goal&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;Recovery&nbsp;Plan&nbsp;is&nbsp;to&nbsp;maintain&nbsp;the&nbsp;involvement&nbsp;of&nbsp;<strong>{stakeholders}</strong>&nbsp;in&nbsp;kākāpō&nbsp;protection.</li></ul>', '<p></p>', 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '[{"content": "<p>7. bulbs<br />(Đoạn 2: “Their diet includes the leaves, roots and bark of trees as well as buds and fern fronds.”)<br />→ Trong phần tóm tắt đề: “…various parts of a tree and ___”, phù hợp nhất là bulbs (củ cây).</p>\n<p> <br />8. soil<br />(Đoạn 3: “The 1–4 eggs are laid in soil, which is repeatedly turned over before and during incubation.”)<br />→ Trứng được đẻ trong đất → đáp án là soil.</p>\n<p> <br />9. feathers<br />(Đoạn 4: “They ate its meat and used its feathers to make soft cloaks.”)<br />→ Người Polynesian dùng lông kākāpō làm áo choàng → feathers.</p>\n<p> <br />10. deer<br />(Đoạn 4: “Introduced species such as deer depleted the remaining forests of food.”)<br />→ Hươu (deer) là loài châu Âu mang tới, ăn mất nguồn thức ăn của kākāpō.</p>\n<p> <br />11. 1980<br />(Đoạn 6: “In 1980 it was confirmed females were also present.”)<br />→ Năm 1980 ghi nhận có cả kākāpō cái, xác nhận quần thể sinh sản được.</p>\n<p> <br />12. funding<br />(Đoạn 7: “A higher amount of funding.”)<br />→ Kế hoạch phục hồi có tăng nguồn tài trợ để bảo vệ kākāpō.</p>\n<p> <br />13. stakeholders<br />(Đoạn cuối: “Ensure stakeholders continue to be fully engaged in the preservation of the species.”)<br />→ Mục tiêu hiện nay là duy trì sự tham gia của các bên liên quan (stakeholders).</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": ""}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c8e0233d-38bc-4ef1-9e1c-e76ced9c7b6b', 'd025bf33-61da-4a94-8e3a-79e55937d701', 'radio', 'Questions 21–25', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="27">A</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="30">B</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="35">C</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A   worried that they are not making progress"}, {"option_text": "B   challenged by their poor behaviour in class"}, {"option_text": "C   frustrated at their lack of interest in the subject"}], "question": "How does Clare feel about the students in her Year 12 science class?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A   He is concerned that the results might not be meaningful."}, {"option_text": "B   He feels some of the data might be difficult to obtain."}, {"option_text": "C   He suspects that the conclusions might be upsetting."}], "question": "How does Jake react to Clare''s suggestion about an experiment based on children''s diet?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A   Any results may not apply to humans."}, {"option_text": "B   It may be complicated to get permission."}, {"option_text": "C   Students may not be happy about animal experiments."}], "question": "What problem do they agree may be involved in an experiment involving animals?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A   Are mice capable of controlling their food intake?"}, {"option_text": "B   Does an increase in sugar lead to health problems?"}, {"option_text": "C   How much do supplements of different kinds affect health?"}], "question": "What question do they decide the experiment should address?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A   other types of food supplement."}, {"option_text": "B   different genetic strains of mice."}, {"option_text": "C   varying amounts of exercise."}], "question": "Clare might also consider doing another experiment involving"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a7e11d9b-8d9e-43b0-ae91-5711da7d1731', 'cf4f5acb-c043-4840-8b74-1743cd4a3053', 'matching', 'Questions 15–20', NULL, '<p>Which event in the history of football in the UK took place in each of the following years?</p>
<p>Choose SIX answers from the box and write the correct letter, A–H, next to Questions 15–20.</p>
<p><strong>Events in the history of football</strong></p>
', 'matching_features', NULL, '[{"option": "A", "correct": false}, {"option": "B", "correct": false}, {"option": "C", "correct": false}, {"option": "D", "correct": false}, {"option": "E", "correct": false}, {"option": "F", "correct": false}, {"option": "G", "correct": false}, {"option": "H", "correct": false}]', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p>1870 {the introduction of goalkeepers}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1874 {two changes to the rules of the game}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1875 {a change to the design of the goal}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1877  {an agreement on the length of a game}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1878  {the first use of lights for matches}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>1880  {the introduction of a fee for spectators}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "the introduction of pay for the players"}, {"optionText": "a change to the design of the goal"}, {"optionText": "the first use of lights for matches"}, {"optionText": "the introduction of goalkeepers"}, {"optionText": "the first international match"}, {"optionText": "two changes to the rules of the game"}, {"optionText": "the introduction of a fee for spectators"}, {"optionText": "an agreement on the length of a game"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "1870", "correctAnswer": "the introduction of goalkeepers", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "1874 ", "correctAnswer": "two changes to the rules of the game", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "1875 ", "correctAnswer": "a change to the design of the goal", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "1877 ", "correctAnswer": "an agreement on the length of a game", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "1878 ", "correctAnswer": "the first use of lights for matches", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "1880 ", "correctAnswer": "the introduction of a fee for spectators", "sectionContent": null}]}', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c536c86e-77f3-4221-a0e7-bfa3c22d3f7f', '3338fd2c-1510-4517-8f5c-3de72d6aa4a7', 'matrix', 'Questions 20–23', '', '<p>Look at the following statements (Questions 20–23) and the list of researchers below.</p>
<p>Match each statement with the correct researcher, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>E</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>NB You may use any letter more than once.</strong></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of researchers", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The brain of a good multi-tasker works differently from other people’s.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "The rate of error is considerably higher when people multi-task.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "People are mistaken in their assumption that they can multi-task.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "One gender does not seem to pause to consider before taking action.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Edward M Hallowell", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Paul E Dux", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "David Strayer", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Etienne Koechlin", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Keith Laws", "categoryLetter": "E"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. The brain of a good multi-tasker works differently from other people’s. — {C: David Strayer}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">David Strayer’s research</strong> uncovered that some rare people possess extraordinary multi-tasking ability… these so-called ‘super-taskers’ <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"151\">exhibit different patterns of brain activity</strong> when multi-tasking compared to ordinary people…” (Đoạn mô tả về Super-taskers).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Strayer phát hiện ra rằng não của những người “siêu đa nhiệm” hoạt động với một mô hình khác biệt (hiệu suất cao hơn, ít hoạt động ở vùng vỏ trước trán hơn) so với người bình thường.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. The rate of error is considerably higher when people multi-task. — {C: David Strayer}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Strayer’s research</strong> shows that performance deteriorates drastically when attention is split between tasks, <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">more mistakes are made</strong> and it takes longer to complete each activity.” (Đoạn nói về lái xe và dùng điện thoại).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “More mistakes are made” (nhiều lỗi hơn) tương đương với “The rate of error is considerably higher”. Đây cũng là kết quả nghiên cứu của nhóm David Strayer.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. People are mistaken in their assumption that they can multi-task. — {A: Edward M Hallowell}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Psychiatrist <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">Edward M Hallowell</strong> even describes multi-tasking as a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">‘mythical activity in which people believe they can perform two or more tasks simultaneously…’</strong>” (Đoạn 1).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hallowell coi đa nhiệm là một “hoạt động huyền thoại” (không có thật), nơi mà con người chỉ lầm tưởng (mistaken in their assumption) rằng mình có thể làm nhiều việc cùng lúc hiệu quả.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. One gender does not seem to pause to consider before taking action. — {E: Keith Laws}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “‘It’s as if <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">they [men] don’t stop to reflect and plan for a moment</strong>,’ says Professor <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">Keith Laws</strong>…” (Đoạn nói về giới tính và việc tìm chìa khóa).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khi so sánh về cách tìm chìa khóa bị mất, Keith Laws nhận xét nam giới thường hành động ngay mà không dừng lại để suy nghĩ hay lập kế hoạch (does not pause to consider/stop to reflect).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ad2d22dc-113a-4285-9987-70f91c2bfa0b', '3338fd2c-1510-4517-8f5c-3de72d6aa4a7', 'fillup', 'Questions 24–26', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Super-taskers</strong></span></p>
<p>Super-taskers are those of us who possess special multi-tasking ability. They can be found in all professions. People who are pilots, chefs and doctors are often super-taskers, and super-taskers are most likely to achieve a {position} that is high on the career ladder. Super-taskers typically have to undertake many tasks simultaneously that need their {attention}. Genes play an important role in having this capability; these people have a special brain {structure} which helps them do what we cannot.</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. …and super-taskers are most likely to achieve a {position} that is high on the career ladder.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…we suspect that super-taskers will rise to a top <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">position</strong> in any occupation that places a high demand on juggling various tasks…” (Đoạn 5).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Rise to a top position” (vươn tới vị trí đứng đầu) tương ứng với cụm “achieve a position that is high on the career ladder” (đạt được vị trí cao trên nấc thang sự nghiệp).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. Super-taskers typically have to undertake many tasks simultaneously that need their {attention}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…juggling various tasks that demand <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">attention</strong> at the same time.” (Đoạn 5).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Simultaneously” và “at the same time” đều có nghĩa là cùng một lúc. Những công việc này đòi hỏi sự <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">tập trung (attention)</strong> của họ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. …these people have a special brain {structure} which helps them do what we cannot.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “You are either born with the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">neural structure</strong> that allows you to overcome the usual multi-tasking challenges, or you aren’t.” (Đoạn 6).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định những người này sinh ra đã có một <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">cấu trúc (structure)</strong> thần kinh đặc biệt giúp họ vượt qua những thử thách về đa nhiệm mà người bình thường không làm được.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e1fc4780-4a2f-4d7e-a02e-6fe6c1349152', '1c4126b5-d544-47fa-a01e-a2cef4b46daa', 'checkbox', 'Questions 22-23', '<p>Choose TWO letters, A–E.</p>
<p>Which TWO of the following statements are true of the researchers at London Zoo?</p>
', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO</strong> correct answers.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO</strong> of the following statements are true of the researchers at London Zoo?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', NULL, '[{"option": "A. They are hoping to expand the numbers of different corals being bred in laboratories.", "correct": false}, {"option": "B. They want to identify corals that can cope well with the changed sea conditions.", "correct": true}, {"option": "C. They are looking at ways of creating artificial reefs that corals could grow on.", "correct": false}, {"option": "D. They are trying out methods that would speed up reproduction in some corals.", "correct": true}, {"option": "E. They are investigating materials that might protect reefs from higher temperatures.", "correct": false}]', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>22–23. B &amp; D<br />(Đoạn 5: “Research… to find those that can survive best in warm, acidic waters.” → B<br />“&#8230; aquarium-based research has enabled some corals to spawn artificially…” → D)<br />→ Các nhà khoa học tại London Zoo đang tìm loài chịu được nước ấm (B) và nghiên cứu cách kích thích sinh sản nhân tạo (D). → B &amp; D.</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('335601d5-fe79-42b3-bbe9-361587d9d123', '68b22eac-8871-4d7f-b7f4-3b19b849a610', 'radio', 'Questions 27-29', '', '<p data-path-to-node="2">Choose the correct letter <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="26">A</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="29">B</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="32">C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="37">D</strong>.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="3">Write the correct answer in boxes 27–29 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A Children are portrayed as adults see them."}, {"option_text": "B Children are unable to write their own stories."}, {"option_text": "C Adults fail to stimulate children’s imaginations."}, {"option_text": "D Adult literature is too difficult for children."}], "question": "Which of the following best summarises the writer’s argument in the second paragraph?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A the quality of the writing"}, {"option_text": "B the imaginative content of stories"}, {"option_text": "C the instructive nature of children’s books."}, {"option_text": "D the way children are written about in stories"}], "question": "In the third paragraph, what does the writer say is the main interest of some people who study children''s literature?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A demonstrate that academics consider computer games to be a logical extension of children’s literature."}, {"option_text": "B explore the impact of computers on the boundaries of children’s literature."}, {"option_text": "C illustrate that literature and computer games have different origins."}, {"option_text": "D prove that children are using computers more than they are reading literature."}], "question": "The main point of the writer’s argument in the fifth paragraph is to"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Which of the following best summarises the writer’s argument in the second paragraph? — {A} Children are portrayed as adults see them.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…adult <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">perceptions</strong> of what children are and of what they could and should become are <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">woven into the literature</strong>.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả lập luận rằng vì người lớn viết sách cho trẻ em, nên những quan điểm (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">perceptions</em>) của người lớn về trẻ em sẽ được lồng ghép (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">woven</em>) vào tác phẩm. Điều này khớp với ý: Trẻ em được khắc họa (<em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"210\">portrayed</em>) theo cách người lớn nhìn nhận chúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. In the third paragraph, what does the writer say is the main interest of some people who study children’s literature? — {C} the instructive nature of children’s books.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…less interested in literary values than in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">kinds of lessons it can teach</strong>… much material for children is still <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">didactic</strong>.” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Instructive nature” (tính chất hướng dẫn/giáo huấn) tương ứng với “didactic” và “lessons it can teach”. Một số nhà nghiên cứu quan tâm đến việc cuốn sách dạy được gì hơn là giá trị văn chương của nó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. The main point of the writer’s argument in the fifth paragraph is to — {B} explore the impact of computers on the boundaries of children’s literature.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…create <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">definitional issues</strong> for scholars. Does the term ‘literature’ <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">exclusively imply a verbal text?</strong> If not, where are the <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">limits</strong>? Could a literary computer game ever be considered a work of literature?” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả đặt ra hàng loạt câu hỏi về việc liệu trò chơi máy tính có được coi là văn học không. Điều này nhằm khám phá sự tác động của công nghệ lên “ranh giới” (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"172\">boundaries/limits</em>) định nghĩa thế nào là văn học thiếu nhi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0411bc10-380f-44c5-9534-95f29b56a0cc', '79a1889f-4582-4550-ada0-71bb52f9bb4f', 'fillup', 'Questions 1-10', '<p>Complete the notes below</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>London Relocation Services</strong></span></p>
<p>Customer’s name：Anna Woods</p>
<p>Customer’s personal details</p>
<p>● Current address: 118 {Fordyce} Park, Balyillan</p>
<p>● Postcode:BT14 9BJ</p>
<p>● Phone no: {07840051963} (mobile)</p>
<p>Other information</p>
<p>●Anna is hoping to find work as a {nurse}</p>
<p>● She needs to find a {primary} school for her son.</p>
<p>Requirements for the new property</p>
<p>Location:</p>
<p>● Her preferred location is in the {south} of the city.</p>
<p>●Her husband would like to be neara {station}</p>
<p>●Her son would prefer to be close to a {park}</p>
<p>Property details:</p>
<p>She would like to live in a {house}</p>
<p>She would prefer {3 | three}  bedrooms.</p>
<p>● A small {office} is also desirable.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f44c0a98-e8d3-45c1-b4dd-2b4edec75c2f', '68b22eac-8871-4d7f-b7f4-3b19b849a610', 'radio', 'Questions 30-34', '', '<p data-path-to-node="12,0,0">Choose<strong data-path-to-node="12,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"> YES</strong> if the statement agrees with the views of the writer,<strong data-path-to-node="12,1,0" data-index-in-node="0">NO</strong> if the statement contradicts the views of the writer,<strong data-path-to-node="12,2,0" data-index-in-node="0">NOT GIVEN</strong> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Children tend to make a clear distinction between print literature and electronic media."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The study of children’s literature at higher education institutions is restricted to one subject area."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Exploring children’s perceptions of reading will assist parents to choose suitable books for children."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Adults may appreciate the appeal of illustrated stories better, if they have more information on how children read."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Children should be asked what features they would like digital games to include."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. Children tend to make a clear distinction between print literature and electronic media. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…children themselves undoubtedly perceive their print literature as <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">part of a broader continuum</strong>.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trẻ em coi văn học in ấn là một phần của một “dải liên tục rộng lớn hơn” (bao gồm cả media), tức là chúng <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">không hề</strong> phân biệt rạch ròi (<em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">clear distinction</em>) như người lớn nghĩ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. The study of children’s literature at higher education institutions is restricted to one subject area. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…at least <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">three disciplinary frameworks</strong> (English, education, and librarianship) <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">fragment the focus</strong> of scholarly study…” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc nghiên cứu không bị giới hạn ở một lĩnh vực (<em data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">one subject area</em>) mà bị phân mảnh ở ít nhất ba lĩnh vực khác nhau (Tiếng Anh, Giáo dục, Thư viện).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. Exploring children’s perceptions of reading will assist parents to choose suitable books for children. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7 có nhắc đến việc trẻ em nhìn nhận việc đọc khác với cha mẹ hay thầy cô.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói rằng hiểu trẻ em sẽ giúp hiểu hơn về bản chất của việc đọc, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">không hề khẳng định</strong> việc này sẽ “giúp cha mẹ chọn sách phù hợp” (<em data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"155\">assist parents to choose suitable books</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. Adults may appreciate the appeal of illustrated stories better, if they have more information on how children read. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…when children’s responses to literature are accessed and interpreted, they frequently <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">lead to an understanding of how picture books appeal to children</strong>.” (Đoạn 8)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Illustrated stories” chính là “picture books”. Khi tiếp cận phản hồi của trẻ (biết cách trẻ đọc), người lớn sẽ hiểu được sức hấp dẫn (<em data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">appeal</em>) của loại sách này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Children should be asked what features they would like digital games to include. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn cuối có nói nên hỏi trẻ tại sao trò chơi lại hấp dẫn chúng (<em data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">asking why the game appeals to the player</em>).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tuy nhiên, bài đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">không đề cập</strong> đến việc nên hỏi trẻ về các “tính năng” (<em data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">features</em>) mà chúng muốn “đưa vào” (<em data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">include</em>) trò chơi trong tương lai.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5e381e48-8b0c-4fd4-a646-69395b742a9e', 'bd99ac49-2a17-4de1-a3bf-ff3a16ef61fb', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p data-start="115" data-end="183">Write <strong data-start="149" data-end="166">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-section-id="1fjtqmh" data-start="190" data-end="208"><strong data-start="193" data-end="208">Tardigrades</strong></p>
<ul data-start="210" data-end="349">
<li data-section-id="tcvyn" data-start="210" data-end="264">
<p data-start="212" data-end="264">more than 1,000 species, 0.05–1.2 millimetres long</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="hbj2r3" data-start="265" data-end="349">
<p data-start="267" data-end="349">also known as water ‘bears’ (due to how they {move}) and ‘moss piglets’</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-section-id="5uaevh" data-start="356" data-end="383"><strong data-start="360" data-end="383">Physical appearance</strong></p>
<ul data-start="385" data-end="664">
<li data-section-id="alm5ci" data-start="385" data-end="442">
<p data-start="387" data-end="442">a {short} round body and four pairs of legs</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1ojvg54" data-start="443" data-end="486">
<p data-start="445" data-end="486">claws or {discs} for gripping</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="6ktof8" data-start="487" data-end="520">
<p data-start="489" data-end="520">absence of respiratory organs</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="8l47bu" data-start="521" data-end="596">
<p data-start="523" data-end="596">body filled with a liquid that carries both {oxygen} and blood</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="17nborh" data-start="597" data-end="664">
<p data-start="599" data-end="664">mouth shaped like a {tube} with teeth called stylets</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-section-id="i3amn9" data-start="671" data-end="686"><strong data-start="675" data-end="686">Habitat</strong></p>
<ul data-start="688" data-end="809">
<li data-section-id="z0g754" data-start="688" data-end="740">
<p data-start="690" data-end="740">often found at the bottom of a lake or on plants</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1hkwhke" data-start="741" data-end="809">
<p data-start="743" data-end="809">very resilient and can exist in very low or high {temperatures}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-section-id="1yr7n8o" data-start="816" data-end="836"><strong data-start="820" data-end="836">Cryptobiosis</strong></p>
<ul data-start="838" data-end="1115">
<li data-section-id="1bze2gd" data-start="838" data-end="898">
<p data-start="840" data-end="898">In dry conditions, they roll into a ball called a ‘tun’.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1iczbtn" data-start="899" data-end="959">
<p data-start="901" data-end="959">They stay alive with a much lower metabolism than usual.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1hxo5te" data-start="960" data-end="1025">
<p data-start="962" data-end="1025">A type of {protein} ensures their DNA is not damaged.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="j5zi40" data-start="1026" data-end="1115">
<p data-start="1028" data-end="1115">Research is underway to find out how many days they can stay alive in {space}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-section-id="fvah9g" data-start="1122" data-end="1137"><strong data-start="1126" data-end="1137">Feeding</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1139" data-end="1236">
<li data-section-id="dcgdi0" data-start="1139" data-end="1206">
<p data-start="1141" data-end="1206">consume liquids, e.g., those found in moss or {seaweed}</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1tx60rp" data-start="1207" data-end="1236">
<p data-start="1209" data-end="1236">may eat other tardigrades</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-section-id="ltp8f" data-start="1243" data-end="1270"><strong data-start="1247" data-end="1270">Conservation status</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1272" data-end="1321">
<li data-section-id="rpy0ex" data-start="1272" data-end="1321">
<p data-start="1274" data-end="1321">They are not considered to be {endangered}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>For my project on invertebrates, I chose to study tardigrades. These are microscopic – or to be more precise – near-microscopic animals. There are well over a thousand known species of these tiny animals, which belong to the phylum Tardigrada. Most tardigrades range in length from 0.05 to 1 millimetre, though the largest species can grow to be 1.2 millimetres in length. They are also sometimes called ‘water bears’: ‘water’ because that’s where they thrive best, and ‘bear’ <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(31) because of the way they move</strong></span>. ‘Moss piglet’ is another name for tardigrade because of the way they look when viewed from the front. They were first discovered in Germany in 1773 by Johann Goeze, who coined the name Tardigrada.</p>\n<p>As I say, there are many different species of tardigrade – too many to describe here – but, generally speaking, the different species share similar physical traits. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(32) They have a body which is short</span></strong>, and also rounded – a bit like a barrel – and the body comprises four segments. Each segment has a pair of legs, at the end of which are between four and eight sharp claws. I should also say that some species don’t have any claws; <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(33) what they have are discs</strong></span>, and these work by means of suction. They enable the tardigrade to cling on to surfaces or to grip its prey. Within the body, there are no lungs, or any organs for breathing at all. Instead, <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(34) oxygen and also blood are transported in a fluid that fills the cavity of the body.</span></strong></p>\n<p>As far as the tardigrade’s head is concerned, the best way I can describe this is that it looks rather strange – a bit squashed even – though many of the websites I looked at described its appearance as cute, which isn’t exactly very scientific. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(35) The tardigrade’s mouth is a kind of tube</strong></span> that can open outwards to reveal teeth-like structures known as ‘stylets’. These are sharp enough to pierce plant or animal cells.</p>\n<p>So, where are tardigrades found? Well, they live in every part of the world, in a variety of habitats: most commonly, on the bed of a lake, or on many kinds of plants or in very wet environments. There’s been some interesting research which has found that tardigrades are capable of surviving radiation and very high pressure, and <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(36) they’re also able to withstand temperatures as cold as −200 degrees centigrade, or highs of more than 148 degrees centigrade</strong></span>, which is incredibly hot.</p>\n<p>It has been said that tardigrades could survive long after human beings have been wiped out, even in the event of an asteroid hitting the earth. If conditions become too extreme and tardigrades are at risk of drying out, they enter a state called cryptobiosis. They curl into a ball, called a tun – that’s T-U-N – by retracting their head and legs, and their metabolism drops to less than one percent of normal levels. They can remain like this until they are re-introduced to water, when they will come back to life in a matter of a few hours. While in a state of cryptobiosis, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(37) tardigrades produce a protein that protects their DNA</strong></span>. In 2016, scientists revived two tardigrades that had been frozen for more than 30 years. There was a report that, in 1948, a 120-year-old tun was revived, but this experiment has never been repeated. There are currently several <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(38) tests taking place in space to determine how long tardigrades might be able to survive there</span></strong>. I believe the record so far is 10 days.</p>\n<p>So, erm, moving on. In terms of their diet, tardigrades consume liquids in order to survive. Although they have teeth, they don’t use these for chewing. <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(39) They suck up juices from moss, or extract fluid from seaweed</span></strong>, but some species prey on other tardigrades, from other species or within their own. I suppose this isn’t surprising, given that tardigrades are mainly comprised of liquid and are coated with a type of gel.</p>\n<p>Finally, I’d like to mention the conservation status of tardigrades. It is estimated that they have been in existence for approximately half a billion years and, in that time, they have survived five mass extinctions. So, it will probably come as no surprise to you, <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(40) that tardigrades have not been evaluated by the International Union for Conservation of Nature and are not on any endangered list</span></strong>. Some researchers have described them as thriving.</p>\n<p>Does anyone have any questions they’d like to ask?</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b18e8b64-c656-4f36-90db-a10e139cb560', '7b70c3ae-8ad6-4ff8-8b7a-24496887b2b8', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–5', '<p> Complete the table below.</p>
<p data-start="190" data-end="230"><span role="text"><strong data-start="194" data-end="230">Ohope Holiday Park Accommodation</strong></span></p>
<div class="TyagGW_tableContainer">
<div class="group TyagGW_tableWrapper flex flex-col-reverse w-fit" tabindex="-1">
<table class="w-fit min-w-(--thread-content-width)" style="width: 99.9989%; height: 229.75px; border-collapse: collapse; border-spacing: 2px; border: 2px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);" border="1" data-start="232" data-end="640">
<thead data-start="232" data-end="292">
<tr style="height: 53.1875px;" data-start="232" data-end="292">
<th class="" style="width: 11.5011%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-start="232" data-end="248" data-col-size="sm">
<p><strong>Type of cabin</strong></p>
</th>
<th class="" style="width: 15.2877%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-start="248" data-end="259" data-col-size="sm">
<p><strong>Location</strong></p>
</th>
<th class="" style="width: 27.9231%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-start="259" data-end="272" data-col-size="sm">
<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p>
</th>
<th class="" style="width: 37.3025%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-start="272" data-end="292" data-col-size="md">
<p><strong>Cost and charges</strong></p>
</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody data-start="354" data-end="640">
<tr style="height: 70.1875px;" data-start="354" data-end="436">
<td style="width: 11.5011%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-start="354" data-end="362" data-col-size="sm">
<p>Basic</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 15.2877%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-col-size="sm" data-start="362" data-end="381">
<p>next to the pool</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 27.9231%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-col-size="sm" data-start="381" data-end="419">
<p>kitchen has a fridge and a {Microwave}</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 37.3025%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-col-size="md" data-start="419" data-end="436">
<p>$35 per night</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 53.1875px;" data-start="437" data-end="525">
<td style="width: 11.5011%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-start="437" data-end="448" data-col-size="sm">
<p>Standard</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 15.2877%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-col-size="sm" data-start="448" data-end="468">
<p>close to {Reception}</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 27.9231%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-col-size="sm" data-start="468" data-end="508">
<p>fully-equipped kitchen and a {Shower}</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 37.3025%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-col-size="md" data-start="508" data-end="525">
<p>$55 per night</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 53.1875px;" data-start="526" data-end="640">
<td style="width: 11.5011%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-start="526" data-end="542" data-col-size="sm">
<p>Standard Plus</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 15.2877%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-col-size="sm" data-start="542" data-end="564">
<p>facing the {Lake}</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 27.9231%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-col-size="sm" data-start="564" data-end="585">
<p>comes with own spa</p>
</td>
<td style="width: 37.3025%; border-color: #000000; padding: 2px; border-width: 2px;" data-col-size="md" data-start="585" data-end="640">
<p>discount of {18} % for bookings over ten nights</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: OHOPE HOLIDAY PARK ACCOMMODATION</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Good morning, Ohope Holiday Park.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Oh hello. We''re planning on coming to Ohope for a couple of weeks during the summer holidays, and some friends of mine recommended your holiday park, particularly the wooden cabins you have.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> That''s good to hear. Well, we have different types of cabin available.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Can you tell me about the most basic type?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Yes, we have a couple of cabins still available which are right beside the pool.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> That sounds great.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Yes, they are in a good spot. They have one main living area and there''s another room with the beds. If you want to do any cooking, there''s a communal kitchen that everyone uses, but otherwise, the kitchen in the cabin just has a fridge—a small one—and also a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"267\">(Q1) microwave</strong></span></span> for heating things up.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> I see. And what''s the cost of that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> That''s $35 per night.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay. And what other types of cabin do you have?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Right, we have our standard cabins. These are near <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">(Q2) reception</strong></span></span>, so that''s handy if you want to come in and get us to book a trip or anything. The kitchen is fully equipped too, so you can do all your cooking there.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> What other facilities does it have? Is there a television?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> In the standard cabin.I''m afraid not, but it has a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">(Q3) shower</strong></span>, which you don''t get in the basic cabin.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman: </strong>And that''s $55 a night inclusive.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man: </strong>And is there another cabin type?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Yes, the standard plus. All of these cabins are directly opposite the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">(Q4) lake</strong></span>, and they all come with a private spa as well.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Sounds good.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman: </strong>I should tell you that these cabins are quite popular, so I''d advise you to book as soon as possible.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man: </strong>I don''t suppose there''s a discount for booking for a longer period?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> There is actually for the standard plus. Once you go up to five nights, there''s a 15% discount and anything more than 10 nights, it''s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">(Q5) 18%</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man: </strong>I''ll give it some thought. I think we''ll probably go for the standard.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">GENERAL INFORMATION (Questions 6–10)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> So for children, what kind of activities can they do at the holiday park? Do you have a trampoline or anything?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> No, but a lot of the kids who come here do <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">(Q6) tennis</strong></span>. It cost nothing to use our court, and they can come borrow the rackets from us as long as they bring them back, of course.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Great, my kids would be into that. And we''re planning to bring our boat with us and get out on the water. Is it possible for an afternoon or something to hire some equipment? We''re hoping to go <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">(Q7) fishing</strong></span>, but we don''t have our own stuff.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Yes, for a small charge, we can let you have some equipment.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Fantastic. Is there anything else for kids to do in the Ohope area?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Well, on Saturday or Sunday, you might like to go to the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">(Q8) farm</strong></span>. It''s only a short drive from the holiday park. You can go riding there and see how everything works. It''s quite a popular thing to do.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay, I''ll just make a note of that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Actually, one thing I would recommend, depending on whether your children don''t mind a late night...</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"1064\">Man:</strong> I''m sure they wouldn''t.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"1093\">Woman: </strong>Well, it''s a guided tour, $20 for a family every evening, and you go along with the guide into the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"207\">(Q9) forest</strong></span>. That''s when the native birds wake up, and it''s a great chance to see them in their natural habitat.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> My daughter would love that. Now I just wanna check all this with my wife. Will you still be there in 30 minutes?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> No, I''m going on my lunch break, but I''ll pass your details on to someone else who can confirm your reservation. Her name''s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">(Q10) Arataki</strong></span>. That''s A-R-A-T-A-K-I.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Alright, thank you.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> You''re welcome.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3d772dbb-ae91-4072-814b-7b9772e63a82', 'd025bf33-61da-4a94-8e3a-79e55937d701', 'matching', 'Questions 26–30', '', '<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="19" data-index-in-node="7">FIVE</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="19" data-index-in-node="63">A–H</strong>, next to Questions 26–30.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.953%; height: 52.9167px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 99.859%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 52.9167px;\">\n<td style=\"padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;\">\n<p>Choose mice which are all the same {C   age}</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">🔽</p>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.953%; height: 2px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 99.859%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;\">\n<p>Divide the mice into two groups, each with a different {H   colour}</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">🔽</p>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9516%; height: 2px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 99.8549%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,4,0\">Put each group in a separate cage.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,5,0\">Feed group A commercial mouse food.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,6,0\">Feed group B the same, but also sugar contained in {C   age}</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">🔽</p>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9516%; height: 2px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 99.8549%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,8,0\">Take measurements using an electronic scale.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,9,0\">Place them in a weighing chamber to prevent {B   escape}</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">🔽</p>\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9516%; height: 2px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 1px solid #000000;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 99.8549%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;\">\n<p>Do all necessary {F   calculations}</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A   size"}, {"optionText": "B   escape"}, {"optionText": "C   age"}, {"optionText": "D   water"}, {"optionText": "E   cereal"}, {"optionText": "F   calculations"}, {"optionText": "G   changes"}, {"optionText": "H   colour"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5d1c60ec-5c32-406c-a392-14840ac3804f', '7b70c3ae-8ad6-4ff8-8b7a-24496887b2b8', 'fillup', 'Questions 6-10', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><strong>General information about the holiday park and the Ohope area:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The children can play {tennis} for free.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>It’s possible to hire equipment for {fishing} for an afternoon.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The children could visit the local {farm} on Saturday and Sunday.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>There are guided tours of the {forest} every evening to see the birds.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Contact  {arataki} to confirm the booking</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2270eb7d-0f97-4d71-a7a4-20b553339ea6', '6259a8b7-a323-45d5-bc60-9fc5a5f3de77', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–6', '<p data-section-id="drgmz8" data-start="245" data-end="270">Write<strong> ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-section-id="drgmz8" data-start="245" data-end="270"><strong data-start="249" data-end="270">First day at work</strong></p>
<ul data-start="272" data-end="574">
<li data-section-id="60zs4d" data-start="272" data-end="310">
<p data-start="274" data-end="310">Name of supervisor: {Kaeden}</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1qh42mk" data-start="311" data-end="379">
<p data-start="313" data-end="379">Where to leave coat and bag: use {locker} in staffroom  </p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1f94ei8" data-start="380" data-end="468">
<p data-start="382" data-end="468">See Tiffany in HR: to give {passport} number<br data-start="436" data-end="439">                              to collect {uniform}</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="115opsq" data-start="469" data-end="523">
<p data-start="471" data-end="523">Location of HR office: on<strong data-start="501" data-end="517"> </strong>{third| 3rd} floor</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1obwvmf" data-start="524" data-end="574">
<p data-start="526" data-end="574">Supervisor’s mobile number: {0412 665 903}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-start=\"157\" data-end=\"244\"><strong data-start=\"157\" data-end=\"168\">KAEDEN:</strong> Hello Charlotte. I’m Kaeden, one of the supervisors. Welcome to the team.</p>\n<p data-start=\"246\" data-end=\"273\"><strong data-start=\"246\" data-end=\"260\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> Hi Aiden.</p>\n<p data-start=\"275\" data-end=\"301\"><strong data-start=\"275\" data-end=\"286\">KAEDEN:</strong> It’s <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(1) Kaeden.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"303\" data-end=\"330\"><strong data-start=\"303\" data-end=\"317\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> I’m sorry.</p>\n<p data-start=\"332\" data-end=\"476\"><strong data-start=\"332\" data-end=\"343\">KAEDEN:</strong> Don’t worry. People often get my name wrong; they never know how to spell it. It’s K-A-E-D-E-N, in case you ever need to write it.</p>\n<p data-start=\"478\" data-end=\"517\"><strong data-start=\"478\" data-end=\"492\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> I’ll try and remember.</p>\n<p data-start=\"519\" data-end=\"761\"><strong data-start=\"519\" data-end=\"530\">KAEDEN:</strong> So, there are a few practical things you need to sort out this morning. Then I’ll show you what you’re going to do today. The email I received said to go to the front desk, to show my letter of appointment and pick up my badge.</p>\n<p data-start=\"763\" data-end=\"880\"><strong data-start=\"763\" data-end=\"777\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> You’ll need that for the staffroom and other areas of the supermarket where shoppers aren’t allowed.</p>\n<p data-start=\"882\" data-end=\"1056\"><strong data-start=\"882\" data-end=\"893\">KAEDEN:</strong> So, after you’ve finished at the front desk, I’ll take you to the staffroom. Put your coat and rucksack in one of the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(2) lockers </strong></span>there. Take whichever one is free.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1058\" data-end=\"1093\"><strong data-start=\"1058\" data-end=\"1072\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> Will I have a key?</p>\n<p data-start=\"1095\" data-end=\"1205\"><strong data-start=\"1095\" data-end=\"1106\">KAEDEN:</strong> Yes. Try not to lose it. At the end of the day, leave it in the door for the next person to use.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1207\" data-end=\"1304\"><strong data-start=\"1207\" data-end=\"1221\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> Well, do I need to go to the HR department to see Tiffany? She’s really helpful.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1306\" data-end=\"1448\"><strong data-start=\"1306\" data-end=\"1317\">KAEDEN:</strong> I was told to bring my <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(3) passport </strong></span>with me. HR need to take a note of the number in it. That’s right. Or you can show your ID card.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1450\" data-end=\"1493\"><strong data-start=\"1450\" data-end=\"1464\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> I don’t have one of those.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1495\" data-end=\"1720\"><strong data-start=\"1495\" data-end=\"1506\">KAEDEN:</strong> OK. Tiffany will give you a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(4) uniform</strong></span>. They have lots in different sizes, so you just tell her what you need. I won’t come with you to HR – I’ve got to go and sort something else out. Probably with a bread slicer.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1722\" data-end=\"1775\"><strong data-start=\"1722\" data-end=\"1736\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> Is the HR office near the staffroom?</p>\n<p data-start=\"1777\" data-end=\"1931\"><strong data-start=\"1777\" data-end=\"1788\">KAEDEN:</strong> The staffroom’s on the first floor, and HR are a couple of floors above that, on the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(5) third</strong></span> floor. There’s a staircase outside the staffroom.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1933\" data-end=\"1953\"><strong data-start=\"1933\" data-end=\"1947\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> OK.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1955\" data-end=\"2050\"><strong data-start=\"1955\" data-end=\"1966\">KAEDEN:</strong> When you’ve finished with HR, come and find me in the bakery section of the shop.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2052\" data-end=\"2108\"><strong data-start=\"2052\" data-end=\"2066\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> I’m looking forward to getting started.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2110\" data-end=\"2217\"><strong data-start=\"2110\" data-end=\"2121\">KAEDEN:</strong> I’ll just give you my phone number, in case you can’t find me. Have you got your phone there?</p>\n<p data-start=\"2219\" data-end=\"2252\"><strong data-start=\"2219\" data-end=\"2233\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> Yes … OK, ready.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2254\" data-end=\"2317\"><strong data-start=\"2254\" data-end=\"2265\">KAEDEN:</strong> It’s <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(6) oh-four-one, double-six-five, nine-oh-three.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"2319\" data-end=\"2345\"><strong data-start=\"2319\" data-end=\"2333\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> OK, done.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2352\" data-end=\"2618\"><strong data-start=\"2352\" data-end=\"2363\">KAEDEN:</strong> So, Charlotte, your tasks today are in the bakery section, on the sushi counter, and on the meat and fish counters. The first job is to check sell-by dates on the bread and cakes. If any of the dates are today’s, put a new price label on the packaging.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2620\" data-end=\"2724\"><strong data-start=\"2620\" data-end=\"2634\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> What if any of the labels are yesterday’s dates, or older? Do I throw those items away?</p>\n<p data-start=\"2726\" data-end=\"2903\"><strong data-start=\"2726\" data-end=\"2737\">KAEDEN:</strong> Yes, but that shouldn’t happen – we check the stock every day. When something needs a new price label, put a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(7) yellow</strong></span> one on the package, next to the original price.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2905\" data-end=\"2925\"><strong data-start=\"2905\" data-end=\"2919\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> OK.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2927\" data-end=\"2993\"><strong data-start=\"2927\" data-end=\"2938\">KAEDEN:</strong> After that, you’ll go to the sushi takeaway counter.</p>\n<p data-start=\"2995\" data-end=\"3046\"><strong data-start=\"2995\" data-end=\"3009\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> Will I be preparing boxes of food?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3048\" data-end=\"3106\"><strong data-start=\"3048\" data-end=\"3059\">KAEDEN:</strong> For today, you’ll just be helping the staff.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3108\" data-end=\"3140\"><strong data-start=\"3108\" data-end=\"3122\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> Yes, of course.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3142\" data-end=\"3354\"><strong data-start=\"3142\" data-end=\"3153\">KAEDEN:</strong> You’ll see lots of flat cardboard boxes at one end of the counter. Beneath those is where we keep the <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(8) plastic</span></strong> boxes – we run out of those really quickly, so you should bring more from the storeroom.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3356\" data-end=\"3415\"><strong data-start=\"3356\" data-end=\"3370\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> Is that my only task on the sushi counter?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3417\" data-end=\"3594\"><strong data-start=\"3417\" data-end=\"3428\">KAEDEN:</strong> No. You also need to clean the area where they prepare the dishes. There are cloths and bottles of spray by the sink. Oh, and please make sure you clean the floor.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3596\" data-end=\"3646\"><strong data-start=\"3596\" data-end=\"3610\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> Sure. That’s important, isn’t it?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3648\" data-end=\"3780\"><strong data-start=\"3648\" data-end=\"3659\">KAEDEN:</strong> Absolutely. But you mustn’t wash up knives. You have to do some training before you’re allowed to touch sharp objects.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3782\" data-end=\"3833\"><strong data-start=\"3782\" data-end=\"3796\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> What should I do if there are any?</p>\n<p data-start=\"3835\" data-end=\"3891\"><strong data-start=\"3835\" data-end=\"3846\">KAEDEN:</strong> Ask someone to put them in the dishwasher.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3893\" data-end=\"3957\"><strong data-start=\"3893\" data-end=\"3907\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> OK, thanks. I don’t want to get anything wrong.</p>\n<p data-start=\"3959\" data-end=\"4029\"><strong data-start=\"3959\" data-end=\"3970\">KAEDEN:</strong> Don’t worry. You’ll be fine. And I’ll be around to help.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4036\" data-end=\"4187\"><strong data-start=\"4036\" data-end=\"4047\">KAEDEN:</strong> Right. Finally, the meat and fish counters. You need to clean the area where staff serve customers, including wiping the weighing scales.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4189\" data-end=\"4224\"><strong data-start=\"4189\" data-end=\"4203\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> OK. Anything else?</p>\n<p data-start=\"4226\" data-end=\"4338\"><strong data-start=\"4226\" data-end=\"4237\">KAEDEN:</strong> The fish is laid on <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(9) ice,</strong></span> but when that starts to melt, you’ll need to get more from the cold-room.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4340\" data-end=\"4408\"><strong data-start=\"4340\" data-end=\"4354\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> I know the cold-room – the food counters are clear.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4410\" data-end=\"4633\"><strong data-start=\"4410\" data-end=\"4421\">KAEDEN:</strong> You won’t be serving customers directly, so no. But make sure you put on thermal <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(10) gloves</strong></span> when you take anything out of the cold-room. The temperature’s low enough in there to get frostbite from touching things.</p>\n<p data-start=\"4635\" data-end=\"4663\"><strong data-start=\"4635\" data-end=\"4649\">CHARLOTTE:</strong> Understood.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ca8e3b36-3451-4d81-99be-739b6e8a4f77', '68b22eac-8871-4d7f-b7f4-3b19b849a610', 'matching', 'Questions 35–39', '', '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, <strong>A–H</strong>, below.</p>', 'matching_name', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "accepting that literature exists in a variety of forms today."}, {"optionText": "verbalising the words in their heads."}, {"optionText": "discovering the reading techniques used by others."}, {"optionText": "the style of written stories changing over time."}, {"optionText": "the lack of some specific abilities."}, {"optionText": "a deeper knowledge of the intricacies of reading."}, {"optionText": "children teaching adults to play computer games."}, {"optionText": "creating a variety of images in their minds."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Young people’s accounts of how they read lead to", "correctAnswer": "F"}, {"questionPart": "The risk of solipsism is reduced by", "correctAnswer": "C"}, {"questionPart": "Strong visualisers judge books on the basis that they are", "correctAnswer": "H"}, {"questionPart": "Children’s insights are important in", "correctAnswer": "A"}, {"questionPart": "When adults read a book more easily than they play a digital game, it simply suggests", "correctAnswer": "E"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Young people’s accounts of how they read lead to {F: a deeper knowledge of the intricacies of reading}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Young people’s accounts of what and how they read also enable a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">more sophisticated description of many of the complex processes</strong> involved in reading.” (Đoạn 9)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “More sophisticated description” (mô tả tinh vi hơn) tương ứng với “deeper knowledge” (kiến thức sâu sắc hơn). “Complex processes” (quá trình phức tạp) tương ứng với “intricacies” (sự phức tạp/tỉ mỉ).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. The risk of solipsism is reduced by {C: discovering the reading techniques used by others}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Asking <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"19\">other readers how they read</strong>, however, <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">reduces that risk [of solipsism]</strong>.” (Đoạn 9)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc hỏi những người đọc khác xem họ đọc như thế nào (tức là khám phá các kỹ thuật đọc của họ – <em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">reading techniques used by others</em>) giúp giảm bớt rủi ro của tính duy ngã (solipsism).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Strong visualisers judge books on the basis that they are {H: creating a variety of images in their minds}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…if I am a <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">strong visualizer</strong>… I may judge books by their capacity to evoke a <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">vivid visual response</strong>.” (Đoạn 9)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Strong visualizer” (người có khả năng hình dung mạnh mẽ) sẽ đánh giá sách dựa trên khả năng gợi lên những hình ảnh sống động (vivid visual response), tương ứng với việc tạo ra nhiều hình ảnh trong tâm trí (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"219\">creating a variety of images in their minds</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Children’s insights are important in {A: accepting that literature exists in a variety of forms today}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Children’s insights are even more important when it comes to understanding the significance of print literature as <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">one aspect of literary culture</strong>.” (Đoạn 10)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hiểu được văn học in ấn chỉ là <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">một khía cạnh</strong> của văn hóa văn học (bao gồm cả game, media…) đồng nghĩa với việc chấp nhận rằng văn học ngày nay tồn tại dưới nhiều hình thức khác nhau (<em data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">variety of forms</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. When adults read a book more easily than they play a digital game, it simply suggests {E: the lack of some specific abilities}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “This does not indicate that a book is better, but that a <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">particular set of skills is absent</strong>.” (Đoạn 10)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc người lớn thấy đọc sách dễ hơn chơi game không có nghĩa là sách tốt hơn, mà đơn giản là do họ đang thiếu đi một số kỹ năng cụ thể (<em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">particular set of skills is absent</em> tương ứng với <em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">lack of some specific abilities</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9730b684-cbf3-445f-aadc-6130f5e13783', 'de4cc89f-516a-4b2a-ae69-e415a5e3fdc5', 'checkbox', 'Questions 20-21', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "There should be a person with legal training in every hospital.", "correct": false}, {"option": "Lawyers with experience in commercial law are the most in demand.", "correct": false}, {"option": "Knowledge of the law is as important as having computer skills.", "correct": true}, {"option": "Society could not function effectively without legal experts.", "correct": true}, {"option": "Schools should teach students about the law.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>20. Knowledge of the law is as important as having computer skills.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) Tác giả so sánh tầm quan trọng của luật pháp với công nghệ thông tin: “Those people, for example, with knowledge of computers, the internet, and communications technology are relied upon by the rest of us… But <strong>legal understanding is just as vital and as universally needed</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định rằng hiểu biết về pháp luật (<strong>legal understanding</strong>) cũng quan trọng (<em>“just as vital”</em>) và cần thiết trên toàn cầu như kỹ năng công nghệ (computer skills).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>21. Society could not function effectively without legal experts.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) Tác giả sử dụng ví dụ về IT: “Without their knowledge, many parts of commercial and social life today <strong>would seize up in minutes</strong>.” Ngay sau đó, tác giả nói: “<strong>But legal understanding is just as vital and as universally needed</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bằng cách so sánh, tác giả ngụ ý rằng nếu không có kiến thức pháp lý (legal experts), xã hội và thương mại sẽ bị đình trệ (<em>“seize up”</em>), tức là không thể hoạt động hiệu quả. Hơn nữa, luật sư là người hiểu rõ “luật chơi” (<em>“the lawyer is the only person who has read the inside of the top of the box”</em>), điều tối quan trọng cho một xã hội có tổ chức.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d15f82f9-a0f6-4183-a253-476461129f33', 'de4cc89f-516a-4b2a-ae69-e415a5e3fdc5', 'fillup', 'Questions 22-26', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>LAWYERS AS PROFESSIONALS</strong></p>
<p>People sometimes say that {Truth} is of little interest to lawyers, who are more concerned with making money. This may well be the case with some individuals, in the same way that some {Journalists} or scientific experts may also be driven purely by financial greed. However, criticizing lawyers because their work is concerned with people’s problems would be similar to attacking IT staff or {Nurses} for the same reason. In fact, many lawyers focus on questions relating, for example, to housing or civil liberties, which requires them to have {Dedication}, to their work. What’s more, a lot of lawyers’ time is spent writing {Documents} rather than dealing with people’s misfortunes.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>22. People sometimes say that <strong>Truth</strong> is of little interest to lawyers, who are more concerned with making money.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Truth</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) People sometimes make comments that characterise lawyers as professionals whose concerns put personal reward above <strong>truth</strong>, or who gain financially from misfortune.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Câu tóm tắt mở đầu bằng việc đề cập đến lời chỉ trích rằng luật sư coi trọng tiền bạc hơn sự thật (<strong>Truth</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>23. This may well be the case with some individuals, in the same way that some <strong>Journalists</strong> or scientific experts may also be driven purely by financial greed.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Journalists</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) There are undoubtedly lawyers that would fit that bill, just as there are some scientists, <strong>journalists</strong> and others in that category.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản so sánh hành vi tiêu cực của luật sư với các nhóm nghề nghiệp khác, bao gồm các nhà khoa học và nhà báo (<strong>Journalists</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>24. However, criticizing lawyers because their work is concerned with people’s problems would be similar to attacking IT staff or <strong>Nurses</strong> for the same reason.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Nurses</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) But, in general, it is no more just to say that lawyers are bad because they make a living from people’s problems than it is to make the same accusation in respect of <strong>nurses</strong> or IT consultants.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả sử dụng y tá (<strong>Nurses</strong>) và chuyên gia tư vấn IT để chỉ ra sự bất công khi chỉ trích luật sư kiếm sống từ vấn đề của người khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>25. In fact, many lawyers focus on questions relating, for example, to housing or civil liberties, which requires them to have <strong>Dedication</strong> to their work.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Dedication</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) Such work is not lavishly remunerated and the quality of the service provided by these lawyers relies on considerable professional <strong>dedication</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Công việc luật công (public law work) đòi hỏi sự <strong>tận tâm</strong> (<strong>Dedication</strong>) cao độ vì thù lao không hào phóng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>26. What’s more, a lot of lawyers’ time is spent writing <strong>Documents</strong> rather than dealing with people’s misfortunes.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Documents</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) Moreover, much legal work has nothing to do with conflict or misfortune, but is primarily concerned with drafting <strong>documents</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Một phần lớn công việc pháp lý liên quan đến việc soạn thảo tài liệu (<strong>Documents</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('69bf69db-860e-47d9-af4f-89296a36e0a7', '514b2588-3cf9-4edb-bc5a-df145915c4ae', 'matrix', ' Questions 14–19', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has eight paragraphs, <strong>A-H</strong>.</p>
<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A-H</strong>, in boxes 14-19.</p>
<p><strong>NB </strong>You may use any letter more than once.</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a description of how rapid change has a negative effect on people", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a reference to an architect whose designs were uncharacteristic of biophilia", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "a definition of the two main aims of biophilia", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "a positive claim about early forms of architecture", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "a reference to the fact that many architects are too focused on innovation", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "a description of features which conserve energy in a biophilic design", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"4\">14. a description of how rapid change has a negative effect on people</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “The rates of technological progress are far exceeding rates of psychological evolution, leaving us <strong>ill-equipped to cope with our lifestyle, which in turn leads to increased stress</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C mô tả tốc độ tiến bộ công nghệ quá nhanh (<em>rapid change</em>) dẫn đến việc con người không thể thích nghi, gây ra <strong>căng thẳng gia tăng</strong> (<em>increased stress</em> / negative effect on people).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"7\">15. a reference to an architect whose designs were uncharacteristic of biophilia</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “Though not technically a biophilic design, Fallingwater – the stunning house in rural Pennsylvania designed in the 1930s by Frank Lloyd Wright – arguably speaks to the human soul much more than the <strong>box-like blocks of flats designed by his contemporary Le Corbusier</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả sử dụng kiến trúc sư Le Corbusier với những khối nhà hộp (<em>box-like blocks of flats</em>) như một ví dụ trái ngược (<em>uncharacteristic</em>) với triết lý thiết kế ái sinh (biophilia), vốn ưu tiên nhu cầu tâm lý con người.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"10\">16. a definition of the two main aims of biophilia</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) “The premise of biophilic design seeks both to <strong>avoid or minimize harmful impacts on the natural environment</strong>, and equally importantly, to <strong>provide and restore beneficial contacts between people and nature</strong> in the built environment.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A đưa ra <strong>hai mục tiêu chính</strong> (<em>two main aims</em>): giảm thiểu tác động xấu lên môi trường và khôi phục liên hệ có lợi giữa con người và thiên nhiên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"13\">17. a positive claim about early forms of architecture</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>H</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) “Ancient architects built for their cultures… They mimicked nature’s forms, producing <strong>magnificent structures with which we are still awed</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn H ca ngợi (<em>positive claim</em>) các kiến trúc sư cổ đại đã tạo ra <strong>các cấu trúc tráng lệ</strong> (<em>magnificent structures</em>) khiến chúng ta vẫn kinh ngạc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"16\">18. a reference to the fact that many architects are too focused on innovation</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “All too often, architects have put <strong>creative originality</strong> before the needs of the people who have to live and work in their futuristic constructions, with scant regard for emotional, as well as practical, considerations.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc đặt <strong>sự độc đáo sáng tạo</strong> (<em>creative originality</em> / innovation) lên trên nhu cầu của con người cho thấy sự tập trung quá mức vào sự đổi mới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"19\">19. a description of features which conserve energy in a biophilic design</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>F</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “The Lewis Center is sustainable in a broader sense… It <strong>harnesses solar power, utilizes both active and passive air systems</strong>, and monitors the weather to adapt to conditions.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn F mô tả các tính năng sử dụng năng lượng mặt trời (<em>solar power</em>) và hệ thống không khí thụ động/chủ động, là các tính năng nhằm <strong>bảo tồn năng lượng</strong> (<em>conserve energy</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8dfd6f20-125b-423a-a42b-f09f2536a73c', '68b22eac-8871-4d7f-b7f4-3b19b849a610', 'radio', 'Question 40', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="26">A, B, C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="37">D</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A to evaluate how the process of reading fits into children’s literature studies"}, {"option_text": "B to discuss the impact of the increasing commercial influence on children’s literature studies"}, {"option_text": "C to review the challenges in the field of children’s literature studies and suggest how to proceed"}, {"option_text": "D to provide arguments in favor of including computerized forms in children’s literature studies"}], "question": "What was the writer’s main purpose in writing this article?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. What was the writer’s main purpose in writing this article? — {C} to review the challenges in the field of children’s literature studies and suggest how to proceed.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Phân tích cấu trúc bài viết:</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Phần đầu (Đoạn 1 – 6):</strong> Tác giả liệt kê hàng loạt các khó khăn và yếu tố gây nhiễu trong ngành nghiên cứu văn học thiếu nhi như: sự áp đặt của người lớn, tính giáo huấn (didactic), áp lực thương mại, sự cạnh tranh của truyền thông mới và sự phân mảnh trong học thuật. Đây chính là phần <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"285\">“review the challenges”</strong> (xem xét các thách thức).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Phần sau (Đoạn 7 – 10):</strong> Tác giả đưa ra giải pháp: “One route through this maze is to ask the child readers for help” (Một con đường thoát khỏi mê cung này là nhờ sự giúp đỡ của chính những độc giả nhí). Tác giả dành toàn bộ phần còn lại để lập luận tại sao việc lắng nghe trẻ em là cần thiết để hiểu về bản chất việc đọc và các hình thức văn học mới (game). Đây chính là phần <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"376\">“suggest how to proceed”</strong> (gợi ý cách tiếp cận tiếp theo).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('24e64efb-308d-4b36-8ffe-4d190a4b622f', 'e06f9fa7-4d38-4e89-90b9-ed2dd66bf6af', 'radio', 'Questions 11-14', '', '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Canadian Festival Theatre</strong></span></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "They can see a second play at a reduced price."}, {"option_text": "They can buy two tickets and get two free."}, {"option_text": "They can get a discount on Mondays."}], "question": "What special offer is there for regular theatre-goers this season?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "They are handed out at the theatre."}, {"option_text": "They provide information on the actors."}, {"option_text": "They give ideas for discussion."}], "question": "What information is given about the study guides?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "It is only for those over 65"}, {"option_text": "It applies to a number of productions."}, {"option_text": "It includes a 5% reduction on gifts."}], "question": "What information is given about the ''Bring a friend'' special?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "He may retire from acting soon."}, {"option_text": "He writes his own plays"}, {"option_text": "He prefers acting in films to performing live."}], "question": "What does Michael say about the actor Christopher Plunket?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fa6d51ad-b10c-4a83-a9d7-c6dfc82a7d17', '6259a8b7-a323-45d5-bc60-9fc5a5f3de77', 'fillup', 'Questions 7–10', '<p data-start="606" data-end="678">Complete the table below.</p>
